That takes optimism and trust you rarely find. While he was too busy to hang out it was not for lack of caring and I would absolutely come through Copenhagen to spend a proper day getting to know Copenhagen from him.

Hadi turned out to be an enigmatic man, being modest as he is, the profile doesn't brag much about him. But I prodded around a bit and turned out he's an upcoming YouTube star, an entrepreneur and also has a few cameos in Danish films as feathers to his hat!

Anyway, we were able to share some good times. :-) We got few little misunderstandings but in both side we enjoyed to meet each other. Hope you the best in your bike trip. Drive safe! :-)

Erik bought us chocolate and made us a lovely Swedish breakfast. We had fun, just by talking and a cup of tea. He played in a cute way with our son!

Erik was one hell of a guest! Super friendly, awesome guy. We share the same couchsurfing / life  philosophy and we had an amazing time together. He cooked amazing breakfast and dinner, we played games and talked about philosophy.
He's now biking from Sweden to Portugal and I reccomend anyone to help him in his hard journey.  He's an awesome person and I hope we meet again in the future!

Erik is a young, fresh and obliging man with a positive attitude. He loves the adventure and being around the world. Right now he is on a bike trip from Sweden to Lissabon on his own, which is mind-blowing for me. If didn't have other plans, I would have just joined him.
I wish you good luck with the weather conditions and that your bike will be as persevering as you :-) Thank you for making me the Swedish-style omelette! Very tasty.

Erik is cool.
We met on his bicycle tour from Sweden to Portugal.
He is a polite guest. We had an interesting conversation and a great Swedish breakfastüëå
It was a pleasure to meet and to support his tour for Amnesty International.

Erik is a great surfer so it was a pleasure to host him for two nights. He's very polite, easy, knowledgeable, smart and fun. We had a lot of fun exploring Malm√∂ with my friends, bbqing and having a few beers in Helsingborg with another surfer. The last morning he acted yoga teacher, which was great. 
Hope to see you again! Wish you the best of luck with the bikingüòç

One of my favourite couch surfers.  I would't have had him, if I didn't know how bad getting caught by a  storm on a long cycling trip feels like. Apparently it's was great, for I got to know a warm hearted ''doubtfully Swedish '' young man cycling for a good cause... not sure about that part  xD but  Erik is  ''well mannered'' witty and ambitious about his +1000km trip. Indeed I was pampered with a late dinner after a long day at work.... something I've missed since I left my parents' house. 
If he comes across your town, don't host him.... he's mean. 
and Erik, Fuck you <¬ß
Have a safe rest of the trip and maybe I'll see you this summer in Sweden.

text: Erik is a very fun, easygoing and friendly guy. He stayed in my caravan for a couple of days and it felt like as if he almost was a part of the family.  My kids really enjoyed having here. I would definitely host him again ! :)
He is kinda really really fun and active guy :)

The condition of my accommodation was not that comfortable. Nevertheless, I thank him that he was okay with them.  Somehow, we spent all of time together during his stay. I was drinking a beer with him, having dinner. and we went to see the ocean and hike along the Northern Sweden's landscape. When we went back to my dorm, we watched a movie together too :) At the last day, I invited him to my fitness center. I like his positive emotion and energetic behavior xD. Hope to see him for the next time when I visit the other cities in Sweden.

Erik was a friendly couch surfer who spent 2 nights at our place. We shared a meal and shared travel stories üòä

Erik was possibly the best introduction I could get to hosting a couch surfer! A lovely,  friendly, intelligent, aware, responsible, fun, caring and considerate person...a very well balanced human being with a curiosity about the world, may he travel far and be hosted by many! :)

text:

Overall, I would just recommend anyone to stay with Yusuf. He has been a really awesome host. Thank you so much Yusuf, you made my experience in Copenhagen great. Keep in touch bud!

text:
I was only in Copenhagen for a few days, but despite that Nika, her boyfriend Marik and her roommates were so hospitable, friendly and kind in welcoming me into their home. So much so I wish I had stayed longer! It was a simple comfort just sharing a beer or breakfast together and talking about cultural intricacies, current events or wherever the conversation took us. 

Talking with Nika, gave you the sense that she really believes in the notion of traveling and how that exposure to the world outside of our little bubbles unites us and that borders are really just human institutions (I say that in the least hokey, contrived sense possible). I look forward to going back to Copenhagen again in the future and visiting them!

Nika, his boyfriend (Marek) and her 2 roomates (Shantal &Sai) made me have an amazing experience in Copenhagen, this travel was really special for me because I wanted to discover this city so badly and I could not have found a better host!
They treat me like one more member of the apartment which is quite warm, organized but overall more like a home with friends rather than just a couple of rooms.
They were extremely helpful and overall extremely nice people!
I wish you Nina and Marek the best in your new life together in Copenhagen you deserve it! keep with the same vibe and whenever I would be my home is your home! Hasta la vista!

I only had  a few days till my trip to Copenhagen and I still had no place to stay. Nika and her flatmates came to the rescue and offered me their couch. Actually couch is an understatement, I had my own room and the nicest possible treatment a couchsurfer can ever expect. Their flat is amazing and so are the people living in it. It was a very international group: Estonian, 2xSlovakian, German, French and Chilean. We had some good meals, talks and laughs and a quick stroll on the city. Long story short, if you have the privilege of of staying with Nika, consider yourself lucky. She is the nicest, sweetest person and host.
Thanks for everything! If you want some sun, then you have a place in Alicante waiting for you ;) 
PS! I still owe you a short magic show.
i hosted Mathias for 2 nights, he's a good guy, talkative, polite, interesting. we shared food and we talked about history, culture and other subjects. good experience, i recommend him.
Although we didn't spend much time together, I can at least say that Mathias is reliable.

text: My brother and I had the joy of staying with Vilhelm for two nights. We both loved his energy and his genuine nature. Vilhelm is incredibly relaxed, caring, and extremely kind. He is also very generous!!! His passion for absolutely everything is so fun to be around. Whether he is talking about something he loves or something he dislikes, he is enthusiastic in his expression and it is so infectious and refreshing. Thank you so much for taking us in Vilhelm. We loved getting to know you and you have endeared yourself to both of us. Hopefully see you in Australia or New Zealand in the near future! To anyone reading this review, if meeting interesting, and kind-natured people are high on your priority list when traveling, then definitely consider this wonderful human. ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è

It is a very cozy place and the main value is the great host, who friendly shared knowledge about culture, language, history, politics, as well as his passions for art, life and the concept of Couchsurfing.
The host has a super nice personality, he is kind and polite, ready to help you if it is needed, as well as he is able to answer all kinds of questions.
Gold.

*Thank you, Vilhelm! Wish u to have a great experience in future travels and especially exploring local places of Baltic in future days.

text:
Our stay by Vilhem was fun; actually Vilhem shared kind of the same humor we were used to have, so it was comfortable.

Thanks again Vilhem ! We hope to see you soon

Fernando is simply an amazing person!
He was kind, nice and warm to me from the very first moment and made me feel so comfortable at his place. We didn't spend much time together because he works really hard during the weekdays and he also has a quite busy life since he plays the bass guitar in two different bands. Although, the time we spent together was extremely good. We had profound conversations about many topics and I don't know how, but at the last minute he got another ticket for an amazing concert - that was supposed to be already sold out - and invited me to join him and his friends for the concert. What an incredible night!
Thank you for everything, Fernando. I hope one day to pay you back for your extraordinary hospitality and I wish you all the best for your life! ‚ù§Ô∏è

Mi primera vez en Couchsurfing y creo que he tenido mucha suerte. Fernando was such an incredible host! He hung out and chatted with us often, and even brought us into the city for an awesome city tour run by a friend of his. He had great recommendations and was extremely sweet and helpful. We had lots of great conversation and a really fun time staying with Fernando üòä
While staying with Fernando I could see everything I read about him was true. He is a nice host and thanks to his recommendations and company I had a really good time in Copenhagen :)
First experience of Couchsurfing for me, it was great ! Fernando is very nice, and sparks great conversations. Do not hesitate if you ever want to visit Paris !

Fernando is a wonderful host! His apartment is very hygge (danish coziness) with comfortable bad and so good vintage music! He lives just near the airport, and its convenient to get the downtown by metro (15 min)
He met me and my friend and was really friendly. Despite he was at work most of the time, once we hang out with him and also spent great evenings by talking and mornings with tasty coffee:)
I stayed there 2 days with friend and 2 day by my own. Fernando is so kind and reliable. Some of the days i came a bit late and he was feel okay with it, that is really important thing for me (coz when you r a tourist sometimes u wanna see the night life)
Thank you Fernando for your great contribution in my first couch surfing experience!:))

We had just a short stay with Fernando as we had a 15 layover in Copenhagen, but we met with him in town and stayed at his place before our flight the next morning. Fernando was great fun and we had a lot to talk about, he's super friendly and listens very very well and has a lot of cool things to talk about. We had only 5 minutes to walk to our plane from his house. Which was wonderful addition to our short but intense night. 

Fernando we hope we can accommodate you on your visit to Helsinki as well as you did for us!
Un madrile√±o muy agradable que nos ha tratado genial.
Fernando was a nice host.  He was flexible with our coming and helpful. We didn‚Äôt have a lot of time to know each other but he is a kind person!
Fernando is a super friendly and helpful host. True gentleman. 5*

Very nice person :) 
Good located flat very near to a metro station. 
A clean flat with a good atmosphere that makes you feel at home. 
Very good conversations, he has much to tell because he has seen very much ! 
Good tips for what to see in Copenhagen !

We met very late because he was busy before but that was no problem because we send our request very late and he offered us his home anyway! He is very friendly and gave us always something to drink. The coffee in the morning saved my day ;). We weren't at home oftem but when we shared nice conversations and get a lots of travel tips for the city!

We spent a really good time with Fernando in Copenhagen ! My cousin Manon and I spent 3 nights at his home in a really quiet neighborhood (close to the airport), and even if it's only one room, this is so cosy and comfy ! He's a great guy who loves music and works hard ! We hadn't the occasion to cook something together, but we had conversations in the mornings and during the evenings, sharing some travel experience. 
I totally recommend him ! And I hope to have the chance to meet him again around the world ! 
You know where to stay in Belgium next time ! ;)

The stay with Fernando was my sons and mine first experience as Surfers, not only Hosts. And he absolutely made it the best we could ever wish for! He picked us up from the Airport and took us to his cute and tiny flat just a few minutes away. Fernando is a warmhearted and very friendly person, shared his bedroom and some Kakao with us. He's pretty helpful and made us feel welcome. We fully enjoyed staying with him.
Thanks for everything, Fernando, you're always welcome into the Saxon Switzerland!

Fernando! I had a great time staying with Fernando in Denmark, good conversations and he has a great taste of music! Couldn't ask for a better host there, he was fantastic! Really friendly and cool.  He suggested places to go and i had much fun during my stay in Copenhagen. Thank you Fernando for everything! And don't forget to invite me to the opening of your restaurant (whenever you feel ready to do so!)  :) good luck in everything my friend and have fun!

Fernando was such a nice host and just a human! His home is really cute and we really felt like home. Unfortunately he had to work and couldn't hang out but we still had some nice conversations in the evening and I hope next time I'm in Copenhagen we can hang much more :) he also helped us to figure out things with Danish kroners! Thank you so much Fernando! See you :)

Fernando has been a great host. Even if we met late, after his work, and that we could spend very few hours with him, he was always in for something to drink and to share some time with me and my friend I was travelling with. 
His little flat is very well converted, so there is a lot of space actually.
If you're really into music and conversations about other things that make this life so awesome, then Fernando is the perfect host.

We had a great time staying with Fernando. Even though he was working until almost midnight, he was still happy to come out to the train station and meet us, not to mention happy to host us at all! We only got to spend one night with him, but we sat up with a beer, talking about travel and cooking and couchsurfing. Fernando is a lovely guy, and even though his apartment is only one room, I would definitely recommend surfing with him while in Copenhagen.

Miki stayed with me for 2 nights in my apt in Tel Aviv.
I have Many good things to say about Miki, but where should I start with?!
He was very knowledgeable about Israel and our politics so we had a lot to talk about.
He was very friendly from the moment I saw him. We went out for a beer, watched a movie and more.
He's a great guy and I'll host him again for no doubt at all. :-)

Miki is a great person. He is fun and into politics. I stayed 5 days in his place. We had great conversations regarding Denmark, Scandinavia, Socialism, U.S. Politics, Turkey, Religion and LGBT politics. He is really intelligent and helpful. He even prepared breakfast and dinner for me (How lazy I am!). All in all, I would say my experience in Denmark became even more colorful with his company.

text: There's so much I could say about the little Danish boy.  He taught me that everyone in Denmark walks around with their bikes on their shoulders (strange!).  Miki also taught me how to catch and kill and prepare a pig from beginning to end (Gross).  Miki used to wrestle pigs when he was young, like most young men in Denmark, but now he wrestles Bulls.  Miki would also remove his shirt whenever possible (like on his farm). Miki also has a special power to look really interesting in his purse and my V-neck shirt and made everyone look at me funny.  Thanks Miki! Seriously, Miki was awesome and I already miss him!!

text: What an amazing smart, articulate, passionate, hard working, and dedicated person.  Miki is what couchsurfers is all about.  He embraces travel, meeting new people, and is very sociable.  Everyone I introduced him to loved him.  He is very respectful, polite, neat, clean, fun and friendly.  He was so easy to talk to and he tells great stories.  Miki is wise beyond his years with a big heart. I now consider him a friend, and eagerly await hearing about all the great things he will do in the political/human rights arena.  My best couchsurfer's experience yet.

text: Miki doesn't have a lot of time to spend together, but he was very friendly and gave me everything I needed. Thanks for hosting me Miki!

We did not get to meet, since my plans changed and my schedule was hectic because of an academic conference, but Miki was very welcoming and was very responsive. He seems like a really nice guy and I would really like to meet him in the future.

Being my first Couchsurfing experience, I was a bit unsure of what to expect but from the moment that I met Miki he was nothing but friendly, accommodating and had a great sense of humour.  A very knowledgable person in many respects and has plenty of travel stories to tell. A great experience and would definitely recommend staying with him! Cheers Miki!

Miki is avery friendly host. He hosted us for one night me and my friend Paul. Even if he was not very available for us because of a family dinner, which we perfectly understand, we had a god time together. We slept very well on his couch. On the morning we shared a wonderful breakfast with bread he had cooked himself! Then we hitchhiked ( luckily) to Copenhagen. :) Thank you for hosting us, you're a very good host. See you!
A great stay with Miki! He gave sound advice on where to go (especially enjoyed Kronborg castle and the Maritime Museum in Helsing√∏r). A smart, learned and agreeable host for your time in Denmark.

Miki is a very nice and welcoming guy, and even though he was busy the days he hosted me and we couldn't hang out a lot, he was always helpful and friendly when he was home and gave tips on what to do and on transportation. On my first day there we also went biking in the beautiful woods close to his place, cooked, drank and talked, I had a good time. I recommend staying with him =)

Miki thanks for offering your place for me (well food, and short tour around ur neighborhood). U r an amazing man. Very hardworking, u dont realize u inspire me so i could tone down my craziness a little bit. A young man with interest in Politic, Social, Religion and much more. A good cook as well (not bad for a single man). I believe u will be someone important someday, thanks for bearing with my craziness. hope to see u again in future!!!!! thanks for inspiring me =)

Farshid is an absolutely wonderful couchsurfer who is very experienced at being a host, and therefore knows exactly how to be the best possible guest. I am very happy that I chose to host him, and feel like I've gained a valuable friend.

Although he is a doctor we talked hours about politics and culture and believe me, he is a very knowledgeable person in this sphere. Moreover, thanks to him I got acquainted with the local culture, for instance when we and his friend went to a barüòÇ  and his house and food were really cool when  we enjoyed common dinners. I stayed at Farshid's place for a little over a day and since I arrived early in Copenhagen it was great he could already open the door for me as early as 8 am. 

During the day we had multiple long conversations about different topics such as politics, history and travelling; which was great. Since Farshid had to prepare for his Danish exam, he had to study hard and I payed a visit to the city. We had dinner together and watched even Paranormal Activity 3 in the evening.

It was great to meet Farshid and he was an easy going and friendly host. So when you're around in Copenhagen and want to stay in a good location with a flexible and friendly host; you should definitely go to Farshid's.

Farshid was a great host! Very knowledgeable about the world and Copenhagen especially. He taught me a Danish game and also cooked for me. Had a great time with him and really made me feel welcome! I would recommend him :)

text: What a kind hearted and knowledgeable guy! He kindly accepted my last-minute CS request, and shared with me his food, drinks and room. We talked a great deal about culture, history and philosophy, and we exchanged book recommendations on these topics too- he is also a big reader. He was willing to share a lot of funny stories and good tips about his home country Iran, and he is an absolute language talent, speaking an incredible amount  (he learned German fluently in 5 months)!!! It was an absolute pleasure to meet him and I look forward to host him when he comes to visit me in Oslo, Norway.

Farshid is a great guy and host. I met him on my way to the USA (my flight departed in Copenhagen).
He let me stay at his place and even though I had to leave very early the next day, he managed to show me the whole city (he can tell you great stories about it) and we even played a Danish version of billiard. Thank you! Hope our paths will cross again. I highly recommend to stay with him.
A nice and gentle guy. A pleasure to talk with and simply a great host.

Farshid is an amazing person and a wonderful host. I stayed at his place in Copenhagen for three nights and I enjoyed it a lot. Farshid is a very intelligent and knowledgeable guy and we had long conversations about various topics, such as languages, history, culture and politics. Farshid gave me many advices on what to see in Copenhagen, and we visited many cool places together, like Christiania and the less touristic N√∏rrebro area. 
Besides that we had delicious food  and enjoyed whatching Stranger Things.
If you have the opportunity to meet Farshid, don't hesitate to do so, it will definitely be one of these experiences which make Couchsurfing so amazing!

Ah and got good travel advises for Iran, looking forward to see your country in a month. Take care Farshid :)

Farcid is a very nice host. My request was very last minute, but he accepted for me, even if it was 3days before his moving to Denmark...We walked around the city and cooked dinner together.
He always cared if I  am comfortable or not.He knows very well about Japan and has a sense of humor, friendly, thoughtful, kind, knowledgeable and interesting  person, very recommended!

Also he has a lot of traveling stories, form countries what are so exciting e.g. Dagestan and Chechenya. It was amazing to listen and share our thoughts.
It was just a short stay, but one of the most memorable couchsurfing experience.  I hope soon we will meet again, and can spend more nights/days together.

Wish you all the best, see you soon!

text:
Farshid is a very nice, polite and friendly guy who let me stay for more than one week in his flat in Baku. The flat is spacious and with easy bus connections to the center of the city. The neighbourhood has also a nice little cafe that serves great shashlik and cheap beer.
Together with Farshid and our friend Esaias, we also went to the mountain villages in northern Azerbaijan and had a really good time there.
Farshid is very welcome to stay at my place when he hopefully some day soon decides to visit Stockholm and I am very glad that I got to know him.

I hosted Camilla, together with her traveling companion & "chauffeur", Cecelia, for one night only, from 14th until 15th June; Another CS host canceled on them at the last minute & they desperately needed somewhere safe & secure to park their rented car....& so that's where I stepped in! (ha, ha) Upon leaving, Camilla very generously presented me with a (lovely gift of) a large bar of Cadbury dairy milk chocolate, a Nestle Aero bar + other assorted sweeties & goodies; And all this despite my two Danish guests staying with me for just one night!
Anyway, Camilla & Cecelia were both very talkative & sociable, for the few hours they stayed here, +, upon departing, left their bedroom in a immaculately pristine & spotlessly clean condition. Camilla, in particular, has spent a lot of time in Africa (i.e. 5 months in total) & can tell you all about the place. The best compliment, however, that I can pay these two affable Danes is how efficiently they packed their bags > no big huge massive suitcases for Camila & Cecelia; On the contrary, they both arrived carrying a couple of very compact, smallish shoulder bags > a pertinent reminder that "minimalism / minimalist" should be the byword of (any &) all successful travelers!

text:
Despite her best attempts to state otherwise Armina the Romanian Dragon proved to be an amazing host during my stay in Aarhus. Aside from providing a floor to sleep on and giving practical advice on places to see and the deal with public transport, she also force-fed me Romanian food and even accompanied me to a local gig. You could say it was like she was a local - not that I would, that would be far too kind! :D
Although we may be have conflicting opinions regarding hugging posture (a large height discrepancy shouldn‚Äôt leave me to do ALL the work), Armina and I bonded before my arrival, during my stay and most likely ever since I‚Äôve departed.
I look forward to seeing both her and my sleeping bag I left behind when I visit again in June.
response: {'id': '15235952', 'text': "The Australian Unicorn (aka Leon) may be a recent addition to the CS website, but is a quick enough learner to fit in perfectly in whatever circumstances he finds himself (except for the whole unicorn-ness thing). text:
Armina is a wonderful person and couch surfer. She doesn't drive, so is hitchhiking across the country, but still manages to get where she is going when she says she will.

{'id': '11589703', 'text': 'Tea and books. 

The first thing I did as soon as I entered their home (after I was affectionately attacked by the energetic and super-friendly Harley and Scout) was pick up a book from one of the many book piles along their walls and cuddle on their sofa. And that was more or less what I did for the following 3 days I was in Medicine Hat! text:
Armina and Paolo were wonderful hosts! They accepted our request, even though they were arriving back late with a friend who was also staying over. They informed us of this, told us their schedule and kept in touch so that everything went smoothly. We were instantly made to feel welcome in their home, and found ourselves in a very comfortable environment.

Armina is a relaxed person with a wonderful personality. Talking with her was very easy and enjoyable. She also gave practical information for our time in the city which came in very handy. We had a better time in Copenhagen as a result of the things she told us. Paulo is lovely and is perfect for a calm discussion and amazing pie/quiche!

We are very grateful to Armina and Paulo for the wonderful time we had staying with them. We are fortunate that we got to meet them, and we hope that we can see each other again :)

Armina and Paolo welcomed me into their home even though they were in the process of moving and had just returned from a trip! I was so sad I had limited time to spend with them, for both of them exuded a steady warmth and are just the type of genuine and caring individuals that will make you fall in love with CS all over again. Thank you Armina + Paolo for your hospitality, inquisitiveness, and excellent company. I hope to meet you again soon!

Armina is one of the kindest people I have ever had the chance to meet. She and Paolo were generous enough to host me not once but twice in Copenhagen. I loved visiting Hans Christen Anderson's grave, playing board games at the board game cafe together, and talking about everything on long walks in the city. I wish that I could have stayed longer (or just move to CPH so that we can be IRL friends). I feel so lucky to have met Armina & Paolo and hope that we can stay in touch for many years to come. No idea where I'll end up, but you two are always more than welcome on my couch üåª‚ù§Ô∏è

How can't you not love having Armina as your host? She is super sweet, attentive, fun, and chilled. We should repeat this again during winter so we can watch 3 tons of movies/docs + 200 series! Thanks you :)

Super postive experience with Armina and Paolo! They are the kind of person that you wish to meet, and not only trough couchsurfing. Thanks again for everything ! Oh and the boiled egg for snack was a great idea ! :)

Armina is really kind and respectful parson.
At first, I had intended to stay her room for two night, but I had to find a hostel or some thing since my plan had been changed. And she kindly said to me "you can stay here for three nights!".

She is kinda unique parson, and it was really enjoyable and interesting to talk with her.

response: {'id': '15704788', 'text': "all the rumours are true! tatsuya is possibly one of the nicest, most polite and most considerate couchsurfers i've ever met! \r\nhe was very independent, which worked great with my hectic schedule, but also generous enough to share some of his exciting stories from his great adventure around the world. i really enjoyed the little time we actually got to talk - he takes the time to choose his words, which is a pleasant change from our hyperactive times. i wish we could have talked more about japan (and not just vending machines ;) ), but perhaps next time we meet, it will be closer to his home.\r\nbest of luck on your journey! domo arigatou for the delicious miso! :D and i hope you find the secret to happiness!", 'createdDate': '2014-07-07T14:07:23Z', 'experience': 'positive', 'relationshipType': 'host', 'isPostTrip': False, 'to': {'id': '1002620811'}, 'from': {'id': '1743532', 'publicName': 'Armina', 'publicAddress': {'id': '4448654', 'description': 'K√∏benhavn, K√∏benhavn, Denmark'}, 'avatarUrl': 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/ht-images.couchsurfing.com/u/1743532/4d7c65ce-8504-418a-a100-9e4f56f5679c', 'status': 'maybe', 'isVerified': True, 'isDeleted': False, 'blockedBy': None}, 'inverseReference': None, 'response': None}

text:
Armina and I met while couchsurfing in Reykjavik and I instantly felt comfortable around her. We found out we were on the same flight to London together and decided to join forces to hitchhike to Keflavik. (We were successful, even after stopping for a delicious raw food lunch en route!) When I lost my bank card in the Icelandair terminal, she loaned me forty quid so I could get to my friend's house from Heathrow - a true lifesaver. 

Fast forward half a year, & I found myself with a cheap flight to Edinburgh - of course I had to hitchhike up to say hello! I discovered a quaint town w/a surprising amount of life for its size. With all the potlucks on, we ate well, & even though Armina was busy with schoolwork she was completely hospitable & all but let me take over her room entirely. In between walks on the beach & stuffing my face, it was nice just to lie in, drink tea, putz around on the internet, & talk to her nice flatmates. Thanks for the haircut, too, Armina!

Maybe I have never had such a funny, truly and interesting talk with someone else I've never met before...
I absolutely recommend to host her anywhere but Glasgow, I want to host her myself here! :D

text: Toai was a great host! I landed early in the morning and he still picked me up and brought me to his apartment. Even thought he was traveling to Brazil the following day, he let me stay and I‚Äôm grateful for it. He showed me around and was extremely nice, respectful and helpful. His place is 45 minutes away from the center by walk, but as you may know you can get there by bike or even bus in about 5-15 minutes.

At the beginning Toai declined my request because I couldn't host me. However, I really wanted to stay at his home and I texted him again. And although he offered me to stay at his place for 2 nights, I was 3! 
Even I arrived too late (I apologize again), he was waiting for me. We had 3 fantastic days which were full of laugher, I tried Danish food which he cooked for me, we went for a walk and we took a beer :D 
Without any doubt, I'll go back to Toai's home, at least, when living in Copenhagen ;)

I had a very pleasant stay at Toai. He was very caring and attentive. Even before my arrival he was texting me regularly to update me on how the weather was going to be, advice me on which transportation tickets I should buy (he even told me the prices in euros so I didn't even have to bother about conversion).We met at Central Station and later in the day we went sightseeing and had a couple of beers while admiring this beautiful city. The next day he had to work but met again and went exploring a bit more. 
He answered all my questions about the country, how it is to live there .. everything I wanted to know.
I highly recommend this host.
Toai, thanks again for making my stay in Copenhagen so lovely.
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Porto Alegre, State of Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil

text:
Toai offered me to stay at his place in Copenhagen for 3 nights, and from beginning he was very considerate and texted regularly to get to know me and make sure I had all information needed.
There, I slept in the living room, which was very comfortable. 
Toai was fun and talkative, though he was sick during first days and was not able to join me outside, which was not a problem. In the evenings we would hang out watching tv, talking and drinking wine :) He  ordered sushi one night, which was very nice of him. His son was also hanging out in the living room playing in the computer most of the time.
In the last day we went outside and he showed me some places, had lunch and coffee. Also we went to his work place to print my boarding pass, which I really appreciated.
Thanks a lot for hosting me and wish you a wonderful time in your next planned trips! :)

Toai was very caring, kind and attentive from the beginning. He didn't mind hosting me for just one night instead of four when my flight got cancelled the very day I was travelling to Copenhagen, managing to fly there three days later than expected. He picked me up from the airport even though the flight got delayed and it was lateat night and showed me how to move around the city. As he was working next day we didn't have the chance to spend time together. However, he texted me by the time he came back to his place so I could go to take my luggage and run to the airport. In spite of being a flying visit, I'm so glad Toai was my host and couldn't ask for a better one on my first wee Couchsurfing experience. Hope to come back to Copenhagen some day and meet Toai when I do, thank you so much!

He's very friendly, I spent two nights with him, we talked a lot about Denmark and Chile. He was very kind to me, he helped me find a room to rent and he even accompanied me to see one. Toai I hope everything goes very well in your life, thanks for opening the doors of your house !!

The moment we meet, we got the good vibes.
 From the very  begining I had a feeling I am visiting a friend, not a stranger. We cooked dinner, and spend a nice day, cruising in Copenhagen. He showed me nice spots, and was not lazy to do anything, what I wanted to do or see. Toai is such a nice and friendly person. He will make sure, that you feel good during your stay.  Glad we meet, and see you again! :)

Toai has a genuine intention of meeting new people. He enjoy to hang out with his guests and show them the city. He is a very calm person and normally spends his weekends at home. As a host he ordered sushi for us and opened two bottles of his wines, what was very nice and kind from him. His house is located at a nice neighborhood, 15 minutes by bus from the Central Station. His house has two rooms, (his room and his son's room). I stayed in the living room. If you are looking for a relaxing moment in CPH, Toai will be perfect for you. If you are looking for party, you should look for another person.
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Canoas, Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil

I was very grateful for Taoi for taking me in when I first got to Copenhagen! He's extremely nice and also helpful -- you should see his available shampoo collection !! :) He gave me a lot of good tips and helped me with directions. His home is lovely and cozy, in a very convenient location. Our time together was short, but he was such a great host and a really nice guy!! He also introduced me to a new flavour of Fanta that I've never tried before :) I really hope I can return the favour and help him find hosts in California!

Toai hosted me and my friend during our trip to Copenhagen for 2 nights. He is kind, friendly and funny. I recommend him, he's a good host.
Thank you Toai :)

Toai was great! He made me and my friend Oksana feel super comfortable.  He had great recommendations on where to go and spent one day hanging out with us when he was free. His apartment is in a great location and he gave me detailed directions on how to get there. Thank you :)

Toai was a really nice host for me and my friend. It was so nice of him that he allowed us to stay in his couch because that morning when me and my friend landed in Copenhagen he landed from New York and hour later. Thus, we all me at the airport and he picked us up home by cab. Toai even managed to get us city maps after he got off the plane before meeting us. He as a very nice flat which he shares with his son. Toai has traveled a lot and it is so easy to find thing in common with him. I would really recommend Toai as a host! :)

Toai is a kind, cheeky, funny person. He has been kind enough to tolerate with my changes due to some unforeseen circumstances. He hosted me for two nights with my friend, Syima, great hospitality & company from Toai and his son Gabriel. Toai was always checking on us during our visits to the city when he was away at work. text:

As he had to recover a little bit after his trip, I enjoyed discovering his very nice and lively area (N√∏rrebro). 
We watched films together and shared a good dinner with him and his son, and it was relaxing after hours of walking in the beautiful K√∏benhavn.

Toai is a really nice and friendly person. He is also very hospitable and I really appreciate that. Although we only met for one evening, the conversation we had was great and it was a lot of fun!

Toai was very kind to send an invitation to allow my friend and I to stay at his place while we were visiting Copenhagen. Toai is very kind, friendly, and easy going. Our stay in Copenhagen during New Years Eve would not have been the same anywhere else, thank you for the wonderful experience!

text: Toai is such a sweet and lovely person to spend time with! He was so patient with me! Unfortunately we spent only an afternoon together but he showed me around and he really was a gentleman. Thank you for your company!

Toai is a very kind, calm, and also very very helpful person, he cooked us winter time danish dinner it was delicious, and help a lot with the transport system too. He is a good host, i can recommend him :))! It was a nice trip! Thanks for it!

Toai provided me with a place to sleep after I had problems with contacting my original host. He was friendly, helpful and made me feel comfortable and at ease during my stay. Thank you so much for providing such a positive experience and I wish you the best.

I stayed with Taoi with my sister during a difficult time over a year ago and he was such a gracious host! I really appreciate the connection we had, the dinners he and his housemate made for us and the hospitality bestowed. If you're ever in the US, come visit Michigan!
Toai was a very welcoming and generous host. I enjoyed spending time with him and his son Gabriel.

Toai is helpful and kind man. Even i was late with hitchhiking and arrived at 2 o'clock in the night - he still waited for me and opened his home :). I really appreciate it! Toai very positive person and gives a big respect to his guests. He has nice son Gabriel and it was interesting family experience for me! Toai can provide good company and spend nice time :)! Thank you so much for help in my first visit of Denmark! :)

Toai is a professional host, putting all his efforts in making your stay as comfortable as possible by explaining all the details, giving directions, checking timetables, etc. He took me on a day trip to the countryside and I joined him and his friends on other outings. Toai's heart is in connecting with people and he has friends all over the world. Thanks, Toai, for everything!
Thanks for hosting me!!! Have a nice trip to Russia! See you :)

Thank you again for that great time!

text: Toai is a very nice, helpful, easy going and warm hearted person. He was very hospitable, picked us up from the train station. We had really good time in Copenhagen thanks to his hospitality! Thanks, Toai for hosting us!

Toai is a very thoughtful and kind person.He cooked a Danish dish for me on the 1st night and the 2nd night we enjoyed Asian dinner together with Melissa!It was a fun experience cooking and eating together!He's trustworthy and fun!I felt at home when I surfed at Toai's house.He even had the city map in his house.Thank you very much Toai!Thank you for providing me a home in Copenhagen.Hope to see you soon!Take care!^^

Toai hosted me and my friend for 3 nights in Copenhagen. He is a super friendly, open minded man, who is very intelligent and funny. He helped us very much for example with tickets to Malmo, Gothenburg and back, he also gave us a map and recommended places to visit in CPH. :) We also spent some time in the evening every day and just talking about everything. :) Last day when our Scandinavia trip was mostly finished, he helped us with suitcases, escorted us to the metro station and he waved goodbye to us :) We really enjoyed time in CPH with you and you are always very welcome in Czech republic! :) It will be nice to see you again. :)

Toai is a really nice person! He helped us out when we were looking for a place in Copenhaguen and the staying was above expectations! He's calm and open-minded. We had interesting conversations and he cooked danish food for us.

Toai is one of the bests hosts I ever experienced. He was restless in finding information so that I could do everything I wanted. We shared meals, conversations and walked around, went to parties, met people. He is partly responsible for Copenhagen being so nice!

I surfed Toais couch 3 nights. Everything was o.k. Its not the best place if you decide to go clubbing in copenhagen,cause Toai does not has a spare key so you will have problems to get in, during the night. Except this point everything is fine.Thank you Toai.
Very good Host:)

text:
Wow! I think it was our best host ever! 
Me and my girlfriend Andriana stayed at Fernando's place for 3 nights. His apartment located in quite and beautiful neighborhood, only 30-35 minutes by walk from the city center. His apartment is very cozy and comfortable. In our first evening Fernando cooked for us vegan lasagne and it was perfect, especially with red wine which he also offered for us.  

Fernando is very positive, hospitable and always smiling guy with a good sense of humor. We spent a lot of time together - watching TV show called Bridge, speaked about everything (about vegans/vegetarians, about government, policy, music, movies, traveling, etc.). I need to say more about music - Fernando is a big music fan and he also a guitar and piano player, we even realized that we have  few favorites bands in common!  

Fernando showed us a nice place, called Bastard Cafe, where you can grab some beer, tea, etc., and play board games. We spent there3 hours playing board games :) Also he has his own google map page with good places to visit for tourists. 

Fernando was very kind and he let us use his bikes to take a trip to a beach not so far from his place. 

I can strongly recommend Fernando as a host, he is just perfect! 

P. S. Thank you, man, for your kindness and hospitality. I think you made our Copenhagen-Malmo journey happier and warmer :)

I stayed at Fernando's just for one evening and night, but those several hours will stay in my memory more than the whole day of exploring Copenhagen before. Fernando is not only the great, friendly and caring host but also a super funny guy to chat with and make jokes on everything together! He met me at home with the best vegetarian dinner I ever tried, then we made a big late-evening ride on bikes through that killing frost, tried a mysterious hot wine that actually didn't contain any wine and ended the night with a nice cup of tea talking about music, traveling, Siberian insects and weird showers :D 
When I come back to see the rest of cool things that Fer showed me on the map, I would definitely get the chance to stay with him again!

I like to use Couchsurfing because I can meet people like Fernando. It was one of my best Couchsurfing experience!
He was so kind to me, even gave me his bicycle. We have been talking for 6-7 hours in a row during the evenings and I haven't even noticed, how the time has passed. Fernando is intelligent, interesting, open-minded and have a lot of experience to share. I definitely hope, that I found a new friend and that I will see him again some day!
So see you, Fernando! :*

text:
Sune has a nice little falt (although not that little) quite conveniently located (near a very nice cemetary to visit) and that he keeps very clean. The kitchen is wicked and I just LOVED the window in it (lots of light in this well decorated flat). He sent be useful directions and replied quickly to my urgent request, being very efficient to communicate.
Sune is a gentle and nice person, probably shy by nature and the fact he hosts so many strangers shows his kindness and envy to help. I had an amazing breakfast that he prepared for me, and I felt completely safe (quite important for a young woman who travels alone). It was nice to meet him in the evening and discuss about my day and our lives. 
Thanks for everything - I hope all your hosts treat you the way you deserve!

We stayed with Antonello's friend. Antonello was nice guy who wanted to hang out with us. Shame that we didn't have time to meet.

Antonello was a wonderful host in many ways. He waited for me at the station when I got lost, we drank wine and had good conversations, he made us a great dinner. He was fun and  helpful, and helped me figure out flight details for the next part of my trip. 
I personally would not stay with Antonello again because I felt uncomfortable. Maybe I was giving off the wrong vibe, but there were a few instances where I felt my boundaries crossed, and I wanted to leave (unclear sleeping situation, offering massage). I think Antonello is a good person, but as a woman traveling alone I felt put in an uncomfortable situation. We talked about it after, and we went out for drinks and he showed me around London at night, and I feel like everything was okay. I am sorry to leave a kind of negative review but I think couchsurfing only works if people are honest about their experiences. 

I wish Antonello the best and I'm sure he would be a great host for most people, I just personally wasn't sure what was expected of me and felt weird about the whole situation.

text:
That was a classical example of bad match of the surfer and the host.
Antonello keeps telling that CS has changed and people don't understand CS spirit now. What he means it that he gains less profit from his Couchsurfers now. So, let me describe Antonello's perfect surfer:
She's a free girl who doesn't mind sharing the bed, blanket, pillow, preferably friend with benefits. Pole dancers welcomed (seriously, he showed me around 30 photos of half-naked girl in pole dance poses, saying over and over again"she was such a good surfer, so beautiful"),  who welcomes host with crate of beers and 1-hour full-body massage (another two examples of Antonello's best surfers). She parties whole night, smokes weed, drinks rivers of alkohol and next morning clean ups everything. If the description matches you, Antonello is your perfect host. Mine wasn't.
He was hard to reach on the phone and didn't answer messages back. The first day when we suppose to "stay in touch", until 22:00 I couldn't contact him and didn't know if I have or don't have place to stay. And when I finally reached his place, he was surprised to see me! Or maybe too drank and stoned to remeber that he suppose to host me.
When I reached the place, it was a party with lots of alkohol and weed there. It could  feel overwhelming but actually his friends and flatmates turned out to be the best part of my staying at Antonello's house. Warm, full of energy and curious, during that one night they spoke with me more than Antonllo during my whole stay. I wish I could spend more time with them, but they disapper the next morning.
And yes, I was aware he offers shared bed and I kindly choosed floor. What I was not aware of that he won't give me any pillow or blanket, which brings me to the question- if I share the bed with him, would we also share pillow and blanket? Seems too intimate for a CS for me... So I slept like a homeless, using my clothes and scarfs as a pillow and cover.
The house was also extremely dirty, just being in the kitchen after the party was a biohazard (seriously- I can send you photos!). And, funny thing- I guess Antonello except me to clean all that mess for exchange to his great "hospitality". 
And when he asked me how is his hosting and I replied "acceptable" he said " acceptable? Such a high expectation for a Couchsurfer" like offering roof above the head should make me to praise him like God.
So, Antonello was not a good CS host. Actually, my worse cs experience ever. Definitelly not recomended!

Antonello was very kind and even though it was raining, he took me to some nice places by car and he introduced me to a friend of his. text:
Antonello hosted me and two friends. He was always available for asking for help and he made a big welcome with delicious food and a cool party including two other couchsurfers. He took us on a boat trip and gave us recommendations for our hike in the beautiful national park. 
He is definitely a party guy, a good cook and he loves italian jokes. 
I am not sure if he liked our delicious german food but we gave our best to show us from a good side.
We hope, he enjoyed our company. 
Thank you Antonello for everything. I don't have final words to say because you are colorful like a parrot. 
Next time in Sardegna I want to explore Baunei and more of the national park...
Take care, stay happy and healthy and say HI to your brother.

text:
Antonello was a very gracious host. For a couple days when he wasn't to swamped with work he taught me some Italian and cooked some wonderful traditional Sardinian food!

The "couch" was hardly a couch but the spare apartment he rents out in the summer. I was amazed at what luxury living I had! My own bedroom and washroom as well as I private kitchen/living area. With a vehicle the location is perfect for visiting much of the amazing sights in the area. On foot you can see a fair bit but it'll take a little while, however people are very friendly to hitchhikers! A couple even pulled over to drive me into town when I didn't even put my thumb up.

text: Mourad was an excellent guest. One of my best experiences with couchsurfing and exactly the kind of person I love having around. He cooked me dinner just after he arrived when I was exhausted after work. What a guy. Handsome as hell, funny, easy-going, intelligent and full of ideas and thoughts he wanted to share. Thank you so much for your visit and remember my doors are always open for you and your family.

Mourad hosted me and my friend for a weekend

Although he was busy with the assignments during the day, we spent the evenings exploring some of not touristic locations and night life of Copenhagen

text: Mourad is a friendly and interesting host. I recommend him for any type of stay in Copenhagen :)

Mourad was my first ever host on Couchsurfing and he set the bar really high! He is really friendly and open minded person. I stayed in his room in a dorm for students and even got a chance to meet his friends (which can give you the idea how Copenhagen students live like!). 
On the first evening we went to the pub for a hip-hop open mic event. Ask Mourad to rap or dance for you, you won‚Äôt regret it! üòé On the second day we went with his friends to a birthday party in a club. Even though he left earlier, I had amaaaazing time and met tens of locals there. 
For sure I would recommend Mourad as a host, he is super friendly and open for new people, it‚Äôs really easy to catch good contact with him immediately! And his taste of music is amazing. You won‚Äôt regret it!

text: Adam is a great person with a comfortable little home. We really enjoyed his companionship - He even picked us up from the Bus Station. Most importantly: we had great conversations and I am thankful that we had the possibility to get to know him. Thanks, Adam.

Adam is smart, funny and very friendly. I had a great time with him and definitely coming back again,hopefully soon üòâ He is very positive and open minded person. We went hiking, biking and at the end of the day we went out for beer. You never get bored with him. Thank you for wonderful time. You are always welcome in my place as well. Good luck and stay free in your heart like a bird in the sky üòâ

Maria and her boyfriend Konstantin were both incredibly nice and interesting people. Even though Maria was super busy with work while I was staying they always made me feel welcome and included, whether it was having dinner together or going out with their friends. I'd absolutely recommend, I had a great time!

Maria and Kostantin are such a kind and helpful host. Although they have busy work during weekday, they tried to help us as much as they could and I truly appreciate it! We had a dinner with them at their home, and we had a very nice chat about our home country and travel experiences. They are such an interesting people meanwhile willing to share their stories. Their house is tidy and the the room is so cozy. We are glad to meet them and we enjoyed the stay very much!
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Hong Kong Island, Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, China

text: Maria was very kind to us and even walked us from the train station to her house since it can be tricky to find. We were a bit tired from travel and was happy to let us sleep in while she went to work. She made us feel very welcome. Thank you again!
I very appreciated the place, which was very cosy and neat. I had time to rest after a crazy day of sightseeing. Both, Maria and Konstantin were very nice people!

Safi first request was in October but something happened so he could only come in late December. But we kept in touch regularly on whatsapp. Safi is a very nice and friendly guy and I enjoyed our talks about Afghanistan a country I visited about 30 times and the country where he was born and also about other interesting topics. I took him to my friend's Shabbat dinner and my friend Yisroel thought of Safi a very nice guy. Safi come as a couchsurfer but left as a good friend. Thank you Safi for the nice gifts from Denmark. And thanks for the nice msg u left and the ginger biscuits on the day you left. My place will always be open to you anytime you visit London so come again whenever u want. Or maybe I'll visit u in Denmark too. Keep in touch and come again, you'll always be welcome here.

Haseeb is very calm, tranquil and outgoing at the same time. Even though i just stayed one day i really enjoyed my time talking to him.    By the way a super impressiv morning routine and tasty breakfirst  (:
Definitely one down to earth guy only spent 1 day with Haseeb but he is genuine an a cool interesting guy.

Safi was literally the ideal host, I wouldn't imagine my first time to the beloved Copenhagen to be more convenient, because of what he did, Safi offered me very nice vegan meals, and also gave me some advice on how and where to go in the city.
Can't wait to see you again my friend...Ahmed
Amazing host. Welcoming, humble generous, and a great storyteller. I only have good things to say. Will definitely visit or host in the future. A new friend.

Safi was so incredibly welcoming and hospitable. I stayed for one night as I had an extended layover in Copenhagen and he had a warm, and delicious, meal waiting for me. I wish I could have had something to offer in return, I'll for sure return the favor in Canada! I found Safi very easy to talk to, it was fascinating hearing about his time in Ghana! All the best and thanks again man!
Haseeb was the best host ever. He is an opend minded, good-to-talk-to, fun person. He even prepared dinner and breakfast for me! Thanks for everything Haseeb! :)

Safi is a remarkable host. I stayed with him 4 nights and I felt like home. He is nice, open minded, and always helpful and talkative. He is a really funny guy. We had good (and funny) discussions. Good luck for your exam my friend, and see you soon I hope, in Paris, Amsterdam or Copenhagen ;)

My stay with Haseeb was very positive! He even was okay that I arrived one day earlier. Haseeb is very kind and thoughtful person. He cooked tasty vegan food but warn him if you are okay with spicy meal not to be turned into firebreathing dragon, haha))
He is the one easy and interesting to speak with about many topics especially traveling, spiritual, culture and politics. Very well executed and curious about lot of things. Thanks to Haseeb I know some basic information about Afganistan. 
Was pleasure to meet you Haseeb!
You are welcome in Ukraine)
Greetings 
Andrii

Haseeb let me stay at his couch for one night very spontaneously, cause i didn't know where to go.
He is a very nice and calm person.
I got tasty food for dinner and breakfast. Had great conversations about politics and society.
I really enjoyed it.
Thanks man

I was glad to have met safi. He is a very happy and sympathetic guy.
I could finally stay a bit  longer than I thought, I appreciated that very much. He was very nice, gave me a key and cooked me a great Chinese soup. I felt very welcome. Thanks!  :)
Unfortunately we did not have much time together (because of me) but hopefully we will catch up and go to grab a beer or hang out.
If you travel through switzerland at any time, please let me know, you are always welcome!

Haseeb was a very accommodating host and great guide to have for Copenhagen, he showed me a very fun time :) He was very easy to talk to, having a diverse collection of knowledge and experiences. I'm happy i got to meet him!

Safi ! I'm really thankfull for your help kindness and generosity ! 
I had a sature nice time with you, biking in the city, laughing as a kids and philosophing in your place. 
I really hope i will see you again in the future in Paris, Morocco or anywhere else. 
Your personality inspired me and I would for sure think of you, when I will make meditation. 
All the best bro :)
Eine sehr nette person, hoffentlich bleiben wir in kontakt

Safi was a kind and delightful host. He was extremely generous with his space and time, even feeding me all the time even when I insisted he didn't have to! He also has very interesting experiences and perspectives and we had lots of stimulating conversations. Thanks for everything, Safi, hope to see you again one day! :)

Safi was a lovely host, interesting and interested, calm and knowledgeable, really thoughtful.
He cooked us dinner and breakfast, both amazing and rich, we had a nice evening with some conversations that were way beyond small-talk.
I am thankful for his hosting skills, and would gladly stay with him again.
Hope to repay the kindness someday!
See you somewhere Safi!

Safi is supper nice, friendly  and pleasant person, as well as very smart and interesting. I really enjoyed staying in his place! Also location was just perfect... very close to city center, airport or train to  Malmo. 
Thanks for hosting me, Safi! Really appreciate it!

I stayed in Hasseb crib my first two night in Copenhagen and it was great. He's a smart man...good to talk to about anything and he's also a great host. He made me dinner and breakfast...really great guy and hope I can host him back in Puerto Rico. Also the place is close to a metro station which is great to move around...or just bike from there to anywhere in the city!
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: San Juan, Puerto Rico, Puerto Rico

text: Haseeb was super host. We had fun together. He showed me many things about Copenhagen. And he made a healty breakfast. He is super cool.

Safi is kind and helpful. He was very spontaneously offering his couch. He also made a warm dinner and breakfast for me which I really appreciate. Good breakfast is a good start in the day. :-)
Thank you Safi for everything and hope you will manage everything at your university!

Definitely the best!! So happy to have met him. He's a great person! Very generous, nice, we had a ride, he showed me the entire city. He cooked dinner and breakfast. Only could host me for one day but it was great, nice breakfast and good friends along. Wish you had that job and the best for the future.

Haseeb was an amazing host, and really worked hard to make me feel at home. Chatted for hours about everything. Even invited me along to a huge dinner at his friends' flat. Had a great time, and am looking forward to traveling together in the future.
7.85/10

(jk, 10/10)

I had an incredible stay with S. He's funny, kind, intelligent, and welcoming. I felt like I was visiting a long lost family member! The building is clean and easily accessible by transit. And he's so ready to show you his gray city! The capstone was spending my
Birthday with him at Chrisitianhavn Bath. Seriously recommend this amazing human.

He is the best one of the best host who host me till now. He is totally  awesome and kind. He has so many knowledge. I feel like he is long time my friend. He show me around Copenhagen and Cristiana and it was great. I fell like totally local with him. He care  environment issues it was nice and he is careful and so much hospitality. He cook me very nice foods. I am totally recommend surf and host him you will learn many thing and spend good time. Haseeb we will see you in future somewhere, thank you for everything
Great stay in Copenhagen with Kiss. Fantastic location in the heart of the city, and a great guy. We had nights out, and listened to Brazilian funk! Thank you for being a wonderful host. Recommend!
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Cardiff, Wales, United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland

text:

We very appreciate his help, time and affords he spent on us.
Copenhagen would never be so cool without Kiss.
Thanks so much for having me! Such a great experience, the location is just amazing, now I dream of leaving in a heart of Copenhagen too :)

Kiss was an ideal host in a ideal location. He is incredibly thoughtful and knowledgeable. I felt comfortable right away,  enjoyed my stay and getting to know him. If you have to opportunity to be hosted by Kiss you will be kindly welcomed and thoroughly informed on everything you might want to need to know about being a visitor to Copenhagen.

First of all, he is very thoughtful. Thank you for that Kiss :) You did teach me a lot of things to make my trip easier. We went around together, saw some sightseeing. We had so much fun together :) His house is very beautiful and  good located. He is so clean and organized. It was inspiring :)) 
Have a great life Kiss, I hope we will see each other again! 
I recommend you to meet with him strongly!

Diogo is a champion! He lives in the best located flat in town, super clean, organized and pretty much fancy. He is super cool to hang out with, very considerate, generous, smart and toughtfull. fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil

text: Kiss really did me a huge favor and saved me by answering my really last minute request. text:
Diogo is an excellent host :)
 He is very nice, flexible, easygoing and polite.
The apartment itself is nice and clean and really well located.

text:
Diogo is a great host, he pick me up in the airport and show me how to get the metro and walk around the city, also, he send me places to go and went out at night with me to show me more places!
The apartment was in a great location and very clean and tidy!

Can thank him enough and definitely want to see him again next time that I will be in the city.

After my original host failed to tell me where and how to meet him, Lars came to rescue! He picked me up from the train station, and I got a chance to see a typical Danish home, which was very nice! I absolutely enjoyed our talks, and Lars told me many things about Scandinavia that I never knew about, and even helped me plan my next destinations.

Lars is one of the friendliest persons ever, and if given another chance, I wouldn't hesitate to couch with him again!

Lars is surely one of those deserving representatives of the humankind that make this world a better place.  He is truly kind, helpful and openminded person who is very eager to meet others and learn more about other traditions and cultures. He is also a keen traveler, so he shares this limitless desire to broaden the horizons.

He is a very artistic and knowledgeable person with great sense of humour - one more feature of him that makes a stay in his house even more pleasures. Be sure he will do his best in order to help you ensure everything for your personal comfort. The moment you get to know Lars is the moment when your acquaintance with Copenhagen and Denmark really starts - there is no doubt Lars will do his best to create a very true impression of Danish mentality: people who love life, stay calm and enjoy interacting with others. 

P.S. Your house is amazing: clean and cozy.

Lars is an outstandingly sincere, open, kindhearted and knowledgeable man. Not only did he appear an experienced host but also an utterly caring person who is very into his guests‚Äô sense of emotional comfort and relaxation. 

Moreover, we  did spend some really great time together in Malmo - truly unforgettable experience, to say the least . If you become lucky enough to have Lars as your host in future, be sure: you are doomed to fall in love with Copenhagen and have one more great friend to learn from.

Lars was everything I could have hoped for in a host. He was so kind from the moment he met me at the airport. He had great knowledge of the city and we were able to have great conversation about any topic. He spared no effort to ensure my comfort and it made my experience memorable. Lars has truly set a high bar for all my future hosts!

Lars is a very friendly and welcoming guy who makes sure his guests are okay. From the moment I arrived at his house, he made me feel at home although I was far away from my home. He is intelligent and communicates very well; we had a lot interesting talks. It is great to meet people who have the right easy going, open minded and relaxed Couchsurfing mindset. Lars has it all and hence he is a great host. I rest my case. :)
I Had nice moments with Lars in Copenhagen. it's my first good couch suffering experience. we became friends.

Lars hosted me for 3 nights. He lives in a quiet and safe area in Glostrup, easily connected to Copenhagen by train. His place is very clean and cozy. Lars makes you feel very comfortable and he is very friendly, talkative and attentive. Thanks for everything! Hope to hear from you soon.

I had really great time during my stay in Copenhagen thanks to Lars. He is super friendly and helpful, his house is really good and he likes to hang out with his surfers. He has really good stories and the chat never ends which is great. I am so glad that I stayed with him. Thanks for everything once again and hope to see you soon!
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Colchester, England, United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland

text:
There are encounters that justify to be a surfeur! I shared with Lars 3 beautiful days. We had some great moments at his home, some diners and some deep conversations about way of life and more. 
He's incredible open-minded, has a good sensitivity and a goodwill to share his vision , his passions and projects. 
He is really nice, friendly and kindly. He has been every time helpful, with a big sens of hospitality and respect.
So, don't hesitate to accept his offers, Lars is a SuperHost ;-)

This guy is the definition of a nice host! Lars is a very knowledgeable and funny guy and I felt very welcome to stay at his place since the beginning. It was really nice having dinner and sharing some stories with him. Really looking forward to coming back to Copenhagen, would definitely stay again at his place! Let‚Äôs grab a beer then... ‚Äôtil next time :)

Lars has been a really nice host. He has an excellent knowledge of Copenhagen so he helped me with transports and suggested me interresting places to visit. His house is confortable as described on his presentation. It was a pleasure!

I had a Marvelous time staying with Lars, he hosted me and my Germany friend, we had a clean and private room and we shared a lot of experiences and had a nice conversations and drinks. He is fun and easy going guy and for sure my stay in Denmark could not be the same without him and his support! Hopefully I will come back one day and for sure ask to stay with him again! Thanks Lars for all and see you somewhere around the world again soon!!!

It was my second time couchsurfing at his place and the experience was equally positive. This time we had the time to share more meals together, which was great because we talked and shared different and new experiences. And since he is naturally funny, his company is always amusing. He was just as attentive as one can be; a feature I praise him for.
A great host! No more words needed.

I have nothing but good things to say about Lars. First of all, he is such a nice and genuine guy. So so friendly and easy to talk to. The stories and experiences he's got to share are simply amazing. I was gladly surprised to find that there are still people like him in this world: Honest, transparent, nice and without an agenda. I'll be forever thankful to him, for this was my very first experience couchsurfing. And I must admit that I had my reservations at the beginning regarding surfing any couch whatsoever, but he quickly helped me realize that this can be a platform to connect with very good and interesting people out there. Not a single negative aspect in terms of my stay at his place... If anything, it was too good to be true. This won't be my last time for sure. Bottom line: You have to get to know him; he's awesome!

It's was my second time in Copenhagen and my second time and Lars home and one more time he was amazing made me and my husband feel so comfortable. Seriously I don't have words to describe how he helped us and made our stay unforgettable. Thanks so much.

Wow, where should i start, well Lars picked me up on the bus station in Kopenhagen and drove me to his place. He trusted me so much from the beginning, i got the keys to the house and a transportation card, which allowed me to use every public transport system in Kopenhagen. He showed me a bunch of cool places and he is so knowledgeable and knows a looot about his city. We went to the beach and we talked a lot about so many topics. And he is so funny too, i laughed a lot. He also changed my views in so many points completely.. but this i will tell you personally. And the highlight we made Cevape (dish) the Glostrop way and i think it is now my favorite way to eat this meal. He is a great Human Beeing so Generous and so affectionately. His Hospitality was so amazing and i can not realize it even now. I mean we didnt know us before but in these days i felt like Home or even a family member. I only can write 1000 words but this Man deserves a whole book..so just let me say: Thank youüôèüèº

Lars was a very attentive host. He offered us everything we needed. His place is also very cool. He was very relaxed and easy-going. He really made us feel like home while staying at him. And also we had great time and fun talking together. Definitely would come back again.

Lars is very kind, friendly and thoughtful person. Also He is  a real traveller and has many stories about a lot of countries. 
I can‚Äôt describe his hospitality. He picked me up from the airport, gave me  his transportation card and even ordered me dinner.  He was willing to spend his time with me. 
I really enjoyed the time i spent with him. He made me feel at home. He is the best host any surfer could ask for. I couldn‚Äôt have expected more during my stay. 
So thanks again for everything. I hope we can see each other again. You‚Äôre always welcome to Izmir!

What to say about Lars. I sincerely have no word to say how astounding my stay in Copenhagen was, definitely thanks to Lars. First of all, he offered me a couch when I was about to book something a day before my arrival in Denmark. It was the beginning of an experience I enjoyed every single second of, and will remember for a long time. That would be very hard to sum up everything I enjoyed when I stayed with Lars, but among the most remarkable things I would say that I really felt transported by all the stories about Copenhagen (and not only!) Lars told me, the places he brought me to and adviced me to go to. I had the very great chance to immerse myself in Danish way of life for those two days, and really made the most of my stay despite Copenhagen high prices thanks to Lars's help and devotion. Last but not least, the house is the most comfortable I could have wished of. 

I had the great chance to have lots of interests in common with Lars, but I would honestly blindly recommend anyone to stay with him after this so fun and interesting stay. It would be a real pleasure to stay with Lars again, I'm looking forward to this!

Lars is a super host and fantastic person. He is friendly, flexible, respectful, super interesting, joyful, kind, polite and a really generous person. I and my husband spent a very nice time with him and we felt like good friends from the first moment we met him at the airport.
To give few examples how nice he is:
He picked us up from the airport by car, drove us to the city, and drove us few times from and to the train station making our life much easier. During our stay at his place we had breakfast and dinner together plus late by night we watched movies with him and always had a very nice conversation.
About his house, it is just perfect. Better could not be.
I highly recommend Lars to all CouchSurfing members and I hope we can meet again soon.
Lars, thank you for the fantastic time together. :-)

Lars was very friendly and make my second Couchserfing experience very special. I am so thankful for his help and everything what he has done for me. He is very fun, smart, open-minded and trevel-lover person. Very recommend this host!

Lars is very openminded host, who is used to it, his cs reputation is as high as his hospitality. He knows the city and its surroundings very well and got me a tour around the districts that are easier to go to by car, so I could see a lot of interesting private parts of the city. On the last day he even took me to the airport at an early hour so Lars, thank you for that ! Out of those pragmatic nice things, i enjoyed every  meal and wine that opened to pleasant conversations. On the first day i even met an other couchsurfer that was here and we spent a amazing night at his place which is big and very open.

He is the perfect host that i would recommand to everybody who is openminded or at least tolerent. He is a free man and will judge you as an equal.

Bye Lars, hope we'll meet again soon, I'm pretty confident that we will ;-) keep contact !

Lars made my trip to Copenhagen be a very pleasant experience. he was really nice n kind with me , showing me around , chatting random n funny things and sharing life experiences. He made 
me felt at home. I can't find words to express how I enjoyed n how I am glad to have met him . I hope I can keep in touch with him n meet up again. Thanks so much ;)
The best best best host ever! I will miss you!!!! Thanks for everything. Hope to see you really soon. I would highly recommend him like host or surfer. Cheers!!!

Lars is super cool.
He invited me to say with him, we were changing some messages even before I arrive.

When I met him, he showed to be super kind, respectful and generous. It was a pleasure to meet him, to spend some time together talking about many things. He also gave me great advices about the city and other things. 

I left his place with the wish to stay a bit longer, or come back again, and I just want to thank Lars for his amazing hospitality.

Copenhagen was my second stop at Europe and I just can‚Äôt believe how wonderful time I had.

This was my time for meeting Lars, and I‚Äôm literally speechless. He is the best host I‚Äôve ever had so far. i quite felt like an unwanted host for the three days i stood at his place, althought miguel has been very nice for some other things, like he let me use his spare bike, offered awesome tea from china. but still he was afraid i just wanted a bed and didn't care about knowing the person and hanging, and then everytime i started telling about myself i would get interrupted, getting the feeling like he didn't care to listen, but just to be listened to. he is a good person and i think it's just about me and him just not getting much along, but this is what i experienced

Miguel is a very nice person! He was busy with his work, but he found time to host us. He waited for us, even though we were a little bit late because of our late flight. Totally recommended

Me and my friend spent four nights at Miguel's home, who is definitely the perfect host ever, I wish everyone who use the couchsurfing system to have the same experience! Miguel is very friendly, helpful and lot-travelled person with whom you can talking about everything and share world experiences. Even though he is Portuguese and lives in Copenhagen just for two years, he knows the city and the good places well, and could tell some interesting stories and facts about both the city and Danish people. He is flexible and easy-going, one night we cooked home dinner together and drunk great vines.:) He gave us his confidence from the first time and give us a key for the appartment, so we absolutely felt ourselves at home.
His home is also perfect, which is a very clean, tidy, comfortable and best-located appartment in the middle of the city center, in a cozy five hundred year-old house... we loved it! It's amazing how can such an old architecture mixed with modern furnitures such in a good style. We could not have had a better place to stay!
It was a great pleasure, Miguel, thank you very much again for everything and hope we can meet again somewhere in the world!:)

Miguel was a very nice host. His flat in the city centre was beautiful and tidy. Miguel is very friendly but unfortunately we hadn't enough time to hang out together but he told us some nice places to go. Definitely would stay with him again.

Miguel has been an excellent host!! he gave me all his confidence since the first moment giving me the keys of his apartment for the following day and lending me his bike which was an amazing way of discovering the city.
