It was nice to meet you guys and good luck with everything!

text: We had a lovely time staying at Veselin's place. He is kind, friendly, funny and generous, and his and Sergiu's home is beautiful. Making contact with Veselin was easy and easy-going; in spite of a few hiccups along the way, Veselin was patient throughout. And even though our schedules did not coincide, we still had some time to chat to Veselin over a glass of wine, long into the evening. What's more, the couch was very comfortable and spacious! Thank you so much Veselin. It was lovely to meet you and hopefully we can meet again next time I'm in K√∏benhavn :)

Veselin was a great host! His place is spatious, clean, full of great decoration, and a half-hour long walk from the centre. He and his flatmate were kind. Veselin showed me around on the first day, but also let me enought time and freedom to discover the city myself (even lend me his bike!). When I arrived we had delicious pancakes for breakfast, and we spent the evenings with chatting, cooking (watching him cooking), drinking wine. He is an easy-going, open-minded guy, with some cool experiences and not afraid of deep conversation. I enjoyed my stay there, hopefully see you again!

Veselin was an amazing host!!!! If you are interested in spending time with somebody with whom you can talk about everything, have a lot of fun, enjoy the city together, hear many interesting stories not only about Copenhagen, eat the best pancakes with Nutella ever and other specialties as well :):), I can definitely HIGHLY recommend him :) One more time: really big thank you Veselin and just let me know when you will be having your road trip in Poland!!!

We stayed just one night but we had a great time! We loved staying with Veselin as a first experience of couchsurfing. He gave us everything we needed and that made us very comfortable. A very nice flat, especially the hall with the self made furniture and an old piano :)

This was an amazing Couch Surfing experience! 

Veselin was extremely friendly and helpful! Although he was not in Copenhagen for our first two nights, he hosted me and my boyfriend for the last one.

Before our flight to Copenhagen he provided us with nice tipps and information about the city. 
We handed out with him after his work and enjoyed so much the conversations with him, the breakfasts we had together and of course - the delicious dinner he cooked for us before we left!

Thank you Veso for the amazing time and hope that we can host you soon in Vienna or Helsinki!

And keep the Couchsurfing spirit alive! üåû

What a lovely stay I had with Ves in Copenhagen, short but sweet. We had a super nice and chill evening together with his friends who are all really funny and open.  Ves is a truly kind, generous and joyous human being. His place is beautiful and personal, really makes you feel like home :) oh and did i mention waking up to the smell of delicious banana pancakes being offered for breakfast! Take care and keep spreading the good vibes xx

Veselin was a wonderful host! We Cooked a meal my first night there and he gave me great advice for traveling through Copenhagen and through other European counties I am planning to travel too. He is very friendly, interesting and generous. Every morning we ate traditional danish breakfast and talked about our days. Thanks for having me Veselin and making Copenhagen such a great experience for me!

Veselin was a great host! He was flexible with my delayed arrival, even when I had trouble communicating because my phone wasn't working. His place is super close to the city center, just a couple stops on the metro. He offered to take me around the city and suggested some places to stop. Though I wish we had more time to hang out (our schedules didn't work out too well!) it was a great day in Copenhagen!
The best host ever! And we had such a good time with veselin and his roommate!
It was an amazing weekend in Copenhagen üòäVeselin is very friendly and interesting guy, we had so much fun with him and his friend:) Thanks a lot for everything !

Veselin is a wonderful host! Me and my friend spent two days in his apartment. It is very clean and big. Veselin kindly shared with us his room and cooked a delicious dinner! He also gave us a map and showed places that are most worthy to visit. My CS experience with Veselin was totally great!

Veselin is very friendly. It is good fun and very caring. His home is clean and very nice, has a very good location. Veselin costs us around Copenhagen and showed the unknown landmarks. Thanks to him, the trip for me and my friend was even more beautiful and enjoyable. THANKS FOR EVERYTHING, VESAK!

text:
Dear Veselin, 
many great thanks for hosting us, although we came so late iat the night. It was very nice to get to know you and to talk with you. You are an amazing person with a lot of nice ideas and travels, so it was a great pleasure to share experience with you. I am sure we will meet again soon. And, who knows, may be we will travel together some day. Wish you all the best and you are always welcome no matter where we are!

Even though he was travelling, Veselin kindly offered me a place to stay in their flat before I could move in to my permanent apartment in Copenhagen. We only had the chance to meet on the last afternoon, I wish we had more time though, as he seemed like a person who you can have an interesting conversation with basically about anything   ...at least I could say thank you for his super-comfy bed. :) In the meanwhile, Sergiu - his flatmate -  took care that I have every evening booked and made sure that I explore the most fun places in the city. Thank you again guys, perfect start for an exchange semester! Hopefully see you soon!
PS: Awesome living room they have! ;)

Veselin was a great host, we would definitely love to stay with him again, host him some day or just meet him to hangout! When we arrived he welcomed us with an amazing meal that he had just cooked and we had a lot of fun talking all night until we realized it's 2 AM. The apartment where he and his flatmate (who is also a great guy and we spent some time with him as well) live is great and the location is perfect, it's really calm and cozy inside, at the same time it's close to the city center and all kinds of transport. Veselin was a really nice host, he made us feel at home and was helpful and kind. In the end we left hoping to see him again some day.
We had an amazing time in Copenhagen thanks to Veselin!! He was very friendly and made us feel always welcomed. Thank you so much!!

Veselin is a great guy! And his roommate Sergiu is also! And their friends are! :D I and my friend stayed with Veselin for 3 days (he allowed to stay one more day because of our mistake about plane). The evenings were full of laugh, talks and beer :) Veselin told us everything about Cph, what should we do and where to go. I feel like I've already known these fantastic guys before - so kind, respectful, knowledgeable, open and fun they are!
It was unforgettable weekend, thank you! Hope to see you again somewhere :)

Veselin and Serguo are really good people!We had good time there,and we hope to meet them again.who knows?:)
Ps: thank you for delicious meal,holograms and haircut!;)

I was so lucky to have met Veselin and his roommate, Sergiu! I stayed with them 3 nights and couldn't have been happier with my experience! Veselin was so kind and knowledgable about all things Copenhagen and as our careers aligned perfectly, we discussed and explored the architecture of the city. He took me many places which I wouldn't have known to go otherwise, and I saw the city through a designer's eyes. He was also kind to invite me along  to two electronic music events over the weekend and I experienced the joy of the summertime! I've met two new friends and will never forget my time in Copenhagen!

After this stay I will use CS wherever I can - it is amazing weekend with brilliant host. I think this is a very rare stroke of luck that I find Veselin in CPH, its something like put all your money on zero and win:-) 
My  trip starts not very good, but I was rewarded with a perfect time in the company of two smart and intelligent guys. Thanks for all one more time and I absolutely hope that we will meet again!
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Saint Petersburg, Saint Petersburg, Russian Federation

text: Veselin and his flatmate are great hosts and great personalities - cute, intelligent and funny - all at once. Veselin is a great cook, extremely friendly, talkative, smart, with a great sense of humor and a great music taste. It was fun to stay with them. We had a really nice time with his friends, did partyes, spend time on the beach, chilled on the Islands brygge, jumped in the sea. It was a lot of fun, thank you for all :)

We had great time. Veselin is very friendly, kind and helpful host. He cooked for us, gave us his own room and even adjusted his schedule because of us. We felt comfy at his place and we  enjoyed time which we spend together. He is really nice guy :)
Thank you very much!

About Veselin? Well... I think I could write an entire book about him and even that way a lot of his qualities wouldn't be meationed there.
If there is a person that can really make you feel like home is this awesome guy and his amazing roomie!
They are the most kind, fun, gracious and respectful human beings that I ever met! Probably we were really lucky because they spent a lot of time with us. We walked around the city together, we went to a party together, we had meals together, we share music that we like to each other and we talked for hours about so many different topics... it was just great! Actually, they are so fantastic that you feel that you already know them for years!
I really want you to come to visit us in Porto and I promise we will do our best to be half as good as you were!
Thanks for everything guys, let's keep in touch :)

Veselin was a truly amazing host; he welcomed us into his apartment and made us feel right at home. V  further went above and beyond to make sure we would enjoy Copenhagen to the most (including great dinner and breakfast that he made). This was only my 2nd couchsurfing experience, but I already feel like it's gonna be one of the greatest. Thank you so much, and hope to host you in Germany on one of these days.

David 

The best experience i had on couchsurfing! We were treated with absolutely utter consideration and warmth, we shared some cooking techniques but V definitively outran us with his chef-level dishes;) That he lent us his travelling card on first sight requires lot of trust and that he gave away his own room was just generous and moving... We also met the crazy funny roomie and friend of V and had thorough yet chilled talk, along with " illegal Moments", laughs and "business plans". ...

Looking forward indeed to a reunion in the very near future!

Jing

This was my first time couchsurfing and i had a really good experience. Veselin was an amazing host, always punctual, flexible with our plans, always ready to help and made us feel comfortable at his place. Plus, the location is great and the house has really good conditions. I'm really happy I had the opportunity to meet Veselin, he is a great guy and also a really good cook!

I had a really good time. Veselin was interested in me, he has read my profil and we were talking about our interests. Veselin was working as a chef so he could teach me some stuff about cooking. 
My stay really was an exchange and this is how a CS host should be! :)
I recomment him as a host. 
You are always welcome at my place.
Regitze is a kind and nice guest. Hope we'll see you again on the next season! Good luck with your journey!

Regitze stayed for two days at my place in Munich. Although I had to work quite a lot and was occupied, we managed to spend a little time together having vegan food and beers at the river in the evening. She is very reliable, flexible and an interesting person to talk to. I would definitely recommend hosting her!

I definitely recommend Regitze. She is very interesting and has a charming smile. She is kind and super friendly!
I hope to see her again when I'm less busy:)

I really spent a good time with Regitze! She is funny, thoughtful, you can talk with her about a lot of subjects because she is an open-minded person! Regitze enjoys to go outside chilling around in the city or at the lake. With her I learnt a lot about Denmark and Copenhagen, she told me her big trip and had interesting stories to share. As for her stay as a guest, she's really flexible, she keeps the house clean and always asked if I needed help! But the best part was spending time with her talking and chilling in Zurich! I recommend her either as a guest or a host! Hope to see you again Regitze!

Regitze was a very spontaneous, very flexibe kind of couchsurfer. As I don't always have time too hang out she was okay with hanging out alone or spending some time with another guest we had at the time. She' the kind of person who's easy to talk to, easy to go out with and a perfect blend into our everyday lives. Always welcome

Regitze was a great guest. We had beers and great conversation about the future of our society, sharing many opinions! We also went to a gig and had a great time. You're always welcome to come back to Brussels ! Enjoy the rest of your travel !
She is really friendly and kind!!

Lasse is a very respectful person,on time, tidy,and joyful. 
He understands German too, which was really great for me to be able to communicate. 

I highly recommend to host him, it would be a nice experience. 

Cheers!
Lasse and Martha, Lasses girlfriend was a very friendly and couple and easy to talk to. They took time playing cards with my 6 yeas old daughter and help clearing up after dinner.

I really enjoyed hosting Lasse and his girlfriend Marta! From three days we had a chance to hang out properly only once, because I was working, but the day we spent together was really great: it is nice to meet people with whom you can laugh about things, discuss common points of interests and just feel relaxed. We had a walk in Kallio district and had a drink at the local bar - it was truly pleasant experience. Guys are clean and respectful, followed house rules impeccably. I was touched that they thought about me without knowing me yet and brought me some souvenirs that I appreciate so much! I am looking forward to their possible visit in summer to share camping adventures! I am happy I have met you, hope to see you again soon!:) 
P.s. I am enjoying the tea you've left for me:))

Lasse was so mature, smart, friendly and laid-back that it was easy to have him as a guest. When you suggest or offer any thing to him, he is anxious to accept. He was gone before I know it--causing me to wish he could have stayed longer. I highly recommend him as a guest and friend.

Super great guy, very laid back and fun to hang out with. Also very intelligent & great to debate with!

text: I hosted Michael and Lasse on a last minute request, and it was a great experience! They showed up with beer and homemade schnapps from Denmark. Tansy schnapps! Now I know that a tansy is a flower. They cooked me dinner and even made me a cd of Danish oldies (which is awesome by the way!). Unfortunately we never got to go out together, but I had a great time chatting with them about all sorts of stuff! Good luck on your travels boys!

Lasse and Michael are great guys and very considerate surfers. My family and I had a great time with them; they played music for us, cooked a fine Danish meal, and even helped pick peaches at the family farm. Very easy-going and great with little kids! Would love to see these two again someday. How was the Kobe beef, guys?..

Staying with Lasse and Marta was really lovely. They are welcoming and helpful hosts. They gave me and my boyfriend useful advice on where to go and what to see in Copenhagen.
Hope to see you soon!
Also, your home is really cool, I love it :)

Staying with Lasse & Marta in Copenhagen felt like finding hidden treasure. They are genuine & generous beings; down-to-earth, funny & creative. Their clean & groovy flat somehow felt spacious even with 4 people in a one bedroom place, with us on the couch. Lasse gave us a tour around the local nature park in his cargo bike - pure simple fun and a must-do for the Copenhagen experience. It was great to spend time together over breakfast and drinking a beer later at night, and then to have space to do our own thing around the city. Loaning Lasse's bike for our adventures was perfect for this.  We travel onto our next destination hoping we see Lasse & Marta again. Tak!

Lasse and Marta are both lovely people, and that have me lots of good advice for my trip :) They have a cozy and clean home, and chatting with them, and getting to play with their little hedgehog Moritz was great fun! I'd love to stay with them again.

Marta and Lasse were super nice! They gave me an extra key so I didn't have to worry about schedules and Lasse even cooked delicious breakfast on Sunday. Had a nice time and hope to see them in Italy or Colombia!
Ps. I'm in love with their place hehe

Lasse is a lovely host that was welcoming and helpful! His place is near a beautiful park and easy to get into city center by bike or bus :) he was kind enough to cook a yummy dinner and lend me his bike. Was an honor staying with Lasse and Marta! Thanks again y'all!
Great stay in copenhagen! Hope to see soon again

Lasse and Marta welcomed me warmly in their cosy appartement, it was a pleasure to stay with them! They are very thoughtful and understanding  hosts, even though I arrived late on my first day and had to wake up very early when I left. Marta gave me a lot of useful material and advice for what to see in the city. Lasse and Marta are a really enjoyable company, I liked it very much to talk and eat with them (and of course to cuddle with their incredible cute hedgehog Moritz)! Hope to meet you again one day! :)

Lasse and his girlfriend were incredible hosts! It was a pleasure to spend a couple days with them over meals, and their place is super cozy. I especially enjoyed how much we got to talk‚Äîboth of them are on point hosts and I highly recommend staying with them if you get the opportunity.

The most happiest and comfortable CS experience I had, and it will be hard to beat üòÇ. Lease and Marta made me feel so good there in Copenhagen, we talked a lot, we shared dinners and beers, they gave me advices, they planned for me what to do in the city, where to go. At first I would be only just 2 days, but I could not see all the things in that time, and I asked to stay one more night, two days more, and without problems they said yes and made me feel so welcoming and so lucky to be with them. Now I can say I have 2 friends in Copenhagen üòÅüòÅ. I will never forget these days in Denmark, and I'll never forget Lease and Marta. It is not easy to describe everything I spent with them, I felt so lucky to meet this people. See you guys! You are more than welcoming in my house.
Lasse is so nice and handsome,the big clean apartment is full of laugh and music.he cooked for me and we talked,it's a very good conversation~

It was luck for me to meet Lasse.
I stayed with my girlfriend for 4days.
We played card game with Lasse and Eny.
It was very fun and he made us be comfortable. Last day we were took a picture together. I will miss this guy.
He is very kind and polite.

text:
Thanks Lasse, Mikkel, and Anders! That was my first couchsurfing experience, and I loved every minute of it. It was really nice of you to host us in your flat for three nights! You were very open-hearted and I enjoyed spending hours on end talking to you guys. I remember when we went out with some of your friends it was sooo much fun! Thanks so much for your hospitality and you are always welcome Austria! Hope to see you soon.

text: wuhuu, had such a great stay at lasse and mikkel's place. they are both very relaxed guys who will share their apartment with you as if you where just a regular flat mate. don't expect them to know anything about sightseeing in copenhagen from a classical point of view :) but be sure when they take you for a bars tour in their neighborhood you can have the real experience of having been to this wonderful city. thanks a lot for your generosity, welcoming and confidence guys, hope to see ya soon again!

text: Josefine was super nice! She really helped us  for our stay in Copenhagen!! Her place is great as well as the city and I can tell she's a really good person!! Hope we'll see you in Paris or Argentina one day!! :)

I was happy to stay at Josefine's place for a couple of days. Josefine is great to talk to, helpful and outgoing. Her house is amazing, located in a quiet countryside with fresh air and wonderful views. It is very easy to reach the center of Copenhagen by train. Would definitely love to see her again.

Josefine was the best Christmas present of June! I am sure, she would be the best Christmas present in any other month as well thought. She was extremely thoughtful, thinking of our well being (like of an umbrella in the rain) even  before we realized we had any needs.  After some Copenhagen experiences we loved to arrive to the quiet Vekso, make some food in the nice kitchen, have discussion over and after dinner and try to resist Armani's strategies to get extra food.  After staying a few days at her house, we felt truly relaxed, wich made our vacation even greater than we would have thought it would be. Thank you for everything!

We had a great time at Josefines place! Her house is huge and we were given our own room to sleep. Such a beautiful place and we loved getting to hang out with her as well as the two other couch surfers. She was very helpful and gave us tips as well. Thank you so much!!

Josefine was an amazing host! We requested to stay last minute and she accepted me and my friend right away. She has a great house in a nice location, close to Copenhagen. She is so hospitable to let so many couch surfers stay at her house. It was fun getting to meet her and the other couch surfers that were also staying with her.  I'm so thankful for Josefine and her welcoming heart towards couch surfers!!

Josefine hosted my housemate and me for one night, I felt so sorry forgot to make dinner for her and her sis. 
When we was there they have 4 cute and good behavior doggies, and she prepared really nice room for us. Thank you very much for hosted us. :D
Josefine let us stay in her beautiful and huge home. She's polite, friendly, nice and communicates well. It was all comfortable and chill. Would love to stay again to hang out at a more fitting time!

I remembered the dogs..the dogs were awesome. It was very nice to stay there, hang out a bit, help around, and get some rest. I liked the house, the company and most of all after days of sleeping in a car I liked the bed :D
Welcomed us despite that we were late...for like a day. Thank you for the hospitality. I just wish we were less exhausted so we could hang out more
Josefine was a very nice host, as well as her housemate and her dog :)

It was my first time to do couchsurfing. I definitely would not like to generalize and judge her hospitability with my experience, but for now I‚Äôm describing mine. I with my friend was supposed to stay for 2 nights in Denmark. Before coming we had nice conversations and arranged some plans. We arrived early morning and spend all day in the city; it was nice of her to pick up us to her place with the car. Until that everything was smooth, we were sharing experiences, etc. The fact that made us not stay for the second night was her ‚Äòrequest‚Äô to carry a big couch for about 1 km to her house. We were really tired that day and still had to spend our whole next day walking, so we refused. Her attitude afterwards wasn‚Äôt pleasant at all and I consider that trying to take advantage of us is not this community‚Äôs goal. As for me, I tried to do my best to not complicate the situation; we cooked, did the dishes and even cleaned the cooker (even if it was dirty before). It is really hard to stay in a place where you do not feel honestly welcomed. Id strongly believe it could happen to anyone to have a bad day, but treating someone unfairly while you‚Äôve subscribed for taking part in this kind of program makes me think that everyone is always doing a favor while demanding for smth in return. I‚Äôd still keep on trying this option of travelling, as I‚Äôd not like at all leaving everything with a one-sided story.
column18: {'text': "I had a bad day (eg my phone broke). He offered to help me with the couch, so I made arrangements and when he was suddenly too tired, I was disappointed. I'm not a hotel, and yes I believe in the community (give and get) this is even written in the guidelines", 'author': {'id': '2001337453', 'publicName': 'Josefine Sondergaard', 'publicAddress': {'id': '100385602', 'description': 'Veks√∏, Capital Region of Denmark, Denmark'}, 'avatarUrl': 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/ht-images.couchsurfing.com/u/2001337453/d0b9a95b-7493-4453-9780-a387f57e7845', 'status': 'yes', 'isVerified': True, 'isDeleted': False, 'blockedBy': None}, 'createdDate': '2017-05-12T04:56:39Z'}

We stayed two days with Josefine. She was extremely kind and took the time to hang out with us even though she was quite busy. She treated us with home made apple sauce and made us feel at home. It was very nice to stay with her.

We even got some homemade applesauce which I got to distribute with holiday greetings around Europe! --- the apples of Veksoe have indeed reached far afield. I hope to be able to reciprocate her generosity sometime in the near future. Glad to hear you passed your exams; Enjoy your holidays!

Jo is great!! I had a great time with her and her friends while staying at her place. She is really fun and has a great vibe, and was also very welcoming on one of my first couchsurfing experiences.
Her house was great, cozy and clean. I would definitely stay with her again and I am waiting for her in Finland üòÄ

I was staying in Josefine's house for a couple of nights and I would really like to recommend it not only because the house it's so nice and clean, in a quite neighbourhood with the station pretty close but also because Josefine proved to be a friendly person, willing to help you, calm and so on. She also have a very nice dog - that kind of dog who is very active and it's nice to play with. The house is very big with lots of facilities (multiple mattresses, blankets, even sleeping bags) and her "roommates" are also very nice persons. It was nice to meet you, Josefine, and I'm hoping to see each other again! Hope that you have a great time in Dubai!

Josefine offers a place for basically everybody. She is very hospitable.
I ended up staying there for only one night and we didn't talk too much, but as far as I've experienced, she's a nice person.

I was grateful to be hosted by Jo and her flatmates as It is pretty rare to find someone so dedicated to hosting on CS nowadays. Though only a short 36 hour visit, we managed to have good conversations, cook a delicious meal, get boozy over a game of scrabble and last but not least, breaking the law!! 
My love goes out to the adorable dog as well!!

Hope to see you on the road soon!

text: Oh la la... This woman... when i comes to the airport Copenhagen at 15:00 am I realized that was already at night and much Would not be able to Know and see in the city with the dark and cold.. so before to go lnside and alone in a hotel I opened couchsurfing and one of the profiles that most impress to me  was  of Josefina so i wrote her if she had time and was free and in 10 minutes responded that was doing a little sport but she could to host me..so  it was the best decision that I could have taken because instead to be alone seeing tv or with √≠nternet in a hotel we were talking all night with her and Daniel and another couch from Green that was also since a few days ago at home and Daniel (his roommate .. OK .. I have to clarify something...josefina says that his roommate Daniel is not in couch surfing and she suggest that let's be respectful with Daniel but I found that in a future him could become in a member of the comunity CS cause he has potencial :) and i think that he is great man spite i dont Know him so much.. and is more, i have created a profile to him (Daniel. copenh.90 is his profile) haha joke Daniel, a big hug friend ... and Josefina, you ll go have a good time with her because she has many stories , she has given a long  world tour and is Super friendly, I l√≠ke her.. a big hug guys ... I wish we let's go back to find each other :)

Josefine is really nice and friendly person. I am really grateful for her hospitality. And her roommaites are so friendly too. :) It was so nice experience to stay in her house and spent some time with all of them. :) Thank u again!

Josefine was an amazing host! She's nice, talkative, open and funny. She really went out of her way and helped us a lot (!!) by hosting us, even tought she was not at home at the time we arrived. Her roomates are awesome and she has the best dog ever :)) Josefine thank you again for everything and see you the next time you come to visit us, right?:))

We stayed with Josefine one night with my girlfriend. I wouldn't recommend her as a host. When we arrived she offered us to play card game later and we agreed. I smelled that she drank alcohol, probably she was not sober.  So there was another girl in the kitchen (Josefine's housemate's surfer), they were chatting there, so we joined. After some time Josefine left, we stayed there and continued chatting. She was cooking, and I thought we are gonna wait her and play together. After one hour Josefine just appeared and started complaining about that she was waiting for us in the living room and we didn't joined. If she wants something, she should let us know, I'm not a mind-reader, and I'm not gonna follow anybody to check what she is doing. Other day we apologized and left.

We came to Josefine's place and there was already another couchsurfer Kari, and Josefine offered to play cards. We agreed, and after some time she went to kitchen and started talking with Kari about USA and Danish politics, we joined them and stayed there, and after some time she just left kitchen. We stayed with Kari and continued talking while she was cooking and after one hour Josefine approached me and said: "you are guys not nice, I offered you to play cards and I was waiting for you for 2 hours, while you all were talking in the kitchen". I apologized and said that we had no idea why she left the kitchen, probably she wanted to do something herself, on what she replied: "do not pretend that you didn't know that. Of course I'm not going to kick you out now, but couchsurfing is not about free bed" after that she turned off lights everywhere and behaved like dictator, what made us feel really uncomfortable. In the morning we apologized again all together and left.
column18: {'text': "Its true, I would never kick someone out, no matter how rude they are (like Elvira and Lazlo). text: Jo was fantastic! Her home was lovely and her roommates were all great! Our first day she drove out to visit a castle with us and that night we all cooked and ate together.  She was even nice enough to lend us her train card which saved us a lot of money.  She's very easy going and has a lot of great stories and the world's cutest, sassiest dog.  I definitely recommend staying with her!

Staying with Jo was one of the most welcoming CS experiences I've had so far; when you meet her it feels like you've known her for years! My friend and I stayed with her for three nights, and on the first day she drove us out to a castle we had mentioned wanting to see and spent the day exploring with us. We loved staying outside of the hustle and bustle of Copenhagen in Vekso, which was quiet and beautiful, and Jo's house is wonderful as well. She is (as are each of her housemates!) a fun, friendly, and caring person with incredible stories and a true love and interest for the humans she encounters. Jo, you are always welcome in the States or the UK or wherever Sarah or I happen to be-- hopefully I will see you again in my travels soon (not kidding, let's do something before I leave Europe!) !! (And CSers, her dog is the best dog in the history of the world. Obsessed.)

Unfortunately at the time I stayed with Josephine I was quite unwell. She was very considerate though in giving me a bedroom right away and letting me just disappear into it to rest up.
I was also able to have some plesent conversation later on and she had some helpful travel tips for Copenhagen. 
Unfortunately the sharehouse WiFi was quite illusive (I never found it).
Also a very friendly canine made the experience even more enjoyable.
Josephine was also flexible when our plans changed and we left sooner than we had planned.

It was my first couchsurfing experience and I loved it. Jo has an incredible house, amazing flatmates (special mention to Nuno) and a lovely dog! But the best part was Jo's availability and friendliness. Even though she was with a project at hands for her university, she always found time to help me out and even drove me to Roskilde to see the Viking's Museum! I really loved the experience and would most definitely reccomend her!
Josefine was great host. The house was beautiful place to stay. We were happy to spend evening with all her housemates and we had lot of fun. Thank you for your time :) :) :)
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Brno, South Moravian Region, Czech Republic

text: I had a great time at Josefine's place. She picked me up at the train station with the beautiful and funny dog :) we cooked with her flatmates and we had a nice dinner all together. Josefine is very polite and funny, she is also respecting your privacy and she is very sensible.

I definitely recommend Josefine as a host. She is very open minded and easy to talk to.  She is used to host many couchsurfers, that is why you can meet many interesting people at her place. I spent there one night with my friend and we enjoyed every minute. I thank her for this experience! It was truly great.
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Brno, South Moravian Region, Czech Republic

text:
Staying with Josephine was my first surfing experience and I really love it. My girlfriend and I stayed for 3 nights at Jo's wonderful house, and we were welcomed by very flexible Josephine and her dog lovely dog Many :) Although we stayed quite long, we didn't have opportunity to bond each other a lot, what was real pity cause she seems to me as really interesting person. 
I would be more than please to meet you again, but this time in Sarajevo to show you all Balkan's hospitality and properly thank you for staying at your couch.  Stay in touch.

text:
Josefine (and her cute dog :)) were really easygoing and flexible hosts, Jo herself is a nice and quiet open person and I highly recommend her for hosting/surfing and would be happy to host her in my home too :) 
We appreciated a lot the fact that we had our own room and the liberty to come and go whenever we wanted. As all the residents of the house are used to everyday visits of couchsurfers your arrival doesn't really change the dynamics of their household.J. herself is a nice and an experienced traveler so she is used to everything and all kinds of people so you may notice that there's a certain routine with the cohabitation with travelers. I really appreciated the stay and I am  grateful but I would love to have more personal connection with people hosting me but it may be just me :)

text: Thanks Josefine for hosting my brother and I.  I appreciated your prompt responses to my messages, providing a place for us to stay and plesent conversation. Josephine lives in a lovely quiet location about 40min out of Copenhagen so we also saw another part of Denmark which was nice. Thanks again Wendy

text: Great girl,  cool dog and some awesome room mates. Very friendly.  Would definitely pop by again!

I admire Josephine for being a great host and spreading the CS spirit, she‚Äôs a very open minded and kind girl!
The house is big and had a very pleasant atmosphere. I was able to share stories and experiences with some of the other people in the house, including one other CS. They even invited me for a party later in the night.
I definitively look forward to a next time and I‚Äôll be quite happy to host her once I set my place :)

I stayed with Jo for two nights. Her house has such an awesome atmosphere with other surfers and flatmates! The first night we went partying to the city and had so much fun. It was a great experience all the time and I really recommend to meet Jo, she is very easy going and you can have interesting chats with her! Thank you for everything. You are always welcome to visit me :)

Josefine's place it is so good and so nice, I could not imagine how nice could be in summer. Actually they told me how nice was last summer with couchsurfer and so. Josefine is a cute and kind girl. I very liked to stay there. Her roomies are also very kind and cool. I had the opportunity to share some conversations with all of them. I played FIFA 2016 with Ray and there were so good matches. Nuno gave some advices of getting a room here in Copenhagen, that was so nice of him and he also offered me his help in whatever. It was also Josefine's sister visiting from Netherlands with her 4 adorables dogs. They are so nice. Today they have a competition, I hope they win !!  I definitely going to come back there for hanging out with them. Thank you for everything guys, specially to Josefine :D

Jo is amazing! During our stay four other surfers came and went, plus her flatmates, so the house was always lively and full of people. Everyone was easygoing and doing their own thing, but would offer invites if anything interesting was up that night. Jo's done a good bit of travelling and was full of stories and advice. 

Her place is very close to the train station, but can be a bit hard to find the first time if arriving after dark, so take a bunch of screen shots if you're reliant on wifi.

I crashed into Jo's place the night of October 9th. She's a intrepid traveler and a very chill person. I have to say Jo's home is one of nicest places to chill when you crash. Her home is a very aesthetic and cute place full of great ambulant people. I couldn't get into knowing all those amazing people, but they for sure have lots of stories to tell. If you aim to spend some time near Copenhagen, far from the noisy life of the city, in a beautiful house with travelers appearing from time to time I totally recommend you renting it, and make this quiet pleasant place a sanctuary of yours. Definitely looking forward to visit them again if possible!

Josefine has a beautiful, big, espacious house outside Copenhagen (35 min in train) but is totally worth it. She has very fun roomates. They make you feel like home. She is very friendly, knowledgeable, and well travelled.
She accepted my request even when it was last minute. And I am very thankful for that. We hung out in the evenings and cooked dinner. I would totally come back and stay with her again. Definitely recommend her.

***(make sure you have a map or a screenshot of the way to her house from the train station. Its easy to find but you can get lost easily (it happened to me) only 4 min walk.

Thanks for everything Josefine ‚ò∫‚ò∫‚ò∫ I hope you visit me in sunny California üåûüåÖüëô

text:

Jo has created a wonderful Couchsurfer paradise! Her home is full of warmth, love and friendship and she is a reliable and caring friend. If you are in Copenhagen you should definitely drop by and meet her and her "lost children" :) You'll always meet interesting people here and will have an awesome time, no matter who you are and where you are from. I had a lot of fun at Jo's place, including cooking, having bonfires and movie nights, but we also discovered Copenhagen and the small yet lively village of Veks√∏ together. I will surely visit Jo again and I hope that you will, too.
Josefine is a lovely person.  She offered me a couch even if I barely had time to say more than hello and bye :)

So I guess you wondering what type of house can host up to 15 people ?
Well I will speak plainly the house is a beautiful mansion in a leafy neighbourhood .ulala nothing can be added or subtracted from it.

Who is Josephine ? Jo is like Mother Theresa of couch surfing¬† .Words are not enough to extend my gratitude to her and it is almost impossible to understand her generosity and love for couch surfers .She is very thoughtful and flexible .

Who are the housemates ? I call them the tomorrow people .Never in any place in my travels have i met any people as amazing,tolerant,accepting as these.All very educated and always interested in engaging in scholastic conversations.My doors in Zimbabwe will always be open for them.

Josephine you are a beautiful¬† soul .You have started a wildfire and I am sure to spread the love and joy I felt while in your home .All those who meet you will never be the same again .

Bless your heart.May our paths cross again.From my heart to yoursüíúüíú

She was great and she has this lovely place where people (CS) meet, this place is very CS friendly and has a nice atmosphere for mix nationalities. 

I would recommend Josefine's place as others say "Couch surfers Paradise"

Thank you Joe for hosting me and please give my love to all others who was extremely nice to me and helpful. Cheers and see you soon!

It was my first stay as a couchsurfer at Josefine's . In her home, I met a lot of other interesting couchsurfers and Jo's housemates. Josefine was very nice, helpful and had a great little post-it system, which helped to know the house rules.  Very pleasantly. Thanks for your hospitality.

It was really nice to stay in very nice house of Josefine, with all of her house-mates and other couchsurfer. I was very surprise that she is into couchsurfing world so often and want to meet people from all over the world. Thanks a lot. And all the best.

It was the first I do couchsurfing.

Josefine is very nice and independent girl. I didn't have much time to hang out, but she is flexible and keeps house rules, so host her it's enjoyable. I hope to meet you one more time, all best wishes for you!!)

text:
My wife and me we were planning a trip around Denmark and Sweden, but It was really difficult to find a reasonable accommodation in Copenhagen. But then Josefine answered to our request - that really helped us to make our trip. 
Our stay at Josefine‚Äôs was short, but It was a great place to be for our first couchsurfing experience. 
The house was really big, tidy with all the comforts and lots of friendly people in it. We met there other couchsurfers from all over the world. That makes her house very enjoyable and it‚Äôs a positive and unique place. 
Even though we haven't seen much Jo (she was rather busy during the daytime with her studies, and we were little late too)  so we didn't have much time to hang out, we really had a nice time there and Jo tried to be flexible and helpful for travelers the best she could, still keeping house rules.
I surely recommend Josefine as a host, and if I would ever have a chance to be around there once, I would surely stay again or at least drop in. 
So, thank you Josefine you‚Äôve made it possible for us, to have a nice visit in Copenhagen. And if you are going to visit Gda≈Ñsk , you are always Welcome to stay in our home ;)
P.S. The dried apples from your garden were very tasty :D

Jo, Ray (https://www.couchsurfing.com/people/ray-stroe), Nuno (https://www.couchsurfing.com/people/nuno-gouveia), Sebastian (https://www.couchsurfing.com/people/rudkovskyy) and Jule
(https://www.couchsurfing.com/people/jule-ochmann) were absolutely great: It felt like a big, open hostel specifically for CSers and I felt like I'd been just another housemate for ages; I should've stayed in Veks√∏ for another day! Thanks a million-- when I get back to Copenhagen (sooner rather than later) I'll definitely get in touch! Ha det godt!
Allthings very nice

We really had a good time there , also it was also a great opportunity to have a good rest as we slept for whole day . it was very comfy and relaxed place with so many friendly people in it that makes the place so much better . Thank you for hosting us josefine , i hope i see you next time and  you can hold a pen properly by then :D

Our stay at josefine's were a short but great experience she really has a big house and lots of friendly people in it . Be it couchsurfers and her friends . if i ever come to copenhagen i would love to be hosted by her again . Thank you josefine :D
It was nice place to stay with my girlfriend, we got the best room with big bed ;) Josefine host us for 4 nights and we felt like at home. Very nice person with big heart. Thanks again !

It was a great place to end up with for my first couchsurfing experience.  I met other couchsurfers from all over the world at her place,  that truelly helped me make the most of my trip to Copenhagen.   How she opens up her house and hosts surfers is very noble and inspirational. 
If i'm ever in the area again I would surely stay again or at least visit.
Very friendly flatmates, flexible and helpful. I recommend them for anyone looking for a nice company to share a few days with.

Josefine's house is haven for couchsurfers and an awesome place to meet other travellers. As far as I have seen there always seems to be some couchsurfers around at any time. So if you want to get in contact with as many people as possible this is the place to go.
Josefine herself is a pretty experienced host and traveller and does a remarkable job in managing all those couchsurfers at her place. Everything is pretty well organized. Bathroom, laundry, kitchen, places to sleep and to hang out: Basically everything you need. Nevertheless she is pretty flexible though. It doesn't matter if you have plans during your stay or not. Besides it's fun just to hang around with her. I really enjoyed our mitdnight dumpster diving trip :D

Greetings from Germany
Stefan
She was so kind and honest.Very good hospitality.

text: It was a pleasure to be at Josefine's home. I could meet there another couchsurfers from Poland - Cristian & Wife,  Japan - Ayaka - , USA - Ryan - , Belgium - Igor - and we had a very good time together in Malmo & Copenhaguen. Also We had a nice talk there with Brasilians, Portuguese,Danish, Austrian ...So if you're looking for an international and multicultural host  that's the right place ! Thanks again for everything Josefine and I hope we can.see again in Madrid. All the best.

She was really kind to us and was really cool about our staying times we came near 7 am and she was okay with that. She is a fun person to hangout with and also talk to her house is full of couchsurfers and it really is nice
It was nice to stay at Josefine house, she is very kind, respectful girl with good heart. I'm happy I met her and would host her if she comes to Latvia some day for sure ;)

I had a great time with Josefine. She's very friendly as are her housemates. They really make you feel like part of the household. Definitely a perfect first couch surfing experience. I was really happy I got to go with her to roskilde to see the town while she was in class. She does host a lot of people at once but also makes a point to meet them all which I enjoyed. It's a very peaceful, but small town which was just what I wanted. Thanks for everything!

Josefine is a really kind girl who saved my life in Copenhagen (it was so hard to find a host at the moment).
She lives in a really nice house in a suburb of Copenhagen. It takes you 30-40min by train (72DKK). Her place is located vary close to the nearest station. 

There were also her housemates and other couchsurfers that was so fun :) It was a pity that I couldn't spend so much time with Josefine, but it was lovely to have conversations with her. I hope I'll be back and hang out with her next time.

Josefine, thank you so much again for everything! Hope to see you again!

Josefine's big house is always full of CouchSurfers, and she says that she has slowed down a lot from when she started! Hard to imagine what it must have been like before. Because of this, it very much has a kind of hostel vibe to it. That could be good or bad depending on what you are looking for from CouchSurfing. On the one hand, you have the opportunity to meet other CSers and do things together, which I did during my stay, on the other hand if you like to connect with or get to know your hosts, don't go in expecting that. It's great that Josefine accepts requests from almost everyone, male or female, solo travelers or couples, experienced surfers or newbies, I think she wants to give back to the CS community and considers it a bit of public service, but I don't really know, we didn't get to know each other very well. For me that was the biggest downside.

Josefine was really helpful accommodating me near Copenhagen when all hostels were booked. She makes sure everyone has their place to sleep, runs the house very organized so that everyone can have a good experience.

This was my first couchsurfing experience and I thank her so much in welcoming me and sharing her experiences while I had a new peofile, and also for creating an environment where you meet lots of other couchsurfers.

The world needs more people like Josefine that actually wants to give back and help as many as she can.

If you're ever in Brazil Josefine, please tell me so I can help you in the best way I can.
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Belo Horizonte, State of Minas Gerais, Brazil

text: It was an amazing experience to live with so many couchsurfers in one house. Jo is a really great person.

My stay as Josefine's place was memorable, it was a house full of lovely couch surfers.
Josefine was very nice and welcoming (she even took us to Roskilde where she studies because we wanted to visit it). We had a great stay and if you ever are in Copenhagen do not hesitate to go to Josefine's even if it may seem a bit far (it really isn't), you won't regret it.

It was really difficult to find a host for this period, but Josefine proposed me to come in his house for a few days. So for that, I'm really grateful. She's really generous personne (around 15 couchsurfers the first night I was there) and optimistic. So ,thanks you again, you made it possible for me, to have a nice trip around Danmark and Sweden. I stayed at Josefine's with my twin for almost a week.

Josefine is a wondeful person, she has traveled the world and has many stories to tell. She's nice, accomodating and kind, and always makes you feel welcome.

Her house is in a beautiful Danish town, with cute houses and lots of nature.
The station is very close, and in 30-40 minutes by train you can be in the center of Copenhagen.
It's a big Danish house, clean and cozy, with a nice garden and many rooms.

Her house is always welcoming many couchsurfers from all over the world, which makes it an incredibly exciting place, one in which you can meet new friends and share stories, food, and have a good time. There's always someone to hang out with and It really feels like a big family of strangers living together in a friendly athmosphere. During our stay there we met a lot of cool, interesting people from the most varied backgrounds that we'll certainly remain friends with in the future.

We enjoyed good conversations, movies, dinners with Jo and the other couchsurfers, we even painted together on a canvas!

Staying at Josefine's is a great experience in itself, and one we can heartily recommend to anyone. We certainly hope to meet her again, and she knows she has a place to stay in Italy if she decides to come say hi :)

Jo is a pretty dang cool gal. She's traveled the world for the past year, but came back to Copenhagen the same day that I got there, and could not have been more chill in opening the door of her home that she had spent all of a couple of hours in. For the week that I stayed at Jo's Home 4 Lost Children, so named for the couchsurfer's hostel that it became by mid-week, Jo and I hung out quite a bit, and I am certainly very happy to be able to call her a friend. She is incredibly giving. Many of the couchsurfers that passed through her doors over the course of the week I was there expressed their extreme gratitude to have someone so open to helping as many people find a place to stay. Every night we would hang out on her back porch in the comfortable Danish countryside air, drink beers, chat, and occasionally watch the fire twirling performances of a fellow couchsurfer. It was a unique experience living in a house with so many people from all over busily making food each evening for every one to share, and Jo was at the center of it all, even if she was always to modest to make herself so. I am excited to have her as a friend and very pleased to be able to hang with for as long as I live in Copenhagen.

Josefine opened her home to a bunch of couch surfers and created a delightful community of international travelers and also of people moving to Denmark. Sometimes there were groups going to the city or on road trips around the island (and one day we went to Sweden just for a few hours and back!) or just hanging out at the house and reveling in good conversation. I'm writing this review from her house now, actually, as it's my last day here, and I must say I don't want to leave! It's a fantastic place to stay for a day, a night, or a week, if you like interesting people, great stories, and a nice home outside of the big city with easy access to the train directly to Copenhagen (30-minute ride).

text: Alexis is super nice, caring, funny, and very kind as well. I had a lot of fun being in Copenhagen with Alexis and his friends! He hosted me and spent some time with me during the weekend although he got jetlag and was busy at work. I got a big comfortable sofa in the livingroom (where you can also watch movie on the big screen because he set up there a projector^^). His flat is very cozy, nice and clean, located in a good location: between the airport and the city center, near the Amager Strand that you can walk to the beach within 20 mins. Besides the time I went sightseeing in the city, we went out to see swoop challenge and cliff diving, and together with his friends we went one night to a cool bar and the other night we cooked at home (his friends are also very friendly and funny). Thank you so much Alexis!! You made my first solo trip and first surfing experience so awesome!! See you somewhere again :).

Alexis was a fantastic host! I am so happy that he was willing to host me even though he had a really busy schedule. He fed me some awesome crepes, played a funny game called exploding kittens with me (where he kicked my butt multiple times), and just shared lots of awesome stories. I‚Äôm so happy to have met and stayed with him, and so extremely grateful and appreciative for his kindness and hospitality. Would love to host you if you‚Äôre ever in Sweden.. take care!

text: Pankaj accepted my request really quickly. He is a friendly and knowledgable man, and his girlfriend is also very kind and nice. Again, thank you very much for everything Pankaj! I really felt like home :)

Pankaj is a real gentleman, very good person, and someone you can really trust!

Nicolas hosted us during 3 nights in Copenhagen. He is a really relaxed and funny person and we felt comfortable with him since the first second. He knows well the city and he always has good advices to give you. We recommend him a lot ! Muchas gracias Nicolas y quizas nos vemos en Francia !

Excelent! Super nice guy, well driven and trustful. I recommend him as host and as guest aswell.

There was something about calling Mads "Grandma" (you'll have to read his profile to get the reference) that set off a series of spontaneous conversations from the very first message exchanged between us. He kept me updated about his arrival in the city and was promptly able to find his way to the right metro station. And from that point, I couldn't have asked for better company to spend my days off during 4th of July. Mads liked to bike, and we biked almost 20 miles in the two days he stayed with me. He embraced DC's unruly traffic, a bat which flew into my house, Ethiopian food, drag queens, and the DC heat with stride. We joked over beer, bantered about cute guys we crossed, and simply had a great time overall!

There still are uncharted attractions in DC, Pride 2019 in NYC, and possibly a future trip to Denmark where I hope to hang out with this amazing guy once again. Until next time, Mads!

Mads is an enthusiastic traveler who is always up for a fun time. He isn't all about the selfies and Glamour shots, which is refreshing considering how so many people are usually stuck to their phones. He had a chance to try out a local drinking spot in my neighborhood and is an excellent drinking partner!

It was my great pleasure to host Mads.  He is a very informed, politically knowledge, intelligent guy, far beyond his years.  We did my walking tour of the West Village, had a smoothie while sitting in the park, and visited NYC's LGBTQI+ Center.  My only regret is that his stay was too short.  Enjoy your travels Mads!

I hosted Mads and Aaron during their weekend in G√∂teborg. They both enjoy cooking so that makes the three of us!

He is very helpful in the house and respects the house rules and is very helpful and good in cleaning. He also made some nice pancakes and loves to explore new places. Enjoy the rest of your travels!
Mads is a nice a cool guy. He's so friendly and it's was cool hosting him for almost a week. I highly recommend to host Mads!!

I'm probably starting as a clich√©, but I really mean it when I say I couldn't have wished for a better host than Mads. My only regret is that I stayed with him for just one night, but even in those 3/4 of a day we spent together, Mads showed himself to be a genuinely nice and pleasant person from the moment we met up at the metro station. It's true that he lives a bit farther away from the city centre and is surrounded by old people, but it's a really nice and calm neighbourhood, and his cute and warm little apartment makes up for it all. We had a stroll through the city starting at Rosenborg (and not Roseng√•rd!) castle, then figured out which palace the Queen lives at, and finally ended up at his uni to print some stuff, which I thought was pretty cool, but maybe that's just me because I'm into that random stuff.

All in all, I'm really glad I met you, Mads, and I'm looking forward to seeing you again sometime, but maybe this time with me as the host :D

I couldn‚Äôt have asked for a better host for my last couple of days in Copenhagen! Mads really made an effort to spend as much time with me as possible, and he made me feel very welcome and well taken care of in his cozy apartment. It was a pleasure to see a little bit of his world, his thoughts - even his friends! -, and I had the best time hanging out with him, having some beers, talking, walking in the city together. He is very intelligent, sociable, fun, and, behind his facade of acid (and funny!) jokes, he‚Äôs a real sweetheart.
Thanks for this awesome couple of days, Mads! Stay healthy and happy, and I‚Äôll see you pretty soon!

Mads is a gem! One of the loveliest guys I‚Äôve ever met, an incredible person offering incredible hospitality and a lot of fun to hang out with. I feel like I‚Äôve definitely made a friend from that experience. I recommend surfing with or hosting Mads to anyone and everyone. See you again!!

text: Mads was a very good host. He met me in the center, showed me some places which I didnt manage to see by myself. I could not possibly have had a better host in Copenhagen than Lars! He's incredibly chill, super easy to talk to and ultimately a lot of fun to hang out with. I'm glad I got to spend my chunk of holiday in Copenhagen with Lars! Thanks for everything!

Truly amazing host! Fun, intelligent, honest, with great communication skills, and working on a deeply touching project with disabled people. We had a great time together, couldn't have found a better host in Copenhagen!!

Lars is an amazing person. I stayed at his place for 2 nights and it was just perfect.  Not only stay, but also we built a very good friendship. I'm glad to know him. Hope to see you very soon! ;)

I am so, so happy to share my experience with Lars! I was lucky enough to stay in his most danish cozy place during my very first visit to beautiful Copenhagen. Lars is very good host, person to talk and a cook. He's job is very intresting. He gave me tips what I should to seen and during last hours helped me forget about my hard situation.

Lars is "the kindness" in person. When I came he made feel as I am athome. He showed me the house and how the things work and everything.  We had great conversations together, we went out the same day I came. He showed me some bars. The next day he showed me part of the city. He also allowed me to stay one more night because my other host had some troubles. I really appreciated it from him and my other host did too :) I met him for 4 nights and I could say that Lars is a person who you can trust, have good conversations and the most, he is a very easygoing guy and that was very important for me, because I am too :D I believe that I will keep the contact with him to hang out or maybe ride the bike through Copenhagen :) Thank you for everything you did for me :D

Lars was the best host I could've wished for. He was kind, welcoming, open-minded, available and fun. I wish everyone could meet openhearted guys like him. And above all, you can see he truly loves people. 100% would recommend

Lars was a fantastic host! He made sure my friend and I had a pleasant stay and was really informative and helpful about visiting the city. Me and my friend spent great time in Kopenhagen thanks to Lars.Lars is not only a great host but also a great guide,we traveled Kopenhagen by bike with him. You can talk with him about everything. We also had an awesome lunch the Danish style with some amazing herrings and pate.. His house is very organized and I felt very comfortable staying over, I very much recommend him as a host and I hope we meet again somewhere Lars!
A very friendly guy who did the best he can to make our stay as comforting as possible. Would definitely stay again at his place if I could.

I came back to Zagreb from my 1st, but short tour to Scandinavia and I'm soooo impressed by beauty and by the people. Copenhagen will be always in my heart and in my TOP 5 cities I've visited ever, but it's also because I had a pleasure to met this amazing guys. Lars and Axel welcomed me warmly and it just felt natural and easy to hang out at there flat. They truly care to get to know their host, and I felt their genuine care for me. Really felt like coming home to an old friends place. I stayed 3 nights and because of their offer, I stayed 1 night more in Cph. Lars has a charming character that any couchsurfer would be lucky to meet, so warm, funny and extremely worldly guy, anyone would be priviliged to be hosted by or to host him.

@Lars: I'm so happy that I helped you with your plans for your summer tour to Croatia. It will be a pleasure to host you here in Zagreb. And big big tnx to Axel! Hugs from Zgb

Lars is friendly, welcoming, kind hearted and flexible host with a comfortable couch setup. I felt privileged to be let in on his experiences of Copenhagen life. I particularly enjoyed our informal tour of the local theatres, bars and clubs, along with an introduction to the Copenhagen music scene. Velkomst to surf London anytime :)

I had a great time staying with Lars and Axel! It was my first time a host cooked for me on my day of arrival - usually I cook for my host! Lars and Axel were really accommodating and super fun! Very clean house and comfortable couch! I would definitely recommend them to others!

My stay at his place was wonderful! Lars is a fantastic person who made me feel welcome since the moment I arrived.

Lars is a really nice guy with a positive attitude! I always felt embraced by his happiness :D 

 We had the opportunity to spend time together, and he took me to  wonderful places that I probably wouldn't have seen without his help. He took me to see an amazing play and also to a show that was done inside a church!!

I feel very happy and blessed because I had the chance to meet Lars and his wonderful life  in HAPPY Copenhagen!

Greetings to both you Lars and Axel, who also is a great guy and made me feel very welcome. Hopefully, I will see you guys again somewhere around the world!

Keep being happy!

Being hosted by Lars was a great experience and feel lucky to find him. He is a unique and so charismatic guy! We had great time together, great conversations, nice wine and great music.
Thanks for all my friend. Hope to see you again soon.
Take care

Jesper is a great guy, flexible, knowledgeable, friendly, funny what more I can say he is awesome to be with.
Well, he is the first person who I have hosted since recently I reactivated my Couchsurfing and yet again he is the first traveler who gave the best experience and insight on hosting a traveler with Couchsurfing.
During my time with him. i learn a lot of stuff from him like learning about Denmark, about his travelling experience especially what funny things he had experienced during his traveling, tips on how to travel effectively, tips on how to use Couchsurfing effectively aside from that we talked and made a lot of jokes together during our journey of Brunei exploration making us like a good friend to be then again I considered him as my new good friend. I would also like to thanks to him for his token keychain gift before he leaving from Brunei.
To all future host, i recommend you to host him and i can guarantee you will have the best experience when hosting him.

Jesper  was polite humble and nice person. Who was punctual and nice person. It was great experience hosting him

Jesper is really good human being. He is very organized and friendly. A peaceful and knowledgeable person. He knows many languages. I couldn't give him enough time for my office and sudden accident. But he managed to move and explore. He travelled with my mom at her village and experienced native life of Bangladeh. Hosting him was a good experience.

Jesper is a very open-minded guy with a lot of knowledge. He's very interested in everything (in culture, art, nature and especially in tennis :)) and he's very easy-going. We spent a good time by discovering some new places in Zurich, hiking in the mountains and just sitting on the balcony enjoying the view.

Has been a real pleasure to host Jesper in my apartment.
Jesper is a  very interesting and kind guy. We spent a good amount of time together, so we had the chance to share our ideas and experiences.
He is resourceful, he has got a wide and deep knowledge about travelling, so he shared some of his tips with me .We have several common interests, such as enjoying  delicious food and  good beers, specially in front of a great football game.
I'd like to meet him again, maybe in Copenaghen or in Rome ,or somewhere around the world.

Jesper is the first person I host since I joined CS, and I could treasure his vast travel experience and couchsurfing.
I read a lot of of the positive reviews you garnered over the years. It would have been pointless reading them all, and it would be difficult adding something original or disagreeing with those who preceded me. A person with a lot of travel experiences to tell, never trivial, always funny and kind. what counts is that your stay here was good. Have a safe trip back, Jesper ... SC√ÖL üòâ

Jesper is surprising person! Travelled all around globe. He is professional in couch surfing in hosting people. His photos tell more about him than talking with him (at least in my case). Wise guy. Mysterious guy who met santa clause, is apparently interested in old empty factories, craffits and barbers (in every culture there are barbers!).

Highly recommend hosting / staying with Jesper. A friendly, flexible guy with a passion for travel. Had fun learning Danish watching dubbed Vaiana together and sharing a few watery Finnish beers. Looking forward to stalking my second favourite Dane in Copenhagen with you!

Jesper is a king of his own life in very positive way and he's able to express his knowledge in many ways. I got many tips to my life, both theoretical and concrete ways. Jesper is a wise guy. He also loves dogs and our dog loved him! :) He's also very brave, he let me cut his hair, haha :D I recommend this guy and I wish all the best where ever hi's ever going. Plus you will have the sunshine along him :D

It was easy to find a tall man with glasses from railway station.  We visited 
Santa Claus Village to see Santa, eat ice cream,  had sauna and some beer. It was easy to talk with Jesper  till late evening.  I welcome him again for longer time.

Jesper stayed at my place for a weekend and during that time demonstrated to be a very nice, relaxed, cultivated, respectful and easygoing person, as well as fun to be with and great as a flatmate. Right from the beginning I felt as if I had known him for a long time (an impression which might have also been to a certain extent related to the fact that he reminded me of the time I spent in Denmark a while ago :-).  To summarize, it was a real pleasure having him and I would be really happy to host him again any time.

Jesper was quite independent at exploring this new city. I gave him a tour of Soho's cast iron buildings, but other than that he found his own way around. Jesper is a calm and pleasant person to host. I appreciated his willingness to help me with an errand and prepare his room for a new surfer.  Trustworthy and reliable!

Jasper is a really easy going guy.  It is easy to talk with him and he enjoy simple activities like going in a bar to see a football match, having a beer or walk around to visit  Montreal!  He is quiet and very respectfull.  It was a pleasure to receive him at home, we had good wine, good converstions and I was happy to learn more about Denmark and how is life overthere!
We became good friends in a few days only and had many deep conversations and activities. Parties, beach, badminton, good food. See you next year maybe?

Jasper was very  enjoyable to talk and hang out with.  He was a traveller, not a tourist, to experience and discover local culture and stories to listen to. We went to Jjimjilbang where he was experiencing local family and friend culture.  We went to the DMZ border area where we were able to see a North Korean village and learn about millions of Korean people forced to be separated from their families and to leave their hometowns since 1950-1953 Korean War. We also enjoyed a Korean cooking class and party with a group of Ajumas, super women of Korea.
He is a nice guy , we had good time together.

It was a short, but memorable time I could spend with Jesper! I'm very happy he sent me a request and even more that I could help him out with a bed for a night. Even though we didn't have much time we shared a beer at night and a breakfast and I would've enjoyed to have him around for some more days. He's easy going, decent, talkative, with excellent manners and some good stories! Feel honoured to be hosted by him, and please anyone, help him out with anything he asks for! He's a good guy and you'll get a lot of good karma in return, for sure!

We shared nice time, my mother, friends and I with Jesper, talking about danish/ italian/ slovenian/ french cultures and joking. He participated to everything we proposed: going to the river and spending a few hours there on the beach or in the rocks, participating to the party in the evening (since it was my leaving party from the house) and kindly helping us to put the house in order after it ;-) Jesper has been a nice guest, I recommend him a lot! 
Have a nice travel in the Balkans and see you soon :-)

It was so good to see Jesper again and finally go full circle with someone from CS. He hosted me in Copenhagen and I finally had the chance to return the favor. He stayed with us for a week and we visited Newtown, went for coffee and had Teppanyaki for the first time. He was happy to hang out with my friends and I and also do his own thing. He was a pleasure to have around and I hope he enjoyed his time in Sydney. You're welcome anytime, see ya soon mate!

Jesper was very keen in badminton and therefore I took this opportunity to introduce him to a friend who has common interest.
He is very open to try new things, and during his time here I was able to bring him to explore local delicacies.
Jesper has very good SOD, he was able to navigate around better than I was in my own town by just looking at the map! 
We had the opportunity to share about our culture and I was able to learn a thing or two from Jesper.
Thanks for showing up at my office and created a scene there! HAHA!

text:
Jesper is a really nice host! He is a kind and interesting person, with whom you will always find a topic to talk. I really enjoyed staying with him during my short trip to Copenhagen.
We had interesting conversations with each other, went to the Davids Collection museum and watched some movies together.
Also, Jesper invited me to play badminton when he was coaching. And I should say it was very very fun! :D
Thank you Jesper for such a nice stay, have fun in Asia and I hope to see you again somewhere around the world! :)

I stayed for two nights in Jasper's house. He is very friendly and kind. Firstly, he invited me to participate in his badminton exercise which was an exciting experience for me, and  also we  had dinner together.  We had lots of good conversations about many things and especially about the culture.  He is very informative and his house is really amazing. I hope to meet him again in the future.
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Mashhad, Razavi Khorasan Province, Iran (Islamic Republic of)

text: Jesper is amazing guy , he was so kind and friendly to me -he even asked his system for bike for me , also once we were speaking for hours drinking dannish beer.He is very interesting person , has big experience of traveling all over the world , for me was very plesure to spend this time with him!‚ò∫Ô∏èAnd despite of Jesper says that he need interior designer , his come is very cosy and sweet , I felt like I am at home üè† Looking forward to see you as my guest , dear friend üòâ

text: Jesper is a great host willing to share his travel stories, flexible with hanging out together, he even borrowed me a bike. Thank you, Jesper for everything, :) I hope to meet you in Lithuania! üá±üáπ P. S. A hint for future couchsurfers: Jesper likes original souvenirs, chocolate, books and collects CDs with good music ;)

Jesper was lovely to stay with. Very easy going, flexible and friendly to be around. 
I met him at his badminton class, and joined his team for a fun game or two, which was heaps of fun! I felt very welcomed by him and his students. Although I only could stay one night with him, it was nice to chat, hang at his apartment and get to know a little about Danish culture and his life. 
Jesper lives in a nice little apartment in a calm area, easy to get to on the train and comfortable too
Looking forward to seeing him again and catching a badminton too I hope!

Jesper is a great host. He was willing to help me at any time. Since the first time, he provided me useful information and he gave me total freedom to enjoy the city. I really appreciate his hospitality.

See you in Costa Rica... "Mi casa es tu casa"

Staying with Jesper was really good, I just stayed 2 nights so the first one he had a kind of marathon and the second one had to coach by couch a badminton team so we spend a few hours of the evening talking, drinking beer and even had sometime to watch the Mummy with Tom Cruise, he was the whole time really nice to me and listen my stories. So if u want to stay with a danish he is the guy, he is very gentle and calm. Thanks mate!!!!
Jesper is very welcoming, friendly and nice host! he borrowed me his bike :) Nice experience in my first trip to Copenhagen.

Jesper is so friendly, I enjoy staying with him even though was only for two nights, I wish I could have stay longer so I could see him coaching a badminton game, anyway he has a big collection of CDs and if your lucky maybe will have one of your favorite band or singer so don‚Äôt doubt to ask, Jesper hope to see again in any part of the world üåé
PS his coach is really comfortable:)

I asked Jesper for a last-minute couch because I used to stay at another place with friends from Belgium, but there was a strike and everything get canceled because they couldn't come to Copenhagen. Jesper was very kind and helped me to print out labels (that Belgian friends couln't bring because of the strike) for my bus to G√∂teborg. Thanks a lot for that ! Although Jesper was friendly, I didn't like the appartment because it wasn't cleaned for a long time. There was a text in his livingroom "my house was clean last week, you missed it". . . So I was there at the wrong week. I hope that the next couchsurfers can arrive at a clean place next time.
