text: A really good friend of mine and I'm happy to meet him again around the world üòä

Jesper is a really nice and easygoing guy! He made me feel comfortable and at home. The place is in a very good location! Close to the city center in a nice neighborhood around 10 minutes walk from train station. I had his bike for a tour in the city and he gave me nice tips that made me enjoy really well my only day in Copenhagen. I recommend it!!

Jesper made my stay in Copenhagen really comfortable and recommended some great places for touring around and some atmospheric places for watching the World Cup games. His place is in an excellent location and was great to cycle around from. Thanks again for everything! If you make it back to Indonesia, mi casa es su casa.
Truly gentle, welcoming and generous. He is defenetly a good representative of Copenhagen people! Reccomended :)

Jesper was a great host really open and nice, also if I had a bit of a crazy schedule we found the time for having a couple on nice chat. 
Let him tell you about his travelling and mostly about his love for travelling by train üòä
Hopefully we will get to meet each other again.

Jesper is a nice an friendly person. The first evening he had the great idea to try the best sushi in Copenhagen. He picked up some and we had a nice dinner at his flat. I was very impressed from his huge CD collection. Due to I¬¥m a musician I liked to get to know something about his favourite band "Suede". Jesper is a very reliable person and he gives any information in time. I got every note I needed to tavel in town and the flat is very centrally located. I would like to visite Jesper again. Thank you for housing me.
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: W√∂rth an der Donau, Bayern, Germany

text: This is the first time that I have couchsurfing and Jesper provided a very good and nice experience to me!! He helped me a lot which made my travel in Copenhagen became so much more easier! I really enjoyed my stay in his place. He also has plenty of movies in his place which is cool! Tank you sooo much for such a wonderful experience Jesper!!

Jesper is a dear heart: kind, intelligent, funny, and genuine. He graciously welcomed me after my travel plans were delayed and we shared some stories. He taught me a little Danish that I was able to put into practice around town and he took me to a local pub. I wish I had had more time with him and will happily welcome him anytime in the US! Mange Tak! Vi ses :)

Ahh still sore from an intense badminton game with his students! But it was something that you don't get to do often while you are traveling that's for sure and who would knew that I will be playing badminton for the first time since 6 years ago in Copenhagen! Jesper was super hospital and the couch was big and comfy! He had a good sense of humour and had a lot of amazing travel experiences.
Did I mention he had a crazy good collection of movies and a sound system that's probably better than theatre :P the location was convenient enough for me to walk and back the two days I was here!
Thank you for everything! Best of luck in the upcoming trip to Asia! I am sure you will encounter some interesting people there :)
Ray
Jesper was an incredible host. Very welcoming, friendly and fun. I went to play Badminton with him and oh man... he is good!!!! So much fun. Thank you!!

It was a pleasure staying in Jesper's home. He is a really nice guy.. we spend little time together but we talked and have fun! He gave me tips to enjoy the city at its best. His house is cozy and the bed-couch was very confortable.. great experience with him in my first time couchsurfing!

I'm very glad that Jesper agreed to accept me at home. He is very friendly, tactful and considerate person! He was very kind and offered me his help and everything I could ever need to feel in an unfamiliar city like home :))) If you like watching movies or listening to music, you are an amazing music collection and Jesper's  film library! If you are interested in sports or traveling, you definitely will have something to discuss. I really hope that I can respond with hospitality when he is in Ukraine.
Jesper kindly host me for a night at his place on his sofa. We had nice talks. Thanks for everything thing Jesper!

Jesper was really nice and cute host. His flat was very cosy and comfortable. I was very glad that I decided stay with Jesper because he is really Denmark person, very clever, interesting and pleasant. It was absolutely good to spent time with him and I can reccomend him like a perfect host and good friend :)

He was a really nice and respectful host. He made me feel like home and he was very helpful when I needed the help. His company is nice to have. Besides that he is very interesting to talk to and conversations were never forced. I loved making Quesadillas with him, cooking traditional Mexican food! Thank you Jesper for being such a wonderful host

I was staying in Jesper's place for 2 days. Jesper was very kind, polite and quite. Mb too much quite/silent) he showed me nearest good shop and bicycle rent, gave me keys from the flat so i was independent. He answered me always when i asked him (before coming). His apartment is good, i slept in a comfortable sofa in living room. He provided me with warm blanket and it was so cool cuz those days were very cold.  
Thank you a lot Jesper.

Jesper was a very welcoming host. He offered everything you could need like maps, to exchange money, and even his wine! He didn't have time to show me around but we still watched some movies together. Great guy with a good heart.

Hello!I had a very good couchsurfing experience with Jesper!He is  a very friendly person , we spend some time together speaking about travel and life.
He suggested  me some very intresting tour and he introduce me the play of  badminton!
Thank you very much Jesper!

Jesper is the coolest host that i have ever meet. I  arrive Copenhagen on weekdays so we didn't manage to spent more time as he work from 8.30-5. But I feel so comfortable because he gives me the key,blanket,pillows,wifi and even change my money from ¬£ to DKK. It helps me a lot! He also got bunch of dvd that might be watch for the rest of my life. Thank you so much Jesper! Aha takkk for the taxi too! I hope we can meet again in future. Just knock me when you're visiting Penang againüòä

Thanks to Jesper  I had best trip ever in Copenhagen! He is super hospitable, and he did everything to make my stay at his place comfortable and carefree! After a few days we spent together I feel like we know each other the whole life. He is very easygoing and I totally enjoyed our evenings and badminton games! I'm so happy we met each other and I'm sure we'll meet one day again in Denmark or Ukraine!

Jesper's place is well located, and he is a really nice person, and a good listener :) we had a good time, he has a great movie/music collection! I was very impressed.
Gracias Jesper! :D

text:
Jesper is a super host and a fun person to hang out with. He offered me a comfortable couch, shared his wine and helped me figure out my way to malmo. He answered all my questions and I felt comfortable in his appartement.  Would definetely  recommend staying with Jesper. Wine + bjork + pringles = win. I hope we hang out again.
Thank you for everything!!!

Jesper was such a great host. I stayed with him for two days. Nice flat with a very comfortable couch. Good movie selection for a relaxed night in. He has good taste in movies, although somehow he liked 'Anomalisa,' which seemed like an anomaly given the other fantastic movies he also enjoys. He was very easy to joke with and have conversations, and was excited to take me to badminton although I have two left feet and can't hold a racket. You're lucky if you get to stay with Jesper! He's an easy-going guy, very generous with his stuff, and was the perfect host for me in Copenhagen. Hope I can return the favor and host him if he ever comes to the states! All the best, Jesper!

Jesper was a wonderful host, very kind and helpful with everything! We took the water bus together which was really cool and he pointed out some interesting sights along the way. He's very well-traveled and is fun to talk to, we spent two nice evenings together and he even showed me his awesome speaker system which made it sound like there was a live concert in his living room! Thank you for the great stay in Copenhagen Jesper, hope to see you again :)

I feel lucky because my first Couchsurfing experience is with Jesper. He is a very nice, friendly and hospitable person. The couch is big and confortable. He prepared me New Year Eve food and champagne and including translated the Queen¬¥s speech for me :). Thank you Jesper, I had a really good New Year Eve and time in Copenhagen.

Ah i worte a reference but where is my reference..?? So i'm writing again :)
Jesper is sooo nice! He is friendly and good listener! He is very kind so i love Jesper's couch! If i go again, i want to meet Jesper!!! Thanks Jesper!!

Jesper agreed to host me, even though he was busy working. We had nice conversations around dinner. My stay was short but I was able to make the most of it to visit the city, as his home is conveniently situated close to public transportation. Tak!
Jesper is very kind and explain To me very well the ways To go to his home. It was a real pleasure to meet him üòä

Thanks for Jesper hosting me for two nights. His home is located in very good place. Quiet but safe. He is very kind, friendly and nice person. We talked a lot about life, career, cities, wine....many many. Thanks for listening to me :) Could not forget the sunset from your terrace. Next time let's meet in Hong Kong! :)
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Hong Kong, New Territories, Hong Kong

text:
It was nice  to stay with Jesper :) 
He was welcome from the very first time. He was a very knowledgable person and he was quite fine with sharing them with you. Thus, I learned a bit about the culture and language as far as we had time thanks to his patience to answer my questions.  He was also kind to ask you whether you had a good sleep and then a great day with a big smile on his face as usual as most of local Danish people do :) 
Thank you for everything Jesper :) When you come back to Turkey again, please let me know :)

Jesper was a fantastic host.  My first night staying with him we watched the first game of the Euro Cup with some of his friends.  Jesper is very friendly and knowledgeable about the area.  The location of Jesper's flat is in a quiet and safe part of town and only one block from a city bike rental location.  I was able to ride the city bike into the center of the city in under 15 minutes.  Jesper and I also had a great time drinking beer and dancing to jazz music at one of his friend's get together.

Staying with Jesper was soo fun! Though we only could spend a little time together, the stories we shared, the things we talked (from travelling to politics!) were so great! He shared couple of drinks with me and I enjoyed our conversation so much. He is a really nice, fun, wise and helpful person. He even waited up for me when i arrived late (which i still am sorry :( ). He loves music, movies and books. His living room is full of CDs and DVDs, which made it a really cozy environment for me :) 
Jesper, thank you so much for making my trip better! I hope to see you in Ankara as well someday! You are always more than welcome!
≈ûerefe!

Jesper is a very friendly person, he made me feel welcome at his home.
We didn't spend much time together, but it was a pleasure to meet him !

Although i stayed with Jesper only 1 evening, it was a great time! I felt as if i'm vising a friend i knew before ;) he's a very intersting person with a great experience and awesome taste of music. It was really nice to share the opinions about the cultures and countries and compare the languages  with him while getting rid of his beer collection xD  Hope to see u again somewhere in the World!

Jesper is a great man, a rich soul, he is highly intellectual with a unique mix of kindness, sensibility and witty attitude :) I thank the universe opportunity that i become not only his guest but also friends with him.  A bient√¥t amigo

Jesper was friendly person, open minded and helpful when I was in Copenhagen and stay at him. I cooked Indonesian Food Nasi Goreng and I brought Tempe from Germany. Jesper was many time in Indonesia the reason why I offer for some Indonesian dishes cooked. We talked about our passions Travelling and about Badminton üè∏. For all Jesper was great host and if you stay at him never regret! See you again maybe in Copenhagen, Germany or maybe in Indonesia.

THIS GUY IS EXTREMELY AMAZING! It was my first experience staying with a couch and I loved it. He is very very kind and so funny and very intellectual as well. He has many interesting and funny things to share because he's been travelling around the world which is fantastic. I'm still sorry for that Barca match and your bet Jesper but I wish you good luck on your next bets :D Hope to see you again! Cheers!

Jesper is a very charming person. He takes time to talk, is welcoming and comprehensive. I feel bad I didn't have time to take photo of him playing badminton as it was planned. I'll definitely come back to Copenhagen to correct that! Let's meet again! :)

text: Jesper helped me a lot by giving amazing tipes of the city. Also, he is a very welcoming person, and very good to talk with. I would recommend him for sure! Thanks for everything, Jesper!

Jesper was a very nice host and it was great to celebrate the New Years with someone in a foreign country! He had lots of good recommendations of things to do and is exteemely helpful. Thanks for letting me stay with you!
For me staying with Jesper was excellent! We watched a very good movie together, he is very helpful and friendly. I really enjoyed and I wish I had more time to talk with him :)

We didn`t spend to much time together bc Jesper was busy but he looks like a very kind and interesting person. He is intellegent and well-travelled man.
You will have own room with a comfortable couch))
Thank u Jesper!
Wish you a nice turkish trip)

I really enjoyed my stay with Jesper :) he invited me to stay at his place for two nights and offered me his comfortable couch. 
We met at his badminton gym where we had a nice hang-out with the guys from his match and changed to a bar afterwards. I am thankful that he made my trip to Copenhagen first of all possible and second of all as nice as it had been :) 
(And showed me the first delicious Kebab I ever had in Denmark :D) 
Tak for alt Jesper!

I stayed at Jesper's place for two nights, and it was really cool ! He gave me precise directions to get to his flat and has one of the most impressive DVD/CD collections I've seen ! He's a very cool, fun and thoughtful host who won't let you down ! 
Enjoy all your upcoming trips !

Jesper was a great host. He is an interesting person to talk to and very nice. He has an awesome collection of movies, books, music, and travel goodies (like durian candies!). Thanks again for hosting me and making my first CS experience nice. I wish we had more time to get to know each other. Until I return to Copenhagen :)

Jesper is actually an activist! He joins a lot of clubs and always welcome you to join him! It was good to stay at his place for 2 nights, he event invited me to a movie club event^^ Thanks for your hospitality and see you again soon! hopefully :D

text:
Great couchsurfing experience ! Jesper accepted my request on an extreme short notice and practically saved me from spending my first night in CPH on a bench :D 
I stayed with him for a night and he was super kind and had a cold beer ready for me on arrival , which means  a lot to a German girl ! 

Jesper is well traveled , has a lot to share and tell , and at his apartment you spend the night surrounded by great music , films and literature of all sorts ! 

Thanks again for your availability and hospitality , Jesper :) Tak Tak

Although Claus stayed at my place only one day, I really liked him :) He is funny and active, we did roller skating together. He makes cool music and has really nice voice. Don't hesitate to host him :)
I had a nice time with Claus. He is an open-minded and friendly traveller.

I stayed at Claus home for two nights and I am super thankful to have met him! He picked me up at the station and we had a really long walk throughout Copenhagen. He knows a lot and has already been to some amazing places in this world! He was very hospital and also showed me some places outside of the city. Thank you again for those few days and I only wish you the very best in life!

Claus is a super active guy, always with some crazy experiences or travel to tell, be prepared ;) he is also the only guy that took us a "shit mountain", but I won't spoil the surprise :D We also had some very interesting conversations about politics and Denmark which helped me to understand the country better. Claus has also been very nice to take us around in the area and in another city closeby. Thanks again Claus :)

Claus is a great host. He's passionate about life, full of energy and fresh ideas. We went to Copenhagen to see all "must see" things, it was adorable! We also visited Christiania at night, that was a truly unique experience. 
Apart from that, I had a chance to enjoy a beautiful Danish nature at Mons Klint and surroundings of H√∏je Taastrup. We also went to play mini golf, that was my first time doing this. I enjoyed it so much!
Claus is also an amazing cook. He does that super delicious. I learned a few Danish receipies to cook at home.
I recommend staying with him.


Hope you come to Russia one day!

Claus had lots of work while my staying at his place. Anyway, if you want to go to the university in the middle of the night and make printed circuit board, then just let him know :) Maybe you'll be sleepy next day but you never forget it. He showed me surroundings like the Viking ship museum and recommended to visit Absalon. Thanks for tips :) Claus is talkative and funny guy. His appartment located in quiet place and it's easily to get there by train. Thanks for hosting!

I only spent a night with Claus, but it was one of the memorable time ever! He is a VERY active guy and pushed me out of my comfort zone with biking around the area. The views were amazing. I usually don‚Äôt bicycle at home so I rented an electrical bike while he rode his own bike and often was ahead of me 99% of the time. What can I say, I‚Äôm a city gal!  We literally spent 5 hours biking until midnight and explored the city of Copenhagen. He is very knowledgeable about traveling and hiking. If you‚Äôre in hiking and the outdoors I would definitely recommend staying or just hangout with Claus. Thank you so much for taking me in! I hope you get to visit Africa soon!

Very nice guy, it's interesting to talk with him and spend time, he's ready to go to a meeting! If there is any question he helps and on his part there is a great interest in communication. He has a car and he arranged an excursion to the shore of the Baltic Sea and to the city of Roskilde. On the territory of its apartments there is a swimming pool, but unfortunately I didnt have time to get there.. I highly recommend Claus as a positive person!

My stay with Claus was very interesting, involved a lot of walking and biking around Copenhagen. He was happy to show me around and share everything he knows! Claus is a very talkative and energetic person. Thank you for your hospitality :)

If you want fun and adventure, Claus is definitely the best host for this! He was a truely amazing tour guide, great personality and full of energy and positivity. I stayed for 3 nights and in this time we explored all of Copenhagen, saw the views over the city, we went to the lighthouse, had a full day of seeing the wonderful white cliffs of Mons Klint, went to Roskilde exploring thr Viking boat museum, the town, around musicon and running around on the skatepark and the swing! On the final night we went to the beach, seam in the pool and played and listened to music in his studio. So much adventure in 3days!!  He truely is a gracious and attentive host. I would LOVE to meet up again and have our cycling adventure to Sweden!!

Claus is a cool Host, open minded, down to the earth. Perfect guide who shows you everything interesting around. 
He picked me up from the airport and started our sightseeing tour through Copenhagen. Also took me to his studio for karaoke even though I don‚Äôt sign haha he was quite good though! He showed me so many fun places close to him, for example Viking‚Äôs village and the art gallery in Roskilde. 
Thanks for everything Claus and hope to see you one day!

My friend and I stayed at Claus' place for two days. He picked us up at the airport which was really nice of him, and he showed us around Copenhagen.  He planned a lot of things for us and he showed us a good and cheap place to eat. During the sightseeing he was telling us interesting things about danish culture, politics and way of living. And he has a pretty cool studio as well, so if you are staying at his place, definitely go to the studio to do some karaoke with him.

That was an unexpected-atypical-memorable-5-day stay at Claus' house. Despite all his efforts to teach me how to pronounce Danish correctly, I still could not do it after 5 days of attempts. But that was a lot of fun trying, oh yeah.
Claus shared almost all his time with me and I am glad he did. We spent every day together, walking around "Cup'n'hown", driving around the countryside, visiting some quarry, lighthouse, the White Cliffs and the biggest mountain of Denmark...; going to the sauna, making some typical Danish food (omg, this blood sausage), playing some music in his studio and registering all those weird sounds from his car when turning. Besides all the jokes, we had great conversations about deep subjects and Claus is very talkative and passionate by what he is doing. And always up to debate. Very interesting personality. Next time, we won't forget the cow costumes.
Thank you, Claus! We might see each other again if you feel like traveling another 7000 km somewhere on earth.

I stayed with Claus for 3 nights. He picked me up from the airport and immediately took me around to see Copenhagen. He had many things planned and took me to see places that I otherwise wouldn't have on my own. I also really enjoyed our conversations where he shared his views and perspectives, and travelling experiences. I can't be more thankful for everything and I hope to see you in Singapore sometime!
Claus is a great host. He's kind, polite, knowledgeable and funny and does everything he can to make sure you have a great time in Copenhagen. Would definitely stay with him again!

I stayed with Clause for 3 days. He did a tour in Copenhagen for me and two other couchsurfers, which was absolutely amazing. We saw places that you can't find in the travel guides, had a great dinner and a even better Glogg later on in Tivoli. He also showed me his music studio, which is pretty cool and very professional. 

On the next day Clause took me on a trip to m√∏ns klint, a cliff in the south east of denmark. We came along lighthouses and a big limestone quarrel on the way. Once we arrived at the cliff, we had a very adventurous time because the water was on a quite high level, so everything was a bit muddy and wet. That didn't stop us from going down to the bottom of the huge cliff, trying to follow the small line of sand. We ended up with feed covered in mud and Claus almost lost his shoe. Definitely the most funny walk ever! I'm so glad that i had the chance to get this amazing and really authentic experience of Denmark. 

Thanks a lot, Claus!

#antihygge :D

Claus offers a completely unique and analytical perspective on the world. Although the actual time we spent together was short, our conversations were incredibly thought provoking and intellectually stimulating.  I can honestly say that his perspective on life has inspired me in more ways than one. His generosity, selflessness, and trust in the world around him is something that I will never forget. Whoever has the opportunity to meet Claus is in for a wonderful surprise. Thanks again!

Claus is a very talkative man who has a lot of stories to share. There was a heavy rain in Copenhagen when I arrived so unfortunately it was very difficult to explore the city with that weather conditions. I met with Claus in the evening and he showed me some very nice places of the city. Unfortunately, his car had broken down so we couldn't see a lot of attractions but anyway we had a really nice talks. 
Then we went to his place and he shared with me some drinks. He is an extremely active person and likes spending time outdoors but the weather didn't allow us to do a lot. But anyway, in the morning we took a trolley near IKEA and he drove me to the station and that was a real fun. 
I hope the next time I will be in Copenhagen we can meet up again and do much more things together.

Claus is active and loves adventure along with being musically skilled. He is sure to show you the spots in and around Copenhagen that you are interested in. Thanks again for showing me parts of Denmark I would have otherwise never even known about! Cheers- Cat

Claus is full of energy and spirit! He has some crazy travel stories he'll share with you too. Interesting guy with a positive outlook. Thank you for showing me the city, the beach, and for letting me use your roller skates!

Claus was really really helpful! His knowledges about Copenhagen and suburbs made my staying there so cool! He's a big fan of spontaneous traveling and doing outdoor activities, so, if you like it, then Claus is a perfect host for you :)

Claus is the amazing host who I have not met in real person. But he left me with the key without a doubt - this is the first time I've experienced couchsurfing without seeing host in real! It's really a matter of trust. But I have to apologize that I accidentally broke a glass while cooking. I felt so sorry about that. I still appreciate him letting me stay. If there is second chance again, I hope to meet and chat with Claus in real person !

Claus spent tons of time and showed me much of Copenhagen. He is interested in deeper conversation, and likes to always stay active and doing things (which I am the same way though had hurt my foot and wasn't able to keep up!). I wish you the best, and hope you get to travel Europe this summer!

text:
I have met Jared at a hangout in Copenhagen. We shared some improv comedy, a meal & a night full of dancing. Was good fun. We talked a lot about different things eg. family, culture, music. When i started moaning about me living in quite a big appartment in Horsens and that i'd love to host people but i simply dont get any requests cause it is in the middle of freaking nowhere he said that he night come and stay with me.
A few days later i got a couch request from him for the following weekend. He was a very good guest. Very friendly and clean and had no troubles venturing out on his own.
One evening we "tried" to go out (the town where I lived had little to offer but we still found a bar and a late night pizza). Then on the last day we went to a nearby city and did some touristy stuff there together followed by an international meet up event. I had a very good time with him and would recommend spending some time with him. Who knows maybe i come by to stay with him when im in CPH :)
Jared was in a CS event in Copenhagen with no place to sleep that night so he came to my place. He is a model guest. Great experience hosting him. Hope see you soon!

After having a rough start in CPH, Yen Cheng and his friend Aster were there to receive me warm.  He is a very considerate host, shared his food with me (and lovingly prepare it) was to make sure to send me tips, even though he had very busy days with work. He also has lend me a bike which made it very easy (and cheaper) to get around Copenhagen . As he is very busy you do have to be considerate of being busy as well because you‚Äôll need to leave early and maybe can only get back in late. If you make good agreements, everything goes smoothly. There was an evening I was later than the agreement because of a bad experience, and forgot to ask for his number earlier, so make sure to ask for his number so you can call him and he will wake up! His place is close to valby station which has 3 trains going into Cph central area.  For my last evening he joined for food and drinks and we had nice talks (especially about Asian food). I would definitely stay with him again (wherever that is).
Jared is so flexible and easy going person. His food is so tasty üòã great location. I'd definitely love to stay again or host him. Thanks Jared for everything.
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Copenhagen, Capital Region of Denmark, Denmark

text: Yen Cheng and I hanged out together at Copenhagen Culture Night with some of his friends. They are all nice and hospitable. We really had a good time together. His place is clean and warm, and locates just one station away from Copenhagen central station, which is quite convenient. Since my phone was not available outside Sweden, he kindly borrowed his SIM card to me. We had breakfast he made together the next morning. I would definitely recommend Yen Cheng since his such a good host. Looking forward to seeing you again!

Yen Cheng is very thoughtful and spoilt his guest. His place is simple but good enough for a solo traveler. He is willing to share his local resources and knowledge for the guest depending on their own interest. With his help, my journey in Copenhagen is smooth and compact.

One tips for people who want to stay with Yen Cheng, do respect he have 9-5 jobs and living in a sharing flats.
Being quiet in the early morning and night is important.

It is great experience to meet him, and looking foreword to host him in Stuttgart Germany!

He is a very friendly and thoughtful host.  I stayed with another couch surfer from Singapore. He offered us food and tips to travel. We went to Tivoli together and had a nice time. He also rented me his bike and shim card, so I was able to travel all around Copenhagen easily.
I was so lucky to stay at your place in Copenhagen. Thank you for everything! 
All the best. :-)

Yen is such a nice guy, he help out with everything he could, he share with me his food, he suggested me places to visit, he even went with me to some of them, he borrowed me a SIM card so I could have
internet. So if you go to Copenhagen don‚Äôt lose the chance to meet him or staying with him if possible you won‚Äôt regret it. And hope to see you soon again, :)

We asked to stay with Yen for three nights but we fled after first one. I have to say that he is very friendly and kind, we could also meet his girlfriend and they seem to be very nice people. However, we arrived to his place and we didn't know that we were going to stay with 5 other people in the same room (4 small kids!). I know he wants to help many people, but for the sake of this family and our, he should at least inform us about situation, cos before we declined other host to stay with him. We also couldn't get alone with him, cos he was too busy so basically we couldn't know him at all, as well I'm not sure if he knew anything about us, what is not written in the profile. 
Maybe that was huge misunderstanding, and I believe that he is very helpful, but it's not good if you want to help everyone in the same time. Even though, I think in different situation we would stay with him again.

He is very helpful and kind. Thank you for his brithday cake (my son birthday) treat.
Although I have four kids travel with me and they are a bit noisy , he still host us for few nights.
His house like a small united nations, my kids happy to meet the people from Poland, Sweden and Vietnam.
Anyway, is a good experience for us to couch surfing in other country.
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur Federal Territory, Malaysia

text:
During around my two weeks staying in Taipei, Yen Cheng was engaging me into a lot of hikes and meet up. He connected me with other couchsurfers and we did a lot of great things. He opened his house to many couchsurfers and offered me a chance to meet a mother couchsurfer traveling with her 4 children. 

Yen Cheng is fun, he made me laugh alot. Extremely flexible to my spontaneous agenda.

His flat locates at a very good location with bus mrt shops around.

A caring host and an active cs member who makes taipei cs community just super cool!!!!

Bravo!
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Ho Chi Minh City, Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam

text:
We stayed (me and my son) with Jared and...Oh what to say, that have not already been said? Besides Jareds way to make you feel welcomed, relaxed and taken care of, this man offers an extremely humble and positive attitude towards life and humans. I think there is beauty inside that goes beyond words. 
A genuin CS:er, trustworthy and interested, making an effort to spend time together and help in most ways.
Thank you from the bottom of my heart!

Probably the best host you'll find ; he was a really kind and considerate host who went out of his way to make sure I had a fun and fulfilling experience in Taiwan and in his home ~ by the end of my stay we were practically all friends. He's also a very hands-on host he introduced me to night markers, took me around on his scooter so I could take photos around the city and best of all introduced me to some great hiking trails !

Jared was one of the best hosts I've had to this day. I just flew in and needed to get some rest asap and he was accommodating. Next day we went on an adventure around Taipei and went hiking! He's a great man and a great host. Would recommend.

Yen cheng (Jered) was √† wonderful host and I couldnt ask for more! He was very welcoming, picked me up and showed me around Taipei. He gave me lots of information, always textning me places to go and visit. He also showed me some really good restaurants and local markers- places I wouldnt have known about without him. 

Jared has √† lovely, clean home. And I got MY OWN room!! Most of the time his girlfriend was there and she was really nice too! 

I would definitly stay with Jered again and I highly recommend him for everyone who Will travel to Taipei. 

See you in Malm√∂ Jered! Hugs!!

Jared was extremely helpful every step of the way and I really enjoyed my stay. He was thoughtful enough to give me a constant stream of ideas and activities to do during Taipei's "plum rain reason." Introduced me to amazing Hakka food with his friends. He even invited me to eat his homemade food while he was gone at work, and gave me vitamins when I was feeling sick! I stayed in both the living room and  a private room, which were both very clean. He is a really chill guy and I would be more than happy to host him and his gf, should they ever find themselves in NYC! Thanks again!!

Jared was very nice and helpful. We had dinner together and a nice chat. Even after we left the next morning, he sent recommendations on a local breakfast place and suggestions on transportation. Best of luck in Copenhagen!

Jared is friendly and easygoing, 
He is happy to share many useful informations for you, and he introduces some friends for me. Wish him has a beautiful life and excellent achievement in Denmark.
üòäüòä
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Taiwan Province, Taiwan, Province of China

text: Jared was such a great host! He was very accommodating to my arrival time and even picked me up at the station.  He's a real down to earth guy who's willing to help any couchsurfer. Living in Taiwan his whole life, he's got a lot of recommendations to make your stay in Taipei memorable. Thank you for the breakfast and lovely stay. Take care!

at first i thought YenZheng was a serious man who will give me a lot of rules to follow, and i probably have to go to yangming mountain alone. But things turn out to be that he is quite easygoing and propose that we go to the mountain together. Finally, he , with a another packpacker (his friend)accompanied me a whole day on the mountain and a whole evening to see the minority assembly. this is such a good mountaineering experience, really thank you for your guide and company!

It was a great experience!!He's a very nice guy.He gave lots of recommendation of places and food.After learning that we haven't seen Taipei night view,he offered to bring us  for a midnight hike at a nearby hill just for that.Its my first time night hike and the view are worth the hike !Thank you Wu!

This was the 2nd time I stayed at Jared's, and actually, it was his lovely sister who hosted me this time. Jen's SO thoughtful and helpful! And an interesting conversationalist, just like her brother Jared. I don't want to wear out my welcome, but I look forward to the next time I can stay with them...

We stayed with Jared and his sister Jen for three nights over the new year. They were welcoming , kind, helpful and all round really great hosts. We are grateful to have met both of them. They were always willing to help us find our way. Jared took us for a tour around the city, allowed us to experience Taiwanese breakfast and was willing to take us to Tai chi. We were lucky Jared and Jen had some time for us and we hope to see our new friends again

Jerry actually saved us in Taipei for NYE 2017. Further plans didn't work out and he was willing to host us even if there have been already three couples staying with him. So it got a little bit crowdy. üòÑ
Jerry showed us around. He and his sister Jen even gave us freedom to come back on NYE whenever we wanted. Not everybody would do that and we appreciate it. 

Jerry and Jen are lovely people and very very helpful. We also had some good conversations and a great time at all. 

It was really nice to meet you guys! Looking forward to meet you in Austria one day. üòä
We would recommend them to everybody. Taipei is great. üòÑ

Jerry and his sister are wonderful hosts. They are really caring and thougtful, spending a lot of time taking us to various attractions in Taipei, and even willing to climb the moutain at night to get us to a good spot to watch the firework. We cannot thank them enough for their amazing hospitality.
Yen Cheng and his sister are super great hosts, nice and kind. The breakfast was awesome! Thanks so much. Hope to have you both in Italy :)

text: Doing everything to make you feel comfortable. Great guy, so happy i met him and his sister jen.

Yen Cheng (Jared) and his sister, Jen, were really welcoming! 
From the first day, when they came to pick us up from the train station, and up to the last day when they helped us trying to figure out how best we can travel Taiwan.
They helped us with everything we needed, they showed us some awesome local places, they celebrated Chanukah with us, and much more!:-)

My girlfriend and I would surely keep in touch with them, and we will recommend them to any couchsurfer in a heartbeat!

Thanks for everything Jared & Jen!

Jared and his sister Jen (they're a couchsurfing team) were warm and attentive hosts. I only stayed with them for two nights but felt as if we bonded and became friends in the short time. They took me and two other couchsurfers from Spain who were also staying with them around town to see many sights and eat lots of food :) Jared even woke up at 6am to do Tai Chi in the park with me (my first time). They were like tour guides that treated me like family, and I'm grateful for the opportunity to stay with them.

Yen and his sister Jen are the best hosts ever! My boyfriend and me spent with them, their friends and another Couchsurfer an incredible weekend. They accepted us even they already had another CS and the offered to us as much as they could. They are so friendly and happy people. They took us for some meals at typical places, they explained us all the things that we wanted to know about Taiwan and its history. Also Yen took us for a trekking. Their house was really big and comfy, even better than description and location was good close to MTR station. We really had to much fun with them and we seriously want to stay with them again next time!

Yen Cheng (aka Jared) is one of the best conversationalists I've ever met. It was so fun chatting with him--he's a great listener, asks interesting questions, and has plenty of uncommon experiences to relate.  I didn't have much time to talk with his housemate (his wonderful sister), but she's a quick-thinking problem solver  who can help you get A to B in Taipei the most efficient way. I was lucky enough to meet their mother, who very kindly did some sewing repair work for me on a bag I couldn't bear to throw away. After meeting her, it was obvious where Jared and Jen got their wonderful hospitality genes from!

Cico and Julius were lovely hosts - welcoming on arrival, helpful with navigation and took the time to explore sights with us. They are genuinely kind hearted people and we lived hangout out with them.
Thank you for sharing your apartment with us and for making us feel very much at home. Please let me know if you are ever in Australia or New Zealand :)

Cico was polite and welcoming. But i wouldn't stay with him again, he didn't respect my personal space and after a point he was a little bit too friendly and i was feeling uncomfortable. He should have told me that we would share a bed with him being half-naked, but that was an unpleasant surprise for me. He didn't hurt me in any way but i had to leave his place and book a hotel room that cost me 130euros. His place is clean and i think he didn't mean bad, but some things should have been clearer.
It was really nice experience. Thanks to Cico and his friend Julius I now know a lot not only about Copenhagen, but also Uganda!
Jan was an awesome host. He helped me around with everything he could and showed me around

Staying with Adriano has been a really great experience! He received us at a last minute request and he was really nice! He warned us about the tiny room he has but anyway we got there and it has been very comfortable. He is easy going and kind. He offered us a bed and a delicious Italian coffee in the morning as well as some recommendations for the city, so it has been fantastic! He is now part of our trip! 
Thank u Adriano! 
-Maria and Elena
Buen compa√±ero, alegre, divertido y con espiritu de adolescente con ganas de comerse el mundo! 100% recomendable

text: Crazy good host. Knows the best pizza places in Copenhagen!

Jon, my friend :) 
First of all, Thank you so much for everything. I really appreciate you hosted me and Sophia in your beautiful home and I am super happy we met in Copenhagen. 

I met Jon at a cs 'meetup' and we spent an afternoon together, with two other couchsurfers. During the evening he realised that me and my friend, Sophia, did not have a place to stay for the weekend back then. So he offered us to stay at his place for two nights. It was really last minute and it was an amazing experience for me. People like Jon always remind me on why I love to use cs. Meeting this individual personalities from all over the world. Having random talks about life and sharing a great time together. 

We went to a food market, had some beers in Christianshaven (not sure how to write that and too lazy to google haha), walked around the city, went to a beautiful park and chatted a lot. Jon welcomed me in his home like if he is welcoming a friend. Things like that are amazing while traveling. He is a generous and helpful guy and my stay was amazing. I am sure it was not our last time we saw each other ;) 

Hasta luegoooo Jon, 
thank you!
Nina :)

text: Andrej is a wonderful coucher, who I have ever met. There was a feeling that we had come to visit our old friend and I know him since I remember myself. We were very welcome guests for him, not just surfers who is looking for a host. He has provided for us beautiful trip with his friends to the danish castles, to the land point where you can see Denmark, Sweden, the Baltic and North Seas at the same time, to the summer residence of the Danish Queen and we drove along the coast of Denmark with spectacular views. Next days we had nice excursion in Copenhagen with such places that we would never open for ourselves without Andrej, we had nice time in the famous Tivoli park, went together to the night party, walked along the river and through the main attractions of the city.  Besides nice host at Andrejs's place, which is close to the city center and is located in the safety area, we spent hours talking to each other and it was fascinating time with controversial issues and interesting opinions, we had champagne in the morning before our departure, which is unbelievably, but so great to remember. I strongly recommend Andrej as a coucher, he made our trip unforgettable and I'm proud that I have met him. Nice time and I hope to meet him again!

I want to thank Andrej for his warm host in Copenhagen. He spent all the day with me and showed all the landmarks and sights. Since he has lived in the city for a long time, Andrej knows pretty much about it. I would recommend him for travellers. Of course, you are always welcome in Kiev!

It was a joy to stay at Milda and Rasmus' home. They are lovely and warm and made me feel at home very quickly. They were helpful about what to see in Copenhagen and it was such fun to meet some of their friends as well. It would be a joy to host then in Australia! :)

Eliza and Nikolai was really really great! Both of them are kind, funny, friendly and knowledgeable
Is was fun and interesting spending time with them and talk - I've learned a lot about life in Denmark. 
Me and Eliza spent 2 mornings together, in one of them we went for a walk to a beautiful church near their home and in the other we went to eat late lunch and it was good place with good food. In I In both cases, was good company, I could have talk with her for days :)
Thanks Eliza and Nikolai - I couldn't ask for better experience for my first couchsurfing :) 
Hope to see you next year in the Eurovision  ;)

text: Stella is a great and hospitable host who assured a very pleasant stay. From a pick-up from the train station to a wonderful meal and good company, she made sure I was comfortable. text: Me and my friend stayed at Glenn‚Äôs place two nights. He was a friendly, welcoming and cool host ever! He was busy that‚Äôs why  we could not spend much time together but we had breakfast, and dinner. He gave quick tips about Copenhagen.We also  had chance to meet his roommate Neil.He was fun to hang out. Guys thanks for making our stay just wonderful hope to see you again . You are always welcomed in Istanbul.

Glenn and his roomates are very generous, creative, and attentive hosts! I had a wonderful time cooking with them, learning about Copenhagen, playing very entertaining games, and meeting Glenn‚Äôs beautiful baby daughter. Glenn owns a bike rental company. He lent a brand new bike to me so I could explore the entire city during my very short stay.  The ‚Äúcouch‚Äù offered was closer to a bed where I felt I had privacy.  I couldn‚Äôt be more grateful to have stayed with such a lively and interesting bunch of people! Thank you Glenn!

Unfortunately I didn‚Äôt get to spend too much time with Glenn and his girlfriend Senna, but from the little time we have spent you could see that they are great people and hopefully we‚Äôll get the chance to be better reacquainted next time I‚Äôm in the area. Their flat mate Neil was a great company for my last day in Copenhagen.

Glen is a good host willing to share with his guests the moments of his family life and is ready to help with everything you need. He enabled an unforgettable outlook of Copenhagen on two wheels. Thank you very much and you are always welcome to Belgrade.

Before anything Is fair to say that Glenn offered himself as a host!!
And not only that he was very kind helping me about transportation. I enjoyed very much riding a bike around 'up and down' of the city. I could say I've been everywhere but I hope not (that's a good reason to go back again).
The first Nights we had some chats about history and tips about the city.
The last night we enjoyed a dinner together, board games and I had my first poker experience but after a long day riding and some drinks I suppose is better to try again!
Thanks Glenn and the house team!
Was a nice one...
THANKS

We had an amazing stay with Glenn and Sanne! They were always up for hanging out and we often stayed up chatting and playing games. We were lucky enough to share New Years eve with them and they put on a dinner party and invited other travellers over which was an amazing way to welcome 2017! Glenn also often drove us into town if he was going and even took us on one of his bike tours one day (he owns a bike tour company)! If you're lucky enough to stay with them you will have an amazing time!

Glenn was the perfect host. He gave me directions on how to get to his place then picked me up from the metro station. He treated me with complete faith from the beginning and helped in a lot of ways, even hooked me up with a bike for the few days I was staying. Thanks for everything!
We are having a great time in his place, wonderful people, very friendly dog, very cozy place and very very very comfortable coach. I'm so happy Glenn was our host!  üíØ +

Glenn hosted me even though he was in the process of moving from a place to an another and had so much to do, I didn't get to spend much time with him but he made himself available to help me out.

Thanks a lot Glenn, I hope to see you at some point in Scotland :)

Glenn is LEGEND!  He very kindly hosted me last minute whilst he prepared and hosted a MASSIVE birthday dinner party.  I got to meet a lot of people and have interesting chats and was fed and watered like a queen.  It was fleeting but very memorable.  Thank you so much Glenn - you started an awesome weekend in CPH!

Glenn hosted a friend and me when 
we were visiting Copenhagen for a festival.
Things went really smooth -- we could 
enter and leave his flat at will, which is
great when you sleep all day and 
return from shows at 4 AM. There were three
other surfers around, two guys from the U.S.
who were on vacation, and a danish guy staying
in Copenhagen for job interviews. Glenn himself
fled to his girlfriend, so we met only 
for a very short time -- which was sad, because
he seems to be an interesting character; but, like
many interesting people, he's always on the go.

One should add that Glenn's flat is not for
those with increased cleanliness standards. A
real hippie dwelling, if you will :) But hey, 
that's couchsurfing, not a five star hotel, right?
If you're in Copenhagen for partying and not 
for a honeymoon, then this is your place! 
I'd always come back.

Me and my friend stayed at Glenn's apartment for two nights. He's really open and welcoming. He gave us keys, a map with circled places to go to and said to make ourselves at home - so we did! We felt really good at his apartment. Oh, and he has the best location ever! Glenn, thank you again for your trust and letting us stay. That was my first CS experience and I couldn't have asked for more.

text: I stayed with Glenn for 6 nights. He was very friendly and welcoming. He gave me the keys of his apartment and he even offered me his food!. Thank you Glenn for letting me stay, I had a great time.

Glenn was a great host. Super generous and open with his apartment. Glenn is a wonderful host!

 I can fully recommend him

I had some really nice days in Copenhagen!
I was so great to stay at Glenn's place, so easy to feel at home.
He borrowed me a map, a guidebook and one of his bikes and gave me some good tips to discover the city and I had the amazing chance to d-dive with another couchsurfer.

Staying with Glenn was like a cherry on top of our Danish trip. I guess I want to be the same type of host when I grow up:) Even though he was busy at work and stuff, he had everything so well-organized for surfers to have a great stay. He let us borrow two of his bikes and gave some tips that helped me totally rediscover Christiania, and I had been there a few times before! Glenn treated us with a yummy veggie soup and had a fridge full of freshly d-dived food free for sharing. I only regret not having dumpsterdived together, but maybe some day...:) He's also got a bike rental/repair store, and helped me find a few details I'd been desperately looking for.  Altogether, he's a super chill and no-frills host, and it was a pleasure to meet him and surf his couch. Thanks a bunch!

text: Glenn is a fantastic host and a great guy to hang out with. Glenn was so generous with his time and resources - he lent us bikes, cooked for us, took us out on the town, and spent a whole day showing us around Christiania. We had a fantastic time in Copenhagen as a result. I would definitely recommend Glenn extremely highly to any other surfers. And I hope we meet again!!

Our Cs experience with Glenn was very good, he invited us when he saw our open request!
we only spent two days with him but had a great time, we joined him for a big dinner he prepared and met many nice people! 
Glenn is very easy going and relaxed, gave us some tips around town, he's simply a cool mate :)

Glenn is an easy-going, free man, giving off a relaxed atmosphere that infects you also. The best part of my stay was Big Dinner on the second day, with 31 neighbors gathered in a cozy kitchen downstairs. I had fun doing the preparation, though all I could do was cleaning the mashrooms (I really felt curious why we did it with a towel instead of washing them :) And then they were transformed into.. something, which tasted very good. Thanks for the nice time, Glenn!

Me and my friend spent some days in Copenhagen at Glenns place and he made us having an amazing time in this beautiful city! We got a key to his appartment (and were amazed by him being so trusting towards strangers), we had a great night out with Eiffel beer and chocolat muffins! He offered us a guidebook, recommended us places to see and even proposed us to take his car for a daytrip!
We have both never stayed with someone who is so much into couchsurfing, who is willing to share everything he owns, who is open, friendly, helpful and easygoing. Hope you all meet him one day!

Glenn is an open minded person who's fun to be around with, cooks delicious dishes and definitely knows how to party! (:

I hope your afternoon was nice and cozy; thanks for having me, even though it was such a short time.
response: {'id': '15008770', 'text': 'Hanna came over one Saturday evening with her friends while a number of friends and I were supposed to play board games but had succumbed to the allure of the newly arrived spring weather, chilling at Christiania, three guitars, a heap of cheese, white wine and bubbles. text: Glenn hosted me for several nights on my trip through Scandinavia. I stayed at his place in Copenhagen which was small but nice and very central. Glenn is a very kind and laid-back guy, he's quite a chef, runs his own business and he's a singer too. He'll make you epic breakfasts almost every day and have lots of people gathering around for dinner at nights! Glenn is very sociable and super helpful, he provided me and a friend with bikes and even let this friend stay at his place for a night. Definitely hope to see him again!

text:
Staying at Glenn's was my first couchsurfing experience as a guest and I could not have asked for a better one!

Glenn is relaxed and easygoing guy.
Despite, he was working a lot he found some time to chat and hang out.
Just after we came to his small but cosy flat, he took us to the indian restaurant and showed us how to spend a chill evening in Christiania with some local specials :)

What's more he told us about nice street party, introduced to some of his friends and even offered us his own bed.

I really regret that we didn't manage to find each other our last night in CPH. 
Hope to see you one day in Cracow!

***************************************

text: Hey guys, Me and Siiri surfed T‚Äôs couch in CPH. It started with (awesome cauliflower-cherry-almond-salad), then there was this stuff with (badass shower experience) and it ended with (extravagant bicycle tour).

I defintely enjoyed staying at Thor's.
He is creative, but at the same time practical and (really :D) direct. No blandishments with him.

He accepted my last minute request and late arrival. We had a pancake party at his place, and an Italian lunch. I shared my room and met plenty of surfers in the following days. That's because he tries to welcome as much real CSers possible in the real CS spirit! He even left me the entire home for a whole day.

If you wanna crash to a cool host in a cool flat, Thor is your man! ;)

Thorbjorn is one of the persons, whom once you get to know, you want to stay definitely in touch with him. He hosted us while our stay in Copenhagen, baked self-made bread (this taste I will not forget! It was delicious!) and prepared his specialty: pancakes! :) Furthermore Thorbjorn recommended us some very nice and interesting places to see and it was a very great experience to go around with his huge cargo bike. Thanks to him our small son had an unforgettable time in Denmark (as he took us to Tivoli Park and guided us to the most fun attractions. We've spent there half of a day and had the happiest child in the world! :) ).  Thor - we would be happy to host you too one day and show you our place :)

I had a wonderful stay at Thor‚Äôs. When I arrived he picked me up from the station and we went exploring in his big bike. He introduced me to a few of his friends and family members, and on the second night we had a pancake party, where more couchsurfers came and hung out. Thor‚Äôs great in the fact that you can sit down and talk about everything and anything. If you get the chance to meet him, definitely take him up on the offer. (Also make sure you are up to date in movie references! It will come in handy). 
Thanks again for having me, let me know when you make it down to Australia. Take care.

My girlfriend and I stayed with Thor for three nights, and it couldn't have gone better. He is very kind and thoughtful, and goes out of his way to help people.
We had the best day together on our wedding, seeing so many great places and having the coolest pics of us taken by Thor. 
There was only one negative thing about our stay, that it was too short! We will definitely come back. Thorbj√∏rn and Copenhagen are forever in our hearts now!

My partner Carlos and me have been in Thor's home this weekend and we couldn't be happier about the experience.

We, unfortunately, couldn't meet Thor, but regardless of that he's been so attentive for our whole trip. 
He's been remotly making sure that everything was alright, and in three nights that we were there he hosted three couples of couchsurfers, without even being able to go home. That shows how selfless and trustworthy is Thor.

This experience is been a true delight, because even not being possible to meet our host, we felt he was taking care of our stay. 

Thank you very much Thor, hope to see you somewhere soon! :)

Before You read I'm just gonna say, good timing good experience. If You are true and creative Thorbjorn is definitely your kind of person to meet.


From the moment I wanted to write to Thor with some technical Couchsurfing difficulties to the moment he wrote back it's all seemed so uncertain.
We came on a Friday morning after a long night on the bus. The tall man with long yellow-white hair greeted us. We climbed the staircases and came into this super cozy apartment on the top floor that crosses the building and has this wonderful windows on both sides of it.
Thor was open and simply ready to talk about any subjects and just hang right away. He gave us bikes with no question at all and showed us the nice spots around. I also was lucky to try the special bike, similar to the one people had like 150 years ago, with a huge back weel and small front one, only the whole bike is in a smaller scale.
Anyway, this was such a cool experience and this 2,5 days in Copenhagen were amazing as we both got to hang out with Thor and get to know him and even meet his brother. Plus the time for exploring the city just walking and biking was so short but so precious. The after the bridge spot near the river was so great due to the weather and company.
I would describe this person so honest, true and knowing what he wants. Around a mess, he knows his way, as probably every artistic human being. I'm sure he can tell You so much You still don't know concerning art, poetry, music etc, and he'll gladly hear your own perspectives. 


Just a wonderful man, if you are even a bit like me (look profile) you will love Thor and his openhearted treatment.

We spoke a lot about diets and fastings as well as physiology and nutrition. He get me a body composition analysis and made me a chart about my theoretical weightloss should i stick to the diet. He also showed me around and introduced me a lot of places that I did not kbow. He has a lot if friends in the city and i had opportunity to meet many friendly locals. On the top of

I stayed at his place for 2 nights. He is a very friendly guy. But I could have very good experience this time besides his support. Hopefully I can visit that beautiful city next time.

Hi Thor! Thanks a lot for welcoming us so friendly in Copenhagen and at your home! He right away filled up my empty stomache and even let us a full refrigerator when he wasnt at home. Thor was the greatest host I had so far. He has offered me a mattress just for me. He is very thoughtful, right away he showed me the best technique for calming down to fall easier asleep. I really enjoyed his comfortable tricycle while he was showing us the beautiful city he is living in.
Thanks for everything and I wish I will soon get some cousine in Copenhagen ;-)
Zarja
He was not there when I stayed but so kind to let me have his place for the weekend !  Also kindly offered me anything in his fridge. Good location next to the lake!

A guy with a big heart! It was wonderful staying with thorbjorn , he helped me with great local tips that I really liked and kept going back to, he also helped me with setting up my own Google webpage, haha, I'm ever so thankful, and stay safe and all the best !

Pancakes with lemon and sugar!
Thorbj√∏n was very friendly. We did a lot of things together. He is an  interesting and open person. I felt comfortable, like in my home. I enjoyed a lot!  He is good cooker too!

Well, it's very hard to put in words, how amazing it was to have Thorbj√∏rn as my very first cs host, but I'll do my best.

text:

He hosted me in a very last minute on my spontaneous visit to Copenhagen and, despite being in the middle of intense home renovations, he welcomed me with open arms. We had long talks about many interesting topics, from working with people with impairments to South African ZEF, we actually shared many more interests than traveling and meeting interesting people.
I now leave Copenhagen with a warm feeling, the one of leaving a friend, just to say "see you again soon buddy"!
Everything was memorable. Best host ever. Took me around the city and show me the best places. Super friendly and incredibly nice.

Staying with Thorbjorn was an absolute pleasure. I was originally meant to be staying on my own however I made a friend along the way with the same travel route. I asked Thorbjorn if my friend was able to come along, which he very kindly said yes to. Thorbj√∏rn is absolutely hilarious. I wish you all the best with the renovations!

Thorbj√∏rn hosted me even though his place was just under a serious reconstruction. The floor was already gone! The stay was great. He will make sure you know where to go and have your day full. He even took me and another couchsurfer around Copenhagen in his bike! I'd definitely recommend anyone to stay with Thor, as you will find a great host and a new friend.
Very easy going guy who was good to chat with and gave some tips on how to enjoy Copenhagen

I'm sure Thor does not need another glowing reference, but I'm going to attempt one anyway.

He's such a kind hearted guy who has experienced so much, he has advice for just about anyone. Thank you for trusting me with your  house and plants, for teaching me how to make your amazing bread, for showing me the kind of work you take up sometime, and for introducing me to Danish television personalities. It was a great glimpse of an interesting life. Hope the construction does not screw up more of your lovely place and may you find excitement in the surprises life brings :)

Thor is the perfect CS Ambassador. He hosts all that he can and lets us comfortable and cozy at his place. Incredibly fun and friendly, I don't need to say much more to describe him, other than saying I just left and already miss him much.

Staying at Thorbj√∏rn for a couple of days was a fantastic experience. He is a very relaxed, helpful, flexible and most of all a very fun guy to be around. If you respect and still want to travel by the old Couchsurfing principles (some people now days expect CS equals Airnbnb or a hostel - in this case, I suggest you look for someone else) I can assure you will have a great time staying at Thorbj√∏rn's conveniently located flat.
