text:
If you truly love the principles of couchsurfing, then you will love Thorbj√∏rn who is one of the true ambassadors of hospitality, openness, the culture of sharing, trusting and just going out there and embracing humanity with a big open heart.  Surfing at his place felt just very true in the sense that you become his flatmate the first second you step into the apartment.  And the doors are almost literally open all the time, so expect to have at least one or two additional people to share the living room with. He is a big ball of energy, very funny, creative and extremely flexible, helping you with whatever troubles you have (and we had quite some:) unconditionally. 

If you do not truly love the principles of couchsurfing, then Thorbj√∏rn is not your man! If you expect to have your peace and comfort as if you would be in an airbnb or hotel and hang out just for a beer one evening, then you will really not enjoy staying with him and he will not be happy with your visit either since he really looks for a more hones and close connection with people. So think twice, cause his house is a true CS community which can be for some a bit too much I guess.  

Well, for me, it was just great! I love this guy and I really appreciate his ways and attitudes, I can only salute him and send a big fat hug across the continent. Thank you dear, you've been more than wonderful!

Thobj√∏rn is open in a lot of meanings. He basically shares his life with his couch surfers. Doesn't matter if there is one, or five of them. He loves to hang out together and he is an outspoken person.
Unluckily he was sick when I surfed there, but nevertheless he was welcoming and warmhearted. I would have handled things differently, but this is one of the beauties in life - that we are all so different - and this is also a good reason to be hosted in someone's life: get to know the thoughts and behaving of others...
I enjoyed my stay at Thobj√∏rn and still hope for some shared games or outdoor-activities in the next days, or during my future stays in Copenhagen.

My experience with Thorbj√∏rn was interesting. The first night there were 7 or so couch surfers so the only place available for me to sleep was in his bed. I awoke a couple times throughout the night to unwanted cuddling. It would have been nice to know there was not floor space available before arriving late at night. The next two nights I was in the other room with other surfers so I felt much safer. He's a very friendly (some would consider him too friendly) and funny guy that made his surfers feel right at home. He made us a yummy traditional breakfast and he let us ride in his bike cart while driving around giving us a day tour of the city. He's sarcastic and witty but his humor is a bit dirty so just make sure you're prepared. He's also a bit touchy and gets in your personal space sometimes so if that's an issue for you I'd sleep elsewhere. However, I enjoyed meeting him and being able to  explore Copenhagen
column18: {'text': "Yeah, there probably were a few couchsurfers too many, I'm sorry if I made you feel uncomfortable, if you'd said, I could have cuddled Sta≈° instead, to be fair, I did warn you about the many couchsurfers and the cuddling...", 'author': {'id': '318221', 'publicName': 'Thorbj√∏rn K√ºhl', 'publicAddress': {'id': '3023398', 'description': 'K√∏benhavn, K√∏benhavn, Denmark'}, 'avatarUrl': 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/ht-images.couchsurfing.com/u/318221/CB2B3520-D5F4-4840-BCFC-DBCF99D4B65B', 'status': 'yes', 'isVerified': True, 'isDeleted': False, 'blockedBy': None}, 'createdDate': '2016-06-23T20:33:22Z'}

text:
Thobjorn was a nice host! He hosted me and my two friends in his place for four nights. He also threw a pancake party for Couchsurfers, but we weren't able to be there, unfortunately! We had fun with him and we really enjoyed it!
Take care Thobjorn and see you someday again! :)

Thorbj√∏rn is a really chill and friendly guy, with a mischievous sense of humour and a very open and direct manner.  I sent him a couch request, and it turned out he was going to be in London the week before, so we arranged for him to stay at my place, then we swapped round. 
He was a very obliging guest, and was happy to work around my schedule, even when I wouldn't be home until late. When it came time for me to stay at his place, I found that he'd packed his place with about half a dozen couchsurfers, so we were crammed into every available space. I thought this was great because it meant that I could meet and hang out with loads of other surfers, and I really enjoyed the experience (and the pancake party on my second night!). However if you're the sort of person who likes their privacy and downtime then you may want to check first because his place isn't that big (although the location is amazing and very beautiful).
Thanks Thorbj√∏rn! I had an amazing time and am so glad that I got the chance to stay with you. :)

Thorbj√∏rn had already a full house (hosting 6 people), but he kindly offer to extend the walls to fit me in. His generosity is boundless. We only spent one evening together, but it was so special that I will remember it for a lifetime. I still can't fathom how he managed to ride a pancake house, a wooden door, his lovely niece and I from one edge of the city to the other, biking seemingly effortlessly, while cracking up jokes with strangers, giving a guided tour, and DJing! He is also a skilled chef, able to coordinate a bunch of people to create a delicious meal shared with his tribe. If the city wasn't so nice, he would be a reason all to himself to travel to Copenhagen! I know for a fact that we'll meet again for more adventures :)

AMAZING EXPERIENCE AND VIBE !!!!
This was my first experience as a guest, 
And he just confirmed that how amazing it is to be also a guest as much fun as host
Unfortunately we couldn't spend much time as he was in london but we met for a short time night before, 
Very enriched thoughts, great personality, very welcoming , as he let me stay there even when he wasn't there, have to say amazing place best view and approach to best places in city, wifi kept me good on a bad weather day, and i have a great friend now, 
All in all, 
If you get a chance to stay with him, don't even think twice and he is one where you want to go, 
A home away from home
See you soon brother :)

Thorbj√∏rn is the best! We took his cool bikes out around and he showed me all around the city. Thorbj√∏rn had to leave and go to London a couple days after of my arrival and actually allowed me to host a surfer from India in his home which was awesome! :) Thor really is a great, fun and genuine guy who cares a lot about giving surfers a grand time in Copenhagen. It's sad that I will be missing the pancake party this weekend but I definitely have plans on coming back and you are always welcome to my home no doubt! Keep being awesome and thanks again üôÉ

Be prepare to have one of the best CS experience ever, Thor has to much to share with others, not just about the city, also about the life, TV shows, Mexican jokes, food and tea recipes.
 
He hosted me even he just moved to his new apartment, we shared good moments and memories in the city, and riding his bike was incredible !! 

He's an expert in jokes be careful trying to impress him. Hope to see you again Thor, never lose your sense of life and humor.
Thanks a lot

Staying with Thorbj√∏rn was memorable to say the least.  We made chicken and pizza (well more like he made it all) and he has a very generous heart.  He biked us all around copenhagen on a beautiful day, and I just really cant describe how kind, giving, and open this man is.  You will be honored to stay with him.  Thanks so much Thor, and you are welcome to stay with me  when you are in Seattle!

I was very lucky to be able to stay with Thor in Copenhagen, because our host had fell through last minute. On our first night there, he cooked a delicious dinner for us, and we felt very welcome in his home. On our last morning there, we all had breakfast together and he took us to the train station on his awesome bike. He gave me some really good advice on couchsurfing, traveling solo, and some tips on packing better. Thank you so much for making our stay in Copenhagen memorable.

Dear Thorbjorn... 
I'm so glad I could stay with you - be flexible, hang out and also have a bit of time for myself wandering around Copenhagen. Best of luck for you, find your happiness and enjoy every day, fill the flat with CSers whenever you feel it's too much empty space between white walls and there is not enough crackles on wooden floor during the day.
 
Extremely helpful, honest and precise + super pleasant 'cycling tour' attraction.

remember, we have a common dinner/party pending :)

Thorbj√∏rn is a really patient host. He was totally cool with the nervous breakdown i was having. And i particularly enjoyed his particular demostrations. This is the ultimate host people! Thanks again Thorbj√∏rn!

This is the coolest host I've ever been with!!!
He took me to the street music festival with his mega bike, it was so much fun! I would say it's one of the happiest days in my life! The next day he even made his bike like a pool so I can sit in the water under sunshine. Yes u can never imagine how cool his bike is until he shows u! 
I'm so glad that I could be the first surfer to his new apartment. Even though I only stayed here for 2nights, I already felt like home.
You can never feel bored when u're with him. So thank u! Èõ∑Á•ûÁÜä! I'll never forget how we laughed together!

Why there's no option of 'fireworks' above 'positive experience'? Thor is the most adorable guy in the universe of Copenhagen. He's witty, wise, full of calm energy and just all the splendor you can imagine plus a bonus dose! May his years be long and pleasantly fruitful in that wonderful way my days around him have been!

Thorbj√∏rn hosted me and my friend for 3 nights and I have nothing but positive things to say about him. He made us feel really welcome and he sure knows how to make your stay in Copenhagen very interesting! 

Thank you for everything! I hope I will meet you again some time - maybe in Leuven! Till then, cheers!

Thorbj√∏rn is definately an outstanding experience among all hosts I had in the last 4 years of my journey...

I was positively surprised by the way he picked me up (with his rickshaw) as well as his great vibes and positive energy that he was sharing during those few days I spent with him...you could taste it in the beer pancakes ge preapred for breakfast or in the night adventures picking up people while listening to the soundtrack of the "Olsenbanden".

Something I will never forget in my history of Couchsurfing will be the rickshaw ride we did together with two other Couchsurfers all around the city, having a great time with mermaids, eating amazing food in Christiania and having a short photoshooting...a passion that we share :-)

Thanks for the amazing time together and a different CS experience in Copenhagen. Take care and see you again for sure, Nicky :-)

P.S.: Thanks for the bicycle.

I spent a night at Thorbjorns with my friend in Copenhagen and we really enjoyed it. The highlight was when he picked us up with his big bike. We all strolled around the town until we got home, then we had a deep conversation around a cup of tea. Thorbjorn has a great sense of humor and is generally selective so I'm happy he hosted me although I still haven't got many references.
Thorbjorn was nice enough to make us discover Copenhagen when he had spare time. We had a good time sharing meals and watching movie together. He also owns a lovely and very good natured cat.

Thorbj√∏rn is a very nice guy, funny and super hospirabile! We went together to a party, he cooked pancakes for me and his friend' sons and he told me a lot of good things about copenhagen! And his cat is amazing, u've to meet IT!;)
I for sure reconmend this guy

He is really such a wonderful host - he even stayed up till late in the night to welcome me, since I had to take a very late train to Copenhagen! And when I left again, he equipped me with "lunch" for my trip on the ferry - just as thoughtful as a mum;-) 
So, as my short trip to Denmark started off rather disappointing, staying over with him was the perfect way of making up for it all. He is extremely imaginative, funny, entertaining, obviously in love with his beard and way deep into alternative living and photography. Being bored around him seems impossible!
Uh, and about the cleaning: well, it helped me to get rid of some aggressions - and anyway in the end turned out to be rather some kind of "redecorating job" ;-)
response: {'id': '16933702', 'text': 'She\'s absolutely amazing, we laughed so hard we almost cried when we watched the German ambassador to the U.S. Hans Beinholtz on the Colbert Report (who said Germans have no sense of humor) and dreamt up "existential crisis yoga" where you bow your head in shame while you reach for but never quite manage to touch your toes, lift your arms and stare helplessly into the empty void of the universe contemplating your own insignificance and do the downwards facing dog of shame while you exhale deadly carbon dioxide further adding to the greenhouse effect while you listen for the sweet sound of the scythe and long for the cold embrace of Death...\n\nAlso I wasn\'t supposed to tell you this, but she helped me clean my apartment with the fury of a thousand cleaning ladies which was a huge and unexpected bonus!', 'createdDate': '2015-01-03T23:11:09Z', 'experience': 'positive', 'relationshipType': 'other', 'isPostTrip': False, 'to': {'id': '52498'}, 'from': {'id': '318221', 'publicName': 'Thorbj√∏rn K√ºhl', 'publicAddress': {'id': '3023398', 'description': 'K√∏benhavn, K√∏benhavn, Denmark'}, 'avatarUrl': 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/ht-images.couchsurfing.com/u/318221/CB2B3520-D5F4-4840-BCFC-DBCF99D4B65B', 'status': 'yes', 'isVerified': True, 'isDeleted': False, 'blockedBy': None}, 'inverseReference': None, 'response': None}

text: Thank you for being a great host to me! Had a very enjoyable time in Copenhagen, while eating delicious pancakes, got transported around in a Dutch bike and been introduced into the freeletics which will keep me fit while travelling:-) Wish you all the best and I'll be happy to host you when you visit Holland :-)

Thorbjorn is a really really nice host ! His appartment is lovely and cosy, and Thorbjorn knows how to make you comfortable ! He brought us with his bike to make us visit the city, it was very nice ! 
We didn't spend a long time together because Thorbjorn had to work but we really had a good time.

Thank you again Thorbjorn !
Marion and Maxime.

Thorbjorn is a really nice person ! We didn't spent so much time together, but i had directly a nice feeling : easy going, interesting, funny and with a lot of energy !
And what to say about his way of making the city of Copenhagen ? It was just perfect : he went at the train station with a bike with a big case and my friend, me and our 35 kilos of bags went inside that case so that Thor could bring us to his flat ! After that, he talk to us about a "small private party", and we went in i think the best place ever in Stockholm to have a polsefest... Amazing, really !
Thanks for all Thorbjorn :)

It was a pleasure staying in Copenhagen, thank you for hosting me. And my host Thorbj√∏rn even has a wonderful cat named Gizmo. The apartment was cozy and warm, and it's location is pretty easy to find.
Thanks again!
response: {'id': '16950722', 'text': "I hosted Mantas back in October 2014, I had to work so Unfortunately I didn't have a chance to spend so much time with him.\n\nHe was very friendly and communicative, I enjoyed the short time we spend together and I'd recommend anyone to host him or stay with him if his couch is available :)", 'createdDate': '2015-01-07T10:10:59Z', 'experience': 'positive', 'relationshipType': 'other', 'isPostTrip': False, 'to': {'id': '2230765'}, 'from': {'id': '318221', 'publicName': 'Thorbj√∏rn K√ºhl', 'publicAddress': {'id': '3023398', 'description': 'K√∏benhavn, K√∏benhavn, Denmark'}, 'avatarUrl': 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/ht-images.couchsurfing.com/u/318221/CB2B3520-D5F4-4840-BCFC-DBCF99D4B65B', 'status': 'yes', 'isVerified': True, 'isDeleted': False, 'blockedBy': None}, 'inverseReference': None, 'response': None}

text: I actually surfed his bike for almost half a day. He has driven me around in Copenhagen showing the area and interesting places, and we also visited Botanical gardens together!He is really fun person to be with!Thank you!

Thorbj√∏rn hosted me in his friend's apartement in Stockholm some time back in 2007 and we spent a couple of nice days walking around the city and hanging out in parks together. Maybe we can repeat that sometime, somewhere :o)
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Orth an der Donau, Lower Austria, Austria

text: Brilliant host, unbelieveably enthusiastic about CS and gave me a tour of KPH on his bicycle!

It was really a pity that both of us were kind of busy during the days I've spent in Copenhagen.
We did not have so much time to spend taking and knowing better each other. But even though I have to say that Thorbjorn=HOSPITALITY.

Thank you for your time and place. You are (among other people) the responsible for my motivation after Copenhagen training. (I am even applying for jobs in there! :) )

Wow what a trip... It was the first time i surfed and it was so good, crazy, fun, etc. We went to a bike demo with Thorn's cool's bike, then a city tour with Masha and afterwards a CS pancake party...

Thorn i must say you're a BIT crazy but that makes you special.

Thanks a lot and hope to see you in the future. Now i have some danish jam haha

Thorbjorn is really a great and funny guys. It is so nice to sit on your bike and look around in copenhagen! shame on me you know much more Chinese history than mine, ahaha. I am happy to be your frist guest from Hong Kong. Come to my city and I will get you delicious tofu dishes!
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Hong Kong Island, Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, China
response: {'id': '3810560', 'text': "Lai Wing Chi stayed with me a couple of days, it was some of those days where I was a very active host and where everything clicked! When Wing Chi was leaving early in the morning, I had just sent my girlfriend on a train and got back and once again found Wing Chi on the way out to catch a bus. text: Thorbjorn was my last chance to find a host in copenhagen. he was busy at this time, but he offered me and my sister to stay at his place with his roomie. i met him just for a short time, but he really seemed easygoing, friendly and openminded.

Thorbj√∏rn hosted us very short-notice: he actually didn't have time but was so kind to just open the door for us. He is a very very open person and hosts many people all the time in his nice apartment, it's just great and we really felt at home!

i haven't actually met him, but his surfer noy me hosted me while he was away..  multi-level hosting! is this guy an expert CS or what! i really want to learn to juggle so hope we can meet in the future sometime

He is THE pancake master, trust me, I do love pancakes so I know what I'm writing about, and very flexible person with full of energy!! Thanks for hosting us, for lending me your amazing bike, for excellent pancake-party in the park and making our stay in CPN way more fun!
Thorbj√∏rn is a really funny guy! We discovered with a friend of mine all the town thanks to him and his strange bike! It was amazing!

text: Thorbj√∏rn is an excellent host. He definitely made me feel at home. It was a pitty we just met for dinner one day, although I slept for 2 nights in his flat. He was busy working during the week. We spoke for some time at night, shared some experiences, I took some pictures of him and of his flat... and I was really happy that he enjoyed the pictures. Very nice guy! Thanks a lot for your help and for the tips about Copenhagen!!!

text: Although I didn't have much time to get to know Thorbj√∏rn more, I really appreciate the help he offered my friend and me with organising our stay in Copenhagen ‚Äì replied quickly, ansewed innumerable questions, gave precise details. He also picked us up close to his place ‚Äì thanks for that, we could hardly find it on our own :D He seems to be a person with a huge sense of responsibility for both his participating in CS project and his job. Keep going & hope to meet you in the future!
response: {'id': '2694850', 'text': 'Ewelina and her friend were very nice, they kept me informed through email about their plans and confirmed by email that they were coming beforehand so I was never in doubt whether they would turn up or not, they also got a danish number so I could easily keep in contact with them. I wish all my surfers would be like this! She also wrote me a long and personal Couchsurfing request, wonderful!\r\n\r\nI only met them a short while when they arrived as I was busy with work, but nevertheless they were very nice.', 'createdDate': '2009-04-14T16:45:06Z', 'experience': 'positive', 'relationshipType': 'host', 'isPostTrip': False, 'to': {'id': '839830'}, 'from': {'id': '318221', 'publicName': 'Thorbj√∏rn K√ºhl', 'publicAddress': {'id': '3023398', 'description': 'K√∏benhavn, K√∏benhavn, Denmark'}, 'avatarUrl': 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/ht-images.couchsurfing.com/u/318221/CB2B3520-D5F4-4840-BCFC-DBCF99D4B65B', 'status': 'yes', 'isVerified': True, 'isDeleted': False, 'blockedBy': None}, 'inverseReference': None, 'response': None}

The kind of guys you think , I want to do all that I can so that he will be happy. What a great first ambassador experience .Thor hamelech !

text: Oh I think if you know Thorbj√∏rn, you know what couchsurfing is. He was my first couchsurfer I met and he answered all my questions I had. He is a tolerant and crazy guy, and have lots of experiences in couchsurfing. If you are in CPH met him, for coffee or better at Tivoli and take some rides with him. And after that you should drink, this combination of breast milk, normal milk, yoghurt, kefir with strawberry flavour? Sounds strange but tasted very good.

This happened a year ago, so sorry this is so late... I didn't meet Thorbj√∏rn but I picture him as some sort of CS angel, hosting wayward travelers in Copenhagen.  Thanks to meeting tons of people at his flat, I got to do some seriously amazing things in the city that otherwise, I would not have had the chance... so thank you Thorbj√∏rn!  Wherever you are!

Surfing at Thorbjorn's place was a unique experience. Our first minutes at his flat were priceless. We were quite disoriented among all these CS guests going in and out of the flat and making their way between the row of backpacks put against the wall and the mattresses covering most of the floor. We learnt from one of them that Thorbjorn was living at his girlfriend's place and he was letting his entire flat to CS people. Nobody knew exactly how many people were sleeping there that night (7-9?) and there were chances that the last ones coming back couldn't find a proper place to sleep. Then I understood what Thorbjorn meant by "hippie-like flat". At the end, the experience was fine and very enriching. It was so different from my past CS experiences as a guest! But I think I wouldn't repeat it. That's not Thorbjorn's fault at all though; he does much more for CS than I will ever do and I'm very grateful to him for having let us crash at his place. But I prefer a less massive hosting.

Thorbj√∏rn is a funny, generous, crazy guy! We had a lot of fun with him!especially in Den lille havfrue and in Tivoli. It was very nice also the brunch we did when we arrived to his place ;)

Denis is so friendly and easy going, he is a man who is living with his 2 kids (they are 10 and 14, and both know English, also his son knows French, and his daughter knows German) They are all open minded and helpful..
Denis arranged everything for us, everything means really everything.. food, beds, alcohol, suggestions, to do list.. We stayed 2 nights in his flat with my friend which is just 20-30m to Metro Station. From airport, after our flight to check out his flat he was always ready to answer our all questions about the city and all the others.. He recomment us a lot of historical places and made to do list. if you are going to stay in his flat you will sleep in living room (1 couch and 2air mattres) He has a good taste of wine (and ready to share them with you) also he is good about music..
Hope next time we will also find a way to hangout together and have more fun.
Thank you very much for kindly care about us, i appriciate it.
Best regards

Staying with Jean-Paul was a great introduction and addition to our adventure in Denmark. He had made his house very ready for us and was accommodating when we asked to arrive earlier that day. He responded quickly when we asked him questions over the app, and went much further than was required of him as a good host. Jean-Paul also has a lot of ideas. He gave what I thought was a good intellectual introduction to Denmark, in which his uneasiness with the country was most interesting, which evolved into a more than three hour conversation about the philosophical website he's working on.  He never meant to lecture us though, he made it clear that our visit could be about listening to him for however long as we wanted, or we could leave right away to explore the city. However, if you are someone who truly believes in the power of travel to widen someone's perspective, and have longed to see the world to find answers and unconventional ideas, staying with Jean-Paul is invaluable.
The most memorable thing was his good manners and honesty. I would highly recommend staying at Jean-Pauls home.

text:
If you ever come to Copenhagen do yourself a favor and stay at Rasmus place. I had  two amazing days in Copenhagen. Rasmus introduced me to a lot of his friends, all of them are nice and talkative. We had a schnaps tasting, he showed me the Copenhagen nightlife and he even took me to a party he was invited to.
His flat is nice and clean and his sofa is really comfortable, so I cannot say anything bad about the sleeping arrangements. 
There's even a grocery store right next to his flat, you can reach it within a minute.
Rasmus is an easy and open minded guy, a great host who doesn't make you feel like a tourist.
He was a really cool guy. Showed me the best places in town to have a good time. Also, he made the effort to spend some time with me. Great music collection too!

It was the first time for me in Denmark and I was very lucky to be hosted by Rasmus! At the moment I arrived he was hosting one cool girl from Montana and they both were very flexible and kind to accept me to stay with them. Rasmus showed us the city and we visited some awesome places in Copenhagen. He is a super chill host and you can really feel how he cares about you. I guess this was a key feature for me, it made my whole stay very comfortable, just like at home :)

Staying with Rasmus was the best part of Copenhague. He welcomed me as a life friend. He introduced me his friends, borrowed me a bike and showed me the city. He's really smart and definetely different from tje others, which makes him the perfect host! No wonder if you want to stay with him.

When I first contacted Rasmus, it was not to ask to stay, but because I¬¥d been "WOW-ed" by his profile - I mean who else has ever lived in Greenland! From that point on, we messaged a bit on and of and when the time came that I needed a place in Copenhagen, Rasmus was very forthcoming in offering to host me despite having plans that night. 

While my stay was only a couple of hours long due to arriving late (which also was not a problem at all for Rasmus) and having an early bus to catch (also no problem, and advice to others: just be mindful that it¬¥s early, you¬¥re in an old building with thin walls and you¬¥re not alone; others are still sleeping!) , I really enjoyed the time we spent chatting over dinner leftovers. It¬¥s all true about his flatmate by the way - he's the world's best, no doubt about it! They¬¥re both amazing people with many experiences to share despite their young age and a lot of stories to tell! 

So, the sleeping arrangements at Rasmus' place have been criticised before, but I see absolutely no reason  why other than their idea of Couchsurfing not living up to high expectations of, say,  a 5 star hotel! I had my sleeping bag with me, but I wouldn't have needed it as everything was there, blanket, pillow, mattress/couch, and Rasmus even cranked up the heating in case I would be cold sleeping in the living room. Other than that, I got a short tour of his flat with explanations and how-to¬¥s to everything so I wouldn't be lost not knowing how to work the shower or use the kitchen. 

All things considered, including the awesome flatmate and his snake Victoria II, I don't think I could have found a better place to stay. The location is great, with buses running to the centre and to Valby bus station from the nearby main street, there¬¥s a big supermarket just round the corner and for those who like to walk, like me, the city centre is within walking distance! 

I could go on and on about all the reasons why my one day one night in Copenhagen was so good (I saw a viking at Nyhavn!) but coming to Rasmus' place at night and just feeling welcome in their relaxed chilled out home was definitely a big part of the whole experience! 

To wrap this up, Rasmus is a top-notch, 10/10 host, I¬¥m feeling extremely lucky to have stayed at his place, and if he accepts your request, so should you! 

Finally, with the little Danish I learned: Tak Rasmus!!

text: Me and my friend stayed at Morten's place for 2 nights, and he is a wonderful and open minded person. text: Our stay with Jakub was very nice. Although Jakub didn't have much time to hang out together, he had no problem with chatting a little bit and giving some advice. We also could use his bike, do our laundry etc. Very friendly guy and definitely would stay again.

Jakub made us feel at home during our stay. He is very trusting and joked with us right away. He has a great sense of humor! We had interesting conversations over dinner about Poland, politics, and education systems. He was very thoughtful about asking if we had questions or if there was anything we needed and also giving us our own space. Jakub, wishing you all the best and we'll be keeping up with politics in Poland from now on. Come to Chicago anytime!

We had a nice stay at Jakub's place. When we arrived he offered us some food and drinks and we had a really nice conversation. He told a place next to his home that we should visit which we are still greatful for! Jakub also trusted us with the keys and let us leave our bags at his flat the next day. I can only recommend staying with him!
And Jakub, if you ever come to Salzburg or Klagenfurt you are more than welcome! :)
Good host, recommend him. Only disadvantage is 4th floor without elevator.

Jakub is a very nice and friendly guy that help you feel comfortable. He was also so helpful in telling me which places should I visit.
He is knowledgeable and it's interesting to talk about startups to him.
I totally recommend him as a great host.
Jakub, thanks again for your hosspitality and hope to see you probably in California.

Hihi Jakub, thanks for hosting me and my friend. I think Jakub just like my big brother haha, he is a super funny and friendly person. Jakub was really an awesome host. Fun and very kind. He even shared his food, was really respectful, talkative, up to games and movies. I could not have hoped more from a first cs experience. Thank you !

I stayed two days with Jakub in Copenhagen and couldn¬¥t have asked for a better host - despite him being a little misanthrope ;) He made sure I¬¥ll find my way around town and won¬¥t suffer lack of coffein, which is very important ;) we spent a great day talking, sunbathing and climbing at Copenhagen university and I won some new insights into economic sciences. All in all, great place to stay and highly recommend host! I¬¥ll hope to meet him again in some part of the world, maybe climbing in berlin nine month from now? ;)

Jakub was very helpful with finding out what to best see and do in Kopenhagen. He was super flexible and easy-going, gave my friend and me keys so we were able to be our own masters. Additionally he was open and funny and his company for dinner was very enjoyable. Thank you very much for the coffee and the book and just for the overall great relaxing holiday time!

Jakub is the probabely most ambitious guy I know, when it comes to sports and career ;) but very friendly and comforting aswell! We had some quite intense political discussions on the evening we arrived which was very interesting and refreshing compared to the smalltalk you sometimes get stucked in when meeting new people. On saturday he unfortunately had  to leave for a working-holiday to beware a friend from economical crises ;) and we had the apartment for ourselves the whole weekend, which was  actually very comfortable! We would definately stay again with Jakub since he s a really sympathic guy and his home is awesome aswell!
Kuba was a great host, very flexible and open. As a person he is a smart guy, a lot of knowledge and stories to share. Thank you for everything;)
I didn't spend a lot of time with Jakub but it was very good experience, he is nice, flexible and he told me about nice places in Copenhagen. Thanks again!!

Jakub is extremely kind and very fun to be with. He has great communicating skills and definately has a lot to say so you could just listen him for hours without missing a thing. I couldn't be more thankful than I am now.

Great host! Although he was very busy when I stayed with him, he still took out some time to hang out, had a nice dinner and some interesting talks. He helped me a lot and made my stay in Copenhagen very pleasant.
I would recommend anyone to host him, and you¬¥ll be very lucky to surf with him.
Thanks for everything Jakub!

text:
You can definitely count on Kuba during hardcore-situations! Some years ago I missed my train home, and cause I was in Poznan (place where he lived) I just called him asked ask If I could stay for the night. he said yes immediately! 

he is very helpful and cheerful person, I'm sure you'll be glad to meet him :)
Jakub was supposed to host me in Roskilde. In the last moment he had to cancel the request, but he got one of his friends to host me anyway.

Kuba is a great guy. Just from the very first moment he made me feel welcome in his dorms room :) He showed me around Roskilde, took me to his favorite places and even he went biking with me. (Thank you, Kuba, I did appreciate it!) 

From my experience, Kuba is reliable, fun and open person. Very friendly and very caring. I certainly recommend to meet / host him~!

text:
Kuba saved our trip to Roskilde by agreeing to host us on short notice. He went out of his way to fit two of us in his room with good comfort and even offered to go and collect my co-surfer who was lost at 4am in the morning!

His knowledge of the world and culture is impressive but his Scandinavian hitch-hiking adventure was really fascinating for an 18 year old and seems to have shaped his character in a good way. 

Thanks for hosting, putting up with us, the Polish bread, the tea, "taking us to the Russians", and the info about Poland and Opener! Much appreciated man be sure to let us know if you need something in Copenhagen.

Thank you Karoline for hosting us in Copenhagen! We felt at home and comfortable staying with you! We enjoyed spending some time with you and your children. We look forward to our next visit to your wonderful city.  Leon

Phil is really fun to hang out with...we attended the Bonaparte gig together.  He's already surfed my flat in Zurich, now I look forward to his subsequent visit to Copenhagen, my new home...he's got my couch ;-)  I'll also visit him in Hamburg. text:
Phil is great - full of energy! He and and his friend Andrew stayed at my place for only one night, but what a night it was. Although Phil prefers the Stones over the Beatles, he is an awesome person, who really knows how to party. If you host him, be prepared for some dancing and lots of interesting and fun conversations about anything, especially music. You should also be prepared, that in a random bar in your hometown, he will probably know more people than you do. 
And of course, both Andrew and Phil treated my apartment with care. 
I'm really looking forward to surf Phil's couch in Hamburg!

text: Ah. What a beautiful first surf experience. Greeted late night with the VIP package of wine and fresh sheets. Incredibly hilarious and hospitable man, with impeccable style and a record collection that will knock your socks off. Central neighborhood, comfy sleeps. Have him take you for pizza around the block. You won't regret staying with this one. Til next time, Honeybear ~ ~

Phil is such a great host! He accepted me even though he already had another surfer. I had a memorable time with him and his friends. He's a funny guy! His appartment is well-located and the couch very comfy! Hope to see u in Spain, thaanks!
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Castell√≥n de la Plana, Valencian Community, Spain

text: Where to begin... Phil is amazing! He was easy to make arrangements with for entry, his flat is incredible , and he and his friends know how to have a good time. He is beyond generous and very easy to get along with. If you have he opportunity to stay with Phil, do not pass it up!! Thank you for making my trip(s) so memorable! x

It was my first Couchsurfing and it was just perfect!:) Phil is really Nice and really helpfull:) i ate two dinners with him at home and it was really fun and decontracted :) his home is just amazing, really near from everything!:) 
I really recommand to stay at his home and i hope to see him again in Copenhagen or in Switzerland !:)

Phil accepted to host me even though he already had another couchsurfer in his flat, and when he learnt that I needed to stay in Copenhagen a bit longer, he kindly offered to host me for another three days, thus sparing me much trouble.
Staying at Phil's was one of my nicest couchsurfing experiences. He is an amazing, welcoming host, and a witty, intelligent, easy-going person with a sense of humour that I particularily liked. He made me feel at home right from the start and it was fun to spend time with him. 
I regret not having been able to go to the Islandic party with you, it seemed like it was a blast! Thanks again for everything, Phil, and let me know when you're ready for some wine tasting in Alsace :D Hope to see you soon!

Phil is the best couch surfing host I've had (maybe because it's my first time surfing). On a more serious note, Phil made this new experience for me, a wonderful one. From the moment I walked through his front door, he made me feel like I was his new best friend. We dined together, partied together, got drunk together and best of all, he opened my eyes (and ears) to amazing 90's Britpop. His passion for music is contagious and he had me dancing and laughing around his living room at 4am whilst listening to the crazy lyrics of his favourite songs. Hopefully one day he'll visit Sydney, so I can show him around my home town and prove to him that not everything in Australia is trying to eat him.  Thank you Phil for being so amazing.
column18: {'text': "Sadly there is no way I'm coming to Oz... but thanks the dangerous offer!", 'author': {'id': '229733', 'publicName': 'Phil Chambers', 'publicAddress': {'id': '2935225', 'description': 'K√∏benhavn, K√∏benhavn, Denmark'}, 'avatarUrl': 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/ht-images.couchsurfing.com/u/229733/D482301B-F013-4C14-98AA-0B2398462A52', 'status': 'yes', 'isVerified': True, 'isDeleted': False, 'blockedBy': None}, 'createdDate': '2016-08-29T15:09:53Z'}

text: Phil was a great host. He was flexible, friendly and open-minded. It was sad that we had no time to hang out together but we're sure time with him is fun time. We would absolutely stay again at his place!

Phil was a perfect host. He was so helpful, friendly, intelligent and funny. He really made me feel welcome in his home and very much embodies the spirit of couch surfing. Genuinely just a great guy all around and someone I am very happy to have met. He's done a lot of rad stuff and traveled to a lot of rad places so he's got a whole lot of good stories to tell as well. His flexibility makes him a great host as he's happy to adjust to whatever the couch surfer wants to do. Also Phil was nice and trusting enough to allow me to stay in his home while he was gone because he had leave for a concert part way through my visit (being the incredibly nice person he i,s he of course invited me to join him and go see the concert if I'd like). bonus: he has a crazy good book & record collection.  In conclusion: Phil is a good egg, 11/10 would hang out with/stay with again

Such joy to come across human beings such as Phil!:) Not only he was super friendly, energetic, and generally lovely, but he really believes in the CS stuff, in sharing! I stayed at Phil's place for 4 nights (one of the comfiest sofas, like ever), and even though Phil himself had to go away for 3 of those days, I felt that I got to know him - and the beautiful city - via his gorgeous flat. Oh and he loves food. Thank you!

We had an amazing time with Phil! His apartment is very beautiful and well-located in the city. He is lovely and funny (and definitely know how to make a party ;) ) we definitely recommend him as a host and he is welcome in France whenever he wants !

No surprise, as all the others references say, Phil is a perfect hoster with an amazing and welcoming apartment! We had a very good time in copenhaguen hanging out with him and his lovely friends, he made our week end unforgettable.
Thanks for everything Phil ! :)

My friend and I stayed at Phil's for 3 days and it was amazing! We immediately felt at home and Phil welcomed us with wine and some delicious soup. He had to go to NY the morning after we arrived, but he was kind enough to give us his keys and let us stay at his place. We spent a nice evening with him and we hope to meet him again in the future! Thanks for everything Phil xx

Phil was just the best host ever!
We had a good time, he cooked a great dinner for us and he even tried to show us around :D
As he knows I'm totally in love with the carpet in front of his fireplace, so I can only recomand to stay in his beautiful home, with his lovable friends and with the best host you can ever desire.
I'm glad to see you again in Milan ( and then Paris, for your marriage with my friend, for su sure! :) )
I hope we will be able to make you feel home as you did with us!
See you in march!

My staying at Phil's place was outstandingly gorgeus! He was flexibe with my arrival time and made an excellent dinner (the soup! #1 ). The location of his flat is perfect and easily reachable (and beautiful!) 
He also has a great taste in music, showed me a couple of his favourite records - the sound system is unbelievable! - as the songs I barely hear before. (I made a list finally :) ) 
It was easy to talk to him about everything, I could get to know more about his job, travelling - even we were talking about the UK festivals where I was working. :D  
As an obsessed biker I was also happy about he lent me one of his bikes to cycle around the city so I could explore Cph like a proper Danish. 

It was an awesome staying at your place Phil, thanks for hosting me and hope to meet you at Glastonbury in 2016 :)
Good guy, loves fire, made soup, got weird. 5/5 stars
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Longyearbyen, Svalbard, Svalbard And Jan Mayen

text:
Phil is generous and attentive British gentleman, it was fun to stay with him. I love his vigorous attitude to life and his taste in music!
All the best,
Anastasia

We had a wonderful time at Phil's: being invited over to his mate's party, got beaten in trivial pursuit  (it was british though ;)) and shared a brilliant dinner, phil made for us. Phil is super-laid-back, easy to talk to and interested in tons of good things. His flat is massive and he always tries to make you feel as comfy as possible (also in choosing the right cabs to make it home safe and sound... haha).
Defo not the last time meeting you THANKS

Staying with Phil was simply fantastic! Even though we arrived on very short notice, he was quick to response, reliable and welcoming. We had our own guest bed room in his beautiful appartment located close to Central Station - and he even cooked dinner! Phil is an inspiring person to chat with, fun and full of spirits - he definitely made our spontaneous trip to Copenhagen special! Thank you for everything :)
phil is a pain to catch up on a bike, but a joy to sing beach house with. cheers for hosting :) !

My friend and I had the most wonderful time staying at Phil's place. Even though, we did not meet in person, he trusted us with his home and made sure that we had a very good time in Copenhagen. 
I hope I will get to meet him in person though because from the conversations we had, he sounds like a pretty awesome guy with lots of stories to share! 
Thanks heaps!!!
Great place and person to hang out, he made my Copenhagen trip more awesome. Having dinner and Mikkeller hangout with also his bunch of awesome friends will make you feel like local. Will be back!

Very uncomplicated, funny and friendly host and very relaxed stay! He involved me into his everyday life (going out for a beer, cooking and having dinner with his friends) which I found nice, but also left enough free space which I also appreciated.

I had a great time at Phil's place. He was very welcoming, cooked me and another couchsurfer a wonderful dinner, let me beat him in British Trivial Pursuit and made me feel very much at home. Great vinyl collection by the way :)

I stayed with Phil for a few days and the experience was awesome! He is such a nice guy and made the Copenhagen experience even better. He showed me a little bit of his life in the city and made me love it as much as he does! His apartment is great and near everything, couldn't get any better!
Thanks a lot for everything Phil! :)
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Campinas, State of S√£o Paulo, Brazil

text: Phil was kind enough to host my friend Sarah and I very last minute when our accommodation fell through. He was the ultimate gentleman and a lovely host. He took us to the best brewery in Copenhagen both nights, and also cooked us a fantastic vegetarian meal (because my friend and I are vegetarian).  He is quite the chef! We stayed up late having fantastic conversation about our favorite music and music festivals while drinking wine. Phil also has an incredible record collection that Sarah and I admired. We also realized we both share a love of dogs, and he then admitted to me that my photo with my adorable dog was the only reason he decided to host us ;).  Phil has a beautifuk home and is very welcoming. We had the best time together. He is very witty and so much fun to be around. He is welcome to visit Sarah and I anytime. We hope to see him again because he is simply the best. Thank you Phil! ‚ù§Ô∏è The Sara(h)'s

Phil is a very cool guy. I feel completely at home in his beautiful apartment (amazing bathtub with a view!!) & with him. He is constantly up to something, Mad Max marathon, cooking sunday roast, good party, interesting gig, a cup of tea in the sofa...& I felt as welcome everywhere & every time. Met several of his friends & liked them all (do know that I like everything & everyone).
Phil is easygoing, open & has a warm heart. If you have the chance to meet him I say you should take it.
See you next time!!
response: {'id': '17670329', 'text': "What can I say about Frida? This beautiful soul touched both me and most of my friends over her short time in Copenhagen. She briefly raised our hopes of coming back, but alas, the hitching didn't work out and now she's also quit Facebook so we've no idea how life in the forest continues. Suffice to say, there is rarely a day that goes past that we don't think of her beautiful energy!", 'createdDate': '2015-06-10T17:42:00Z', 'experience': 'positive', 'relationshipType': 'host', 'isPostTrip': False, 'to': {'id': '1564278'}, 'from': {'id': '229733', 'publicName': 'Phil Chambers', 'publicAddress': {'id': '2935225', 'description': 'K√∏benhavn, K√∏benhavn, Denmark'}, 'avatarUrl': 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/ht-images.couchsurfing.com/u/229733/D482301B-F013-4C14-98AA-0B2398462A52', 'status': 'yes', 'isVerified': True, 'isDeleted': False, 'blockedBy': None}, 'inverseReference': None, 'response': None}

text:
I had a fantastic time at Phil's place. Even he was a little busy those days and we couldn't spend much time together, made me feel like home, cooked really nice vegetarian dinner and brought me to a cool Funky session (Please, I need you give me the name of the band!) :-)

From the very first moment I had the feeling that Phil is super intelligent guy, generous, kind and extra talkative. His british accent made the rest.

And about his place, probably is one of the best I have been hosted. The most awesome and splendid flat ever and very well located! Cozy, charming and with this kind of Scandinavian style present in every corner. You will be delighted with Phil's great taste for decoration!

Thanks man for EVERYTHING. Hope to see you around Barcelona or the world! :-)

A bit about my trip to Copenhagen... All I wanted from it was Noma, seeing a bit of the city and my friend and then a couch for a night. I really wasnt like into bonding or anything - yes, that what is travelling all about I guess, but that time I just wanted to be...there and not being stressed out. Couchsurfing can be stressful, when a person is not replying-so my hopes were tiny seeing that response rate(sorry had to mention it) that Phil would ever host me.I bet he was persuaded by my double-heart-wrecking text to host me- and to persuade his friend to actually "babysit" me till he returns from the airport and feed me beer and vietnamese food (not literally, no worries here) so I didnt feel alone. Once in Phil¬¥s flat,it turned out to be uhm pure luxury with an interesting library, and I didnt say no when offered olives and yummy wine!
I was even brought some breakfast croissants from his flat mate, must have been cause I looked rough :)

Thanks for the wonderful stay and c u soon.

My life has been changed thanks to Phil's incredibly delicious roast. Aside from his superb cooking skills he is a super duper host. His place has got style and you're sure to find yourself with a glass of red on a daily basis. 
Great music taste, great place, great guy! 
Thanks Phil :)

I had an amazing experience in Copenhague because of Phil! He is a great guy super intelligent, he sings and plays the guitar really goodd and he cooks amazing! !!! I felt like home so thanks for everything! ! Just tell me when you're coming to argentina I'll be waiting for you!!!!
Phil is ace. Contagious energy, brimming with passion, generally lovely to be with. Copenhagen is an amazing city to explore, but hanging with Phil is just as lovely!

text: Phil is a really kind, open and relaxed guy with the most awesome flat. Even though we haven¬¥t seen each other very often, we still enjoyed our stay a lot. And Juliane definitely had a very nice and special birthday. Thank you again, Phil!!

Writing this reference from our beach spot in the highly underrated Halmstad, where we are recuperating after admirable alcohol and BBQ consumption at Phil's beautiful flat in central CPH. I think it's fair to say we all had a jolly good time. Would be great to meet up with you again. Keep up the yoga. Ruby and Maddy xx

First of all: I miss your Biritsh accent!!!:P It was amazing to have met you and you have been an awesome host! It was so nice (and DELICIOUS) that you cooked dinner for us and thanks for the great wine and danish beer! I'll always remember you singing and playing the guitar and Johanna with her Ukulele!!! I really really hope to meet you again one day! You are a really nice, funny and generous person! Thank you for everything :)

like all the people who have been couch in the apartment of Phil... i loved !
great place, great host and great parties ! thanks to you i loved cph !!!
you are welcome to Toulouse to come back in the places of the best year of your life ;)

Oh man, Phil's hosting was top shelf. It doesn't hurt that his home is one of the most beautiful pieces of real estate in Copenhagen, in an amazing location, but more than that was the fresh tomato-basil soup we were making five minutes after I arrived and the hilarious conversation. Pro-tip: don't let him convince you that he always drinks on a weeknight. ;-)

text: Michael is the sweetest most easygoing generous person ever. He welcomed me in his place even when he wasn't home. He took me around the city and I had an absolutely great time. His place is so clean and conveniently located close to everything. I enjoyed every minute I spent with Michael. Don't miss a chance to meet him! :)

Michael, his friend and his lovely queer couchsurfer ladies ;) really came in the right moment for me. I am so happy I have met these lovable people, otherwise my time in CPH would have been never so hyggelig. I know I said thank you a lot of times by now, but I really mean it!
He is a very funny, friendly person and a real gentleman. He knows a lot about CPH and I felt in very safe hands with him and his friends. The night out was so much fun and the next day we went for a great lunch bar. All in all a great meet-up!!!

Mange, mange tak and I hope one day I can return the favor!

Hope to see you soon again ! :)
Hugs

Infact I would say the conversations with him will actually get you thinking. His visit to India was perhaps not so great so Micahel come to India and we will change your opinion about it :)

text: Osama is a gracious host. He hosted me for almost a week in June 2015 on his comfy air bed.  He's very laid back, flexible and always up for an experience. He also helped my cycle all over Copenhagen!

Anna has a beautiful, open and integrative personality ! She directly invited us for having dinner with her and her friends  (flatmates) :)  All of them are open people to whom it was easy and very pleasant to talk with. 
Anna seemed like and easy going tough girl who is going to explore several countries soon,so I can just recommend every future host this sympathic young women to offer her a bed for a night!

Anna was a wonderful host and extremely welcoming into her home. Particularly easy going and easy to talk to! On arrival she had set up a projector for watching the world cup for us to watch the world cup even though she wasn't into football and had also arranged a bbq with all of her friends. This was very enjoyable and I felt very thankful for the amount of effort she put into this and the rest of my stay :). The memory of this and going to the meat packing district on my 2nd night will make it difficult to leave Copenhagen. Thank you for my stay Anna, all the best :)

text:
My stay at Anders' place was amazing. 
He's incredibly warm and hospitable. 
He made me discover his neighborhood, we had some great moments with his friends and at his place. 
I'd highly recommend staying with him and hope to visit again soon!
I couldn't dream better for my first CS experience. 
Thanks again champ'!

Max and his lovely cousin Louise have hosted me on two different occasions, once when I gave them WAAAY to much notice (about three months) and once when I have them about two days. On my first trip Lousie made me feel really welcome, gave me great recommendations on how to make the best of my short stay in Copenhagen, made me cups of delicious tea and lent me a very useful map. On my second trip even though I was held up by transport and arrived late, Max and Lousie were really understanding and still made me feel like a welcome surfer and not a burden. I wish I could have spent more time staying with them, and if I ever go back to Copenhagen I would definately want to stay with them again. PERFECT hosts.

He lent me his bike for the whole weekend to cruise through Copenhagen, made me discover the best meat packing place, the organic food markets, the chilled atmosphere of the harbour sitting on a piece of wood in front of a giant fire. He's very easy to talk to as well, I felt like I was talking to an old friend from Minute 1, he has highly interesting hindsights about Danish culture too. Thanks again Geoffroy for the great weekend and am looking forward to seeing /hosting  you one day in Paris! 
Take care!!!

text:
Magnus is a cool guy! Super chill and flexible. He's living with his friend Balder, thanks him for meeting us! 

Me and my friend stayed in their place some days and felt like home. We were cooking together, talking, drawing, having fun.  That's the main thing of Couchsurfing I think. To feel comfortable and chill and have some fun time together. And guys are absolutely great hosts in this case! 

Hope to see you in Stockholm or Russia one day!

We stayed at Magnus place for 2 nights and it was a very good experience! He is a very kind and open minded person who opened his home to us with great hospitality. He gave us advice about nice places in the city and helped us with our questions. I can totally recommend him as a host as we were very happy with our stay. :) thank you, Magnus!

Magnus hosted me and my friend for one night and two days and it was definitely not enough! He's a warm, helpful, hospitable and fun guy, we enjoyed staying with him a lot. He showed us around, took us to nice places to chillout and comforted us perfectly after the accident we had had :P Magnus is a great ans reliable person, we made the best choice to spend our time in Copenhagen with him (and I can't forget to mention his super friendly mates!) and I'm sure we'll meet again in the future, either in Poland or in Copenhagen to explore more hidden spots of Christiania together ;)

I had a nice time in K√∏benhavn, thanks in large part to Magnus and Balder! Great hosts helped me with everything I need and even more. It was a joy to have supper together with good music and permanent jokes. Last but not least excellent cooking)

Magnus and Balder are really nice and friendly ! It was kind of an unexpected couchsurfing, great experience ;) see you guys!

I hope to see you again in Copenhagen or in Paris.

Hans is really nice guy , he invited us a lot of places and really tried to help us.

Hans is amazing. He hosted me for about four nights and rode me around Copenhagen on his awesome bike. His apartment was lovely and his taste in art rather eclectic. He also works at this cool bar and has really lovely friends. I want him to come stay on my couch in New Zealand!

Oh Hans Kristian Andersen... he could not have been more helpful to me in my traveling time of need! text:
Thank you so much for letting me and my friend stay at your place for one night. So helpfull from we got to the airport, explained how we could get easy to his place, and told us what attractions in Copenhagen to do. He also picked some really good strawberries that we got when we got back from our sightseeing in Copenhagen, and he also where so friendly that he offered to drive us to the airport in the morning when our flight was going early. Really recommend. Thank you so much for hosting us! 

Best regards from Silje and Jenna

I am so glad that he is my first experience on my next 3 week travel. He is such a sweet heart. My airline got delayed, and he was completely understanding about it. He even drove to the airport to pick me up, and luckily he had a day off work, so he showed me everything! I had a list of things to see and he showed them all to me, and the coast drive was stunning! I couldn't believe how it was still daylight at midnight! His home is beautiful, its huge and the couches are sooo comfortable. He's very respectful, polite, hes funny, and very kind. You are in great hands with him. He's a definite must be with for your first visit in Denmark! Thank you so much, we will stay in touch and hopefully see each other again!

Me and my friend stayed at Sheraz for one night and it was a very nice experience. He is very responsible, respectful and thoughtful and made our stay memorable. Even though his place is not in the center of Copenhagen, he offered us a ride back and forth to Copenhagen. His place is nice and clean. Sheraz and his friend were very sociable, we shared our travel and life experiences and had very nice conversations. They even took us to Kronborg castle, in Helsing√∏r which is about an hour drive from Copenhagen! It was very nice to spend time together and hopefully we will keep in touch and see each other again. 
Thank you Sheraz for everything, it was very nice to meet you!!!

I spent one night in Sheraz place. His home is really lovely and cozy place close to beautiful lake. He was really nice company, he is really talkative and friendly guy with such a great heart. Even if he had some things to do, he found time for me and showed me around Copenhagen in couple of hours. I really appreciate that he took me to the airport in the morning because of my early flight. 

Thanks for everything Sheraz.:)

Sheraz is definitely a very nice host that you cannot miss. He drove all the way to pick me up in the midnight so that I could get away from a very weird guy I met right after I arrived Copenhagen. I couldn't be more thankful about that. Since the villa is quite far from city center by bus and I didn't have Danish money with me, Sheraz came to take me to the center during the break time of his work. He's willing to spend time with guest, his roommate (Nirven) is very nice to always care what do you need as well. I knew Copenhagen /Denmark a lot from their perspectives and I hope I could get a job there real soon, and share more stories together! Until then, good luck and take care!:)

I stayed with Kasper for 5 nights in August. He was so amazing with communication from first response to last. He kept in touch with me before my stay to make sure I found him okay and was extremely flexible with his time as I was a little last minute. Kasper is SUPER chill. Haha. He could probably get along with anyone and make them feel comfortable. He's a busy guy but will gladly make time to show you around and give many tips. His home is beautiful, spacious, and clean with a nice balcony that I took advantage of to enjoy a nice ros√®. His home is located about 12mins by bike to most tourist attractions and a bus stop is right across the street. I took a Flixbus in to Copenhagen and that station is only 15mins by one bus from Kasper; it was soooo convenient! Thank you so much Kasper for your generosity and introducing me to VR and GOT !ü§£ Anyone who stays with you is very lucky and I cant wait to see you in France or Chicago!

Kasper! Incredible guy! 
Even though we didn‚Äôt spent enough time together, he was always ready to answer my questions. Trustful. Easy going. Positive. Funny. Caring. Life-lover. Those are the words that I might use to describe what I‚Äôve seen ‚Äúsuperficially‚Äù on him. 
He welcomed me giving me everything to make me feel as at home, towels, food, advices, realizing that I found a spot of Italianness through his great sense of welcome, almost as an Southern Italian friend can do. 
Also, if you appreciate being independent, I guarantee you that Kasper is the perfect host and his house is definitely the best place for whom is into films, video games and relax. I‚Äôm sure there‚Äôs much more that I haven't known yet but I'll know it for sure!

text:
I had the pleasure of hosting Agata and her daughter for 2 nights. 

Agata is both physicaly and mentally agile. She rock climbs like a boss and is soon to be a blackbelt in Aikido. She knows a lot of computer programming languages and she speaks more languages than anyone I know.

We had a lot in common so it was easy to just sit and talk with her hour after hour.

She is the kind of person that leaves feeling inspired after having a chat with her. 

She has done a great job raising her beauftiful daughter Magda who is going to be one of the biggest ballet dancers Denmark has ever produced.

When I do my European road trip I would love to visit you guys.

Stay in touch xx

text:
it's hard to say how excited i was to meet agata..! a traveling mom plus her teenage daughter to report about their adventurous lives.. that was the encouragement i needed.. and she really IS amazing!! i was fascinated by listening to her when she told about her many trips and hiking tours with her kids even when they were still so small.. and later on we would crouch on the corridor of my flat because all the rooms were occupied by our sleeping children and talk half night long.. as openly as with a really good friend.. and there was a lot to talk about!!
it was also great that they joined the critical mass with us.. - a nice coincidence that they had arrived in vienna on their bikes just one day before the demonstration.. how lucky they were.. and i was happy that they liked it..! my kids had a very good time with the two young ladies, once painting the street with colourful chalks, and liked agata's delicious pancakes a lot.. ! we have to meet again!!

text: Agata and Magda were wonderful surfers! They brought chocolate and a determination to make it to the highest point in Wales and England, and we shared both with great success. I was very grateful to have them as my first surfers and had such a fun weekend with them. Full of riddles and nice conversation, they were clean and courteous, couldn't ask for more in a Couchsurfer! They really embodied what the project is all about. I hope that we can meet again, this time on their side of the world! Or maybe on top of another mountain would be nice too...
response: {'id': '8585382', 'text': 'Marcus is a gentle and considerate host, that makes you feel welcome well before arrival. text:
Agata is a very heartfelt person, she welcomed us (me and my boyfriend) in her house with her joyful family and we felt at home in a second. When we arrived she had prepared dinner for us too: the vegetarian version of a danish dish, very tasty! We had some wonderful conversations about cooking, games and much more. She also suggested many different places and activities for us.
We slept in the living room on the couch and a mattress, she gave us sheets and towels. We were indipendent, since she provided us with a copy of the apartment keys.
Everything was very appreciated and we absolutely recommend staying with her and her family!

Agata welcomed me with a hug and immediately made me feel just like at home, by handing me the keys and offering to join her in her afternoon activities. Her vast knowledge and experience makes her an formidable conversation partner, and an excellent source of information for any traveller. 
 My stay with her truly was a pleasure.

Agata is the sweetest person ever! She made my bed to stay on, and offered her home as if it were my own. Even though my stay was short, we did so much together! I got to meet her son, and we all cooked dinner together. She took me rock climbing and gave me a ton of tips and food for thought. We also had a nice dinner at one of her favorite restaurants, which was fantastic. Agata has a wonderful zest for life and I am so lucky to have shared my amazing Copenhagen trip with her. I wouldn't have had it any other way.

Staying at Agata's place was an amazing experience. She is a lovely person! And her cats are sweet, playful and lovely too :)!!!
Agata shared with us her travel experiences and adventurous spirit, now we want to travel even more than before!!
She cooked both an awesome breakfast and Danish dinner "burning love", it was super tasty!! We got lucky to meet her son, and her flatmate Peter, both of them were an amazing companion. 
Her place is centrally located, it's really easy to reach by metro, bus, or even walk everywhere. 
We hope to see you all again soon, maybe in Mexico or maybe somewhere else in the world. Thanks for everything! 
Liz and Adrian.

Agata is a very special person. She allow me to stay in her home for one week, in christmas week, it was a very new and wonderful experience, I was alone and take care her cats, I dont know a lot of her because I just talk one day but she is very open mind very evolution people, she trusted in me, I hope I was good with you! You know that you have a home in Buenos Aires when you want!!
Thank you very much for everythhing!

Agata is great host! I stayed with my Mom for a three nights at her place in Copenhagen. She invited us even if she had other plans for the weekend. We are really grateful for that and for this short time which we could spend together and chat and for advices what we could see in Copenhagen. 
It was really nice to meet you! :)

agata is a very inspiring woman that tries to live the life to the fullest and wants to share her living with the community ..she is very giving and doing a lot of fun things. very open and flexible and very helpfull.loved staying with her and her daughter

Had a great chat with Agata and her family and cats ;) Such a lovely woman with so much interest in learning from each other. She does really interesting vegetarian meals! Dont miss it! Thank you so much for keeping me warm in my stay in Denmark, Agata. Til next time :)

Agata was an amazing host, I'm so grateful for my time at her apartment.  The cats were both wild and sweet, the little one especially.  I can't beleive how easy she made my stay in Copenhagen, I really feel very lucky to have met her and her family and to have had such a comfortable and safe place to stay while I was there.

Thank you!
I've had an amazing time with Agata and her family. They are certainly experienced traveling and represent the true CS spirit. They've hosted me for 4 days and I can only say THANK YOU.

Agata was my first host ever. She & her daughter made my stay in Copenhagen special! They are very welcoming, generous & fun to hang out with. Her home was cozy and she was very welcoming as well as her 2 childrens. It was one of the best experience with couchsurfing community and I definitely recommend Agata as a surfer or host : )

I stayed 1 night at Agata's place, and I really enjoyed it! It was not long but Agata and her daughter did everything to make my trip better. Successfully :) I really enjoyed to be with an other dancer and I am really thankful for the bike what I could borrow from you, Agata! Hope you have a good time in Spain! :)

Agata was incredibly nice. Even though she was very busy, she invited me to local events in Copenhagen and gave me great tips about how to explore the city. Renting a bicycle and doing a full day trip with it was a great idea, and thanks for the gloves as well! I enjoyed staying with Agata and her daughter and also the small discussions we had. Her breakfast was great and her daughter plays the guitar well.

Agata and her family are very helpful :) when i came to Odense for Erasmus, they host me for 4 nights :) we cooked some traditional foods, played games for dishes :), talked about our hobbies and cultures. somenights her boy played Baglama and her daughter played guitar :) also, i taught them the game backgammon :) and we made a backgammon tournament :) further, she gave a map, and sometimes she gave me her own bike. and she took me and my huge luggages to my dorm with her car :) i am very greatful to Agata and her family :) :) :)

Juan and his flatmates Alejandro and Camilo are some very friendly, openminded and helpful hosts, who took us in for 4 nights. They gladly helped my friend and I to find out about London and gave us some great tips about where to go. We didn't spend much time together as we were out most of the day, but my impression of them was positive. They like to party, so this is the perfect spot if you're looking to have a fun time in London! 
The only thing the guests should be aware of is that the couches were pretty small to sleep in and the temperature in the room where we slept was very low, and we didn't have any blankets, so as a guest it is a good idea to bring that yourself, otherwise you won't get much sleep. 
Other than that, thank you for a nice stay!

For me he was not commited with the stay.
 I didnt felt confortable or welcome because he changed mind lots of times (about to receive me or not, about time to arrive, and about how many days) and all of this after accept my stay.
I was going to his city to work in a event, so it was not a touristic travel. Is importante to say this because I was clear with him about it, and it was important to me to be sure where I should stay.
We had problems with the communication at the begining because he didnt receive my msg, that result he accepted another guest and could not receive when I arrive. 
Even like this, he was able to receive me few days later. We deal a time, that he changed, and few hours before he let me know I should stay less days taht was planed... 
In resume, during my 5 days I should change place 3 times because of this.
After all of this I decided don't stay with him and don't recommend. :-/
